    "npc_notes": "HYDRA\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 5 to 12\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 5 to 12\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6, 1-8, or 1-10 according to size\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Multiple heads and attacks\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Body dies only when all heads are killed\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Hydrae are reptilian monsters found in marshes, swamps, and similar places, as well as in subterranean lairs. Their large, four-legged bodies are surmounted by from 5 to 12 heads. Roll an 8-sided die to determine the number. Each head has 1 hit die of a full 8 hit points. When all of a hydra’s heads are killed, the body dies, but not until every head is destroyed. The hydra attacks according to the number of heads it has, each head being considered as a hit die. It is possible for the hydra to attack several opponents at once, and up to 4 heads are able to attack the same target simultaneously. Damage is based on the number of heads: 5-6 heads do 1-6, 7-10 heads do 1-8, and 11-12 heads do 1-10. Description: Hydrae are gray-brown to blackish brown with lighter underbellies tinged toward yellow or tan. Their eyes are amber to orange. Their teeth are yellowish white.",
