    "npc_notes": "KI-RIN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -5\nMOVE: 24\"/48\"\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: 5%\nTREASURE TYPE: I, S, T\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8/2-8/3-18\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Magic use\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: 90% magic resistance\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 90%\nINTELLIGENCE: Supra-genius\nALIGNMENT: Lawful good\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 130 to 200\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\n\nNotes: The ki-rin are a race of aerial creatures whose hooves rarely touch the earth, for they dwell amongst the clouds and behind the winds. Females are never encountered, and ki-rin are always solitary. They sometimes aid humans if properly abjured or if the need to combat evil is great. They also sometimes travel the Astral and Ethereal Planes. A ki-rin attacks with two powerful hoof blows and a thrust from a magically sharp +3 horn much resembling that of a unicorn.\n\nKi-rin are able to employ spells of all levels at 18th-level quality: 9 first-level, 8 second-level, 7 third-level, 6 fourth-level, 5 fifth-level, 4 sixth-level, 3 seventh-level, 2 eighth-level, and 1 ninth-level spell during any given day. They also command 4 major and 6 minor psionic disciplines, operating at ninth level of mastery in all. Once per day each, a ki-rin can create nutritious food for 2-24 persons, create drinkable beverages for 2-24 persons, create soft goods or wooden items, create temporary metal items up to 2,000 gold pieces weight, create a lasting illusion with auditory, visual, and olfactory components, assume gaseous form, wind walk, call lightning, and summon weather. When a ki-rin conjures things of the sky or involving air, the creature or magic is at twice normal strength, including hit points and damage inflicted. Ki-rin speak their own tongue, but by special telepathic speech they can converse with virtually any living thing. Description: the coat of the ki-rin is luminous gold like a sunrise on a clear day. Its mane and tail are darker gold, its horn and hooves are golden pink, and its eyes are violet. Its hide is worth 25,000 gold pieces if perfectly intact.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_ki_rin"
  },
