    "npc_notes": "KOBOLD\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 40-400\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 1-4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals J, O; Q (×5) in lair\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 or by weapon\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: -1 to hit in bright sunlight\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average (low)\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: S (3' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: The society of these creatures is tribal, with war bands based on gens. Stronger tribes rule weaker ones. Kobolds are usually found in dank, dark places such as dismal overgrown forests or subterranean settings. They hate bright sunlight, not being able to see well in it, but their night vision is excellent, and they have infravision operating to 60'. If they are in bright sunlight, they fight at -1 on attack rolls. Kobolds hate most other life, delighting in killing and torture. They particularly hate brownies, pixies, sprites, and gnomes, and they war continually with the latter, attacking them on sight. In addition to the tongues of lawful evil and kobolds, these monsters can usually, 75% of the time, speak goblin and orcish. Description: kobold hide runs from very dark rusty brown to rusty black. They have no hair. Their eyes are reddish, their small horns tan to white, and they favor red or orange garb. Kobolds live up to 135 years.\n\nA force of kobolds is typically equipped as follows: short sword and javelin 5%, short sword and spear 10%, short sword 10%, axe 20%, spiked wooden club 30%, javelins 15%, and spear 10%. All kobold shields are of wood or wickerwork.",
