    "npc_notes": "LEPRECHAUN\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1 or 1-20\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 2-5 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: F\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 0\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Theft; illusion; invisibility; object polymorph; ventriloquism\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Keen hearing; 80% magic resistance\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 80%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Leprechauns normally dwell only in fair green lands with lush hills and dales, though adventurous bands sometimes reside elsewhere for a time. These small magical and mischievous beings can become invisible at will, polymorph nonliving objects, create illusions, and use ventriloquism as often as they like. Their keen ears prevent surprise. Being full of mischief, they often, 75% of the time, snatch valuable objects from persons, turn invisible, and dash away. The stolen object will be valuable, and there is a 75% chance of successful theft. If pursued closely, there is a 25% chance per turn of pursuit that the leprechaun drops the stolen goods. If caught or discovered in its lair, the leprechaun attempts to mislead the captor into believing its treasure is being surrendered, while actually duping the victim. Great care is required to obtain the treasure. Leprechauns are very fond of wine, and this weakness may be used against them. Rumor has it they are a species of halfling with a strong strain of pixie.",
