    "npc_notes": "LICH\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 11+\n% IN LAIR: 90%\nTREASURE TYPE: A\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysis; fear; spell use\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +1 or better weapon to hit; many spell immunities\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Supra-genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (evil)\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: See below\nAttack/Defense Modes: See below\n\nNotes: A lich exists because of its own desires and the use of powerful and arcane magic. It passes from humanity into a non-human, non-living existence through force of will and retains this state by special conjurations, enchantments, and a phylactery. A lich is most often encountered in hidden chambers, typically in wilderness areas or vast underground labyrinths, and in any case in a strong stone structure and deep darkness. Through the power that changes it, the lich gains armor equivalent to +1 plate and +1 shield, and its hit dice become d8s. It can be affected only by magical attacks or by monsters with magical properties or 6 or more hit dice. Liches were formerly ultra-powerful magic-users or magic-user/clerics of not less than 18th level of magic-use. Their touch is so cold as to inflict 1-10 points of damage and paralyze opponents who fail their saving throw. The mere sight of a lich causes any creature below 5th level or 5 hit dice to flee in panic. All liches retain spell ability appropriate to the level they had attained before becoming undead. The following spells or attack forms have no effect on liches: charm, sleep, enfeeblement, polymorph, cold, electricity, insanity, and death spells or symbols. A lich appears much like a wight or mummy, skeletal in form, with black eye sockets containing glowing points of light, and usually wearing rich but rotting garments.",
