    "npc_notes": "LURKER ABOVE\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (1-4)\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 1\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 10\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: C, Y\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Smothering constriction; surprise on 1-4\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (20' wing spread)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: The lurker above is a carnivorous subterranean creature. In large chambers or caves there may be as many as 4, but usually only 1 is found. It can creep slowly along surfaces or generate a gas which gives it neutral buoyancy, allowing it to flap its wing-like appendages and fly about. It surprises prey on 1-4. When disturbed, the lurker drops from the ceiling and smothers all creatures beneath in the tough folds of its wings. This constriction causes 1-6 points of damage per round, and victims will smother in 2-5 rounds regardless unless they kill the lurker and break free. Unintelligent, it fights until dead. Prey caught in its grip cannot fight unless the weapons used are short and already in hand when the creature falls. It somewhat resembles a huge manta ray, and its grayish belly is so textured as to appear like stone. Normally attached to a ceiling, it is almost impossible to detect, 90% unlikely unless actually prodded.",
