      "npc_notes": "ABOLETH\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 3\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: F\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 4\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6/1-6/1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Sliming touch, illusion, enslavement, mucus cloud\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Slime\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 250\nAttack/Defense Modes: C, D, E / G, I, J\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1275 + 10/hp\n\nAboleths are ancient amphibious horrors dwelling in subterranean lakes and caverns. They are highly intelligent, hate most surface life, and seek to enslave or destroy land-dwellers. Their race is said to preserve lore older than mankind, and that knowledge is widely rumored to be foul and terrible.\n\nAn aboleth has a fish-like, slime-covered body, a great fluked tail, three slit-like eyes set one above another, and four tentacles extending from the top of its head. Its mouth is toothless and located on the underside. In water it swims with ease; on land it drags itself with its tentacles.\n\nIn combat it strikes with all four tentacles. Any creature hit must save vs. spells or its skin begins changing into a clear, slimy membrane within 2-5 rounds. A cure disease cast before the change is complete will stop the transformation. Once completed, the membrane must be kept damp with cool water or the victim suffers 1-12 points of damage each turn from intense pain. A cure serious wounds spell restores normal skin.\n\nThe creature can create realistic visual and audible illusions so long as it concentrates fully on doing so. It may also attempt to enslave a single creature up to 30 feet away, three times per day. The victim must save vs. spells or become compelled to serve the aboleth. Enslaved creatures will not usually fight for it, but will obey telepathic orders. If separated from the aboleth by more than a mile, the victim may attempt a new saving throw once per day. Remove curse, dispel magic, or the death of the aboleth breaks this bond.\n\nWhile in water, the aboleth secretes a mucus cloud extending 1 foot around its body. Any creature drawn into it must save vs. poison or inhale the substance and lose the ability to breathe air, suffocating in 2-12 rounds if it attempts to do so. The same mucus may be used to allow slaves to breathe water for 1-3 hours, as a potion of water breathing. Soap or wine dissolves the mucus.",
