the death of the aboleth breaks this bond.\n\nWhile in water, the aboleth secretes a mucus cloud extending 1 foot around its body. Any creature drawn into it must save vs. poison or inhale the substance and lose the ability to breathe air, suffocating in 2-12 rounds if it attempts to do so. The same mucus may be used to allow slaves to breathe water for 1-3 hours, as a potion of water breathing. Soap or wine dissolves the mucus.",
