      "npc_notes": "AFANC\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: Swim 15\"\nHIT DICE: 15\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 or 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 5-20 or 1-12/1-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Whirlpool\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (evil)\nSIZE: L (50' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/4000 + 20/hp\n\nThe afanc is a dreaded sea-beast commonly mistaken at a distance for some sort of whale. It inhabits shallow salt water and is feared chiefly because of its power to generate deadly whirlpools.\n\nIt may attack by bite for 5-20 points of damage, or by battering with its two flippers for 1d12 points each, but it more often preys upon surface craft. It circles its target at speed, beginning about 100 feet out and closing by 20 feet per round until within 40 feet. In so doing it accelerates far beyond its normal swim rate, sometimes reaching 30\" or more. This motion creates a whirlpool sufficient to drag down a small or small-medium ship up to about 60 feet in length. Such vessels are pulled under at a rate of 10 feet per round.\n\nIt avoids larger ships. Since 5-8 rounds of circling are needed to form the whirlpool, and because the afanc must remain near the surface to do so, heavy missile fire or magic may drive it off before the vortex is fully established. Small boats, rafts, and similar craft of 30 feet or less are usually rushed directly, capsized, and their occupants devoured.\n\nThe afanc resembles a cross between a whale and a great fish. Its body is whale-like, its head more fish-like, and its tail is vertical. It is gray to blue-gray in color. Though fish, it breathes both air and water.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
