      "npc_notes": "ANNIS\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 7+3 to 7+12\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: D\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-9/2-9/3-9\nDAMAGE/ATTACK WITH STRENGTH BONUS: 9-16/9-16/3-9\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Grappling, fog cloud\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: 100% vs. illusion/phantasm magic only; change self; iron-hard skin\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (7½'-8' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1300 + 10/hp\n\nAnnis are powerful hag-like giantesses related to night hags, though they dwell naturally upon the Prime Material Plane. They are larger and physically stronger than their planar kin and are especially fond of human flesh, though they will eat nearly anything. They may be found alone, in small groups, or in rough association with ogres, trolls, or evil giants.\n\nAn annis attacks with iron-hard talons and vicious teeth. Its Strength equals that of a hill giant, and it favors grappling. If it hits the same opponent with all three attacks in a single round, it automatically seizes that victim after inflicting damage. Thereafter its attacks on the held opponent automatically hit each round unless the victim is stronger, the annis is slain, or the victim escapes by magic. It then rends and bites until the captive is dead.\n\nIt may also use fog cloud offensively to confuse or delay stronger enemies. Defensively it can employ change self to appear as a large human, ogre, or similar being. These spell-like powers are usable twice per day each, one at a time, one per round, functioning at 8th level.\n\nIts skin is hard as iron. For purposes of weapon vs. armor adjustment, treat it as though wearing plate mail. In addition, edged weapons inflict -1 damage, while blunt weapons inflict +1 damage. Flails and morning stars count as blunt for this purpose.\n\nAnnis possess normal infravision, but their hearing and sense of smell are superior. They speak their own tongue, Ogre, common Giant, and some Common. Smarter specimens may also know humanoid languages. They are deep blue in complexion with glossy black hair, teeth, and nails, and usually greenish or yellow eyes. Their bodies are tall, thin, wiry, and muscular.",
