    "npc_notes": "ANT LION\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 9\" (1\" in loose soil)\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: 95%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 5-20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Pit trap, latch bite\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/575 + 10/hp\n\nGiant ant lions are enormous insects found in sandy, gravelly, or rocky regions where giant ants and similar prey are common. Their favored habitats include desert fringes, badlands, and rough terrain.\n\nThey dig great funnel-shaped pits roughly 60 feet in diameter. Half the time such a pit resembles a cave mouth or lair entrance. Any creature entering the pit has a 50% chance each round of slipping down the loose sides into the bottom, where the ant lion lies hidden beneath sand and stones. It bursts forth and seizes the victim in its enormous mandibles.\n\nA successful bite means the ant lion clamps onto the prey and will not release it until one or the other dies. After the initial hit, it automatically inflicts 5-20 points of damage each round thereafter. Though ant lions do not hoard treasure, there is a 30% chance their lairs contain 1-4 items from previous victims: coins, shields, metal weapons, jewelry, or miscellaneous goods. Any such item has a 10% chance to be magical if appropriate.\n\nAnt lions eat one or more giant insects per day and drag the remains away to conceal them. It is therefore possible, though less common, to encounter one outside its pit.",
    "id": "monster_manual_ii_ant_lion"
  },
