      "npc_notes": "ASPIS COW\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 3\"\nHIT DICE: 10\n% IN LAIR: 95%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3-18\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Acidic slime\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1350 + 14/hp\n\nThe cow is the fertile female of the species. Unlike larvae that mature into drones, the cow remains in larval form, growing into a huge, bloated creature 10-15 feet long. Its sole purpose is to lay eggs for the nest.\n\nIt is sluggish, but its size makes its bite dangerous. In addition, its skin exudes a milky acidic slime that destroys metal or wood in 1 round and burns exposed flesh for 1-8 points of damage per round until washed away.\n\nAspis nests are underground complexes bored through dirt or soft rock. They generally include 1-3 egg chambers, 2-4 granaries, 1-6 grub hatcheries, and a central chamber. Tunnels are usually about 4 feet high and are well guarded and trapped. Each nest contains only one cow. There is a 10% chance that 10-100 giant ants also inhabit the same nest.",
