      "npc_notes": "ATOMIE\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 30-120\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 12\"/24\" (MC: A)\nHIT DICE: 1/2\n% IN LAIR: 35%\nTREASURE TYPE: M, Q, C (magic)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spell-like powers, initiative bonus, diving or charging attacks\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: 20% magic resistance; great stealth and surprise\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to very\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral (good)\nSIZE: S (1' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/40 + 1/hp\n\nAtomies are the smallest of sprites and dwell only in secluded glens. They are nocturnal, emerging at night to gather food, frolic, and pursue the concerns common to fairy folk. Twenty percent of encounters place them with grigs.\n\nThey make their homes in great trees, lush banks, hollow trunks, underground chambers, and other hidden retreats. They are nimble and extremely swift, darting in with spear or sword before most opponents can react. They gain +1 on initiative rolls and attack as 3rd-level fighters.\n\nTypical armament includes small crossbows with a 3\" range doing 1-3 damage, small spears dealing 1-4 damage when thrust or thrown and double damage when used in diving or charging flight, and tiny swords functioning as knives for 1-3 damage.\n\nTheir spell-like powers are usable at will, one at a time, one per round, at 5th-level ability: blink, invisibility, pass plant, speak with animals, and summon insects.\n\nAtomies are 90% likely to surprise opponents and only 10% likely to be surprised themselves. Their hearing is twice human norm, and both infravision and ultravision extend to 120 feet. They speak their own dialect of Sprite, along with Pixie and some Common.",
