      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "AURUMVORAX\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 9\" (3\")\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: Incidental\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Clamp bite, automatic bite damage, 2-8 claw attacks after a successful bite\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Half damage from blunt weapons and large or magical fire; immune to poison, gas, and small normal fires\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/2700 + 16/hp\n\nThe aurumvorax, or golden gorger, is a vicious burrowing predator found in open or lightly forested areas. Though only about 1½ feet tall and 3 feet long, it weighs more than 500 pounds because its flesh is unnaturally dense.\n\nIt resembles a heavy badger with eight legs. When it attacks, it rushes from its burrow, bites, and clamps on. The initial bite inflicts 2-8 points of damage. Once it has a hold, it automatically inflicts 8 points of bite damage each following round and also gains 2-8 claw attacks for 1-6 damage each. A victim so seized loses Dexterity adjustment to Armor Class. The jaws do not release except in death.\n\nIts concealed den attack gives it a 50% chance to surprise. Due to its massive hide and dense bones, blunt weapons inflict only half damage. Small normal fires do nothing to it, and even large or magical fires inflict only half damage. Poison and gas are entirely ineffective.\n\nIts coat is bright golden, often gleaming like true gold. Its claws and teeth are coppery, its mane and whiskers bronzed, and its eyes are silvery with golden pupils.",
