      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "AZER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare (common on the Elemental Plane of Fire)\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4 (3-30)\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2+1 to 5+4\n% IN LAIR: Nil (20%)\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil (individuals Q; tripled in lair)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Heat\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to fire\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 5-20% (by size)\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to very\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: M (4½'-5' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n2+1 HD = II/40 + 3/hp\n3+2 HD = III/85 + 4/hp\n4+3 HD = III/130 + 5/hp\n5+4 HD = IV/225 + 6/hp\n\nAzers are a race of humanoids native to the Elemental Plane of Fire. They are common there, but almost never encountered elsewhere unless summoned. They resemble dwarves with brass-colored metallic skin and flaming hair. Their tough, metal-like skin accounts for their low armor class, and they wear only simple garments of beaten brass, copper, or bronze.\n\nCommon azers of 2+1 hit dice are encountered most often. Those of 3+2 hit dice are less common, the larger 4+3 hit dice azers still less so, and the strongest 5+4 hit dice specimens are rarest. The weaker sorts carry lesser gems, while stronger azers bear more valuable stones.\n\nAzers use broad-bladed javelins which do damage as spears, and in melee favor mallet-like weapons equivalent to a footman's mace. Because of their strength, both hit probability and damage are adjusted as follows:\n\n2+1 HD: Strength 17, +1 to hit, +1 damage\n3+2 HD: Strength 18, +1 to hit, +2 damage\n4+3 HD: Strength 18/01-50, +1 to hit, +3 damage\n5+4 HD: Strength 18/51-75, +2 to hit, +3 damage\n\nAny creature not immune to fire suffers 2-5 points of damage if grasped by an azer. The heat of an azer's weapons also adds +1 damage against such foes. However, azers cannot survive temperatures below 200°F for more than about an hour, and cold attacks inflict double normal damage upon them.\n\nAzers usually dwell in small groups in towers worked from the natural basalt of their fiery realm. They are unfriendly, taciturn, and compassionless, but also lawful in temperament. They prize clear purple and red gems, and once an azer gives its word, that bond is considered firm.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
