      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "BAKU\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare (very rare on the Prime Material Plane)\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (2-5)\nARMOR CLASS: -2\nMOVE: 21\"\nHIT DICE: 12+12\n% IN LAIR: 0\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3-18/2-12/2-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Trumpeting roar, psionics, use of magic devices\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Invisibility, etherealness, astral travel\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional to genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral good\nSIZE: L (9' or taller at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 180 + 2-24\nAttack/Defense Modes: B, E / F, G, I\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/4900 + 18/hp\n\nBaku are great elephant-like beings seldom seen in the wild, for most move invisibly among the settlements of mankind. On the Prime Material Plane they prefer semitropical forests, where groups of 2-5 may rarely be found. Their true home is on the neutral Upper Outer Planes.\n\nThough normally timid and peace-loving, baku hate evil and will openly combat malicious monsters. In this way they secretly protect humankind. Despite their size, they move rapidly. Their attacks consist of a goring butt and two trampling foreleg attacks, the latter usable only against man-sized or smaller foes. Their short prehensile trunks can manipulate simple items, so baku often carry magic weapons or devices.\n\nA baku can become invisible at will and remain so until it acts. It can also become ethereal and travel astrally. Its psionic powers include 12th-level animal telepathy, 6th-level body control, body equilibrium, 12th-level fighter cell adjustment, 12th-level detection of good or evil, 12th-level reduction, and shape alteration.\n\nOnce every 4 melee rounds, a baku may utter a trumpeting roar. All evil creatures within 4\" suffer 1-8 points of damage and must save vs. paralyzation or flee in panic as though affected by a fear spell cast by a 12th-level magic-user.\n\nA baku has an elephant-like head and short trunk, tusks curving backward from the lower jaw, rhino-like forelegs, leonine hind legs, and a draconian body covered with horny dorsal plates.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": "12"
    },
    "npc_notes": "BAKU\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare (very rare on the Prime Material Plane)\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (2-5)\nARMOR CLASS: -2\nMOVE: 21\"\nHIT DICE: 12+12\n% IN LAIR: 0\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3-18/2-12/2-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Trumpeting roar, psionics, use of magic devices\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Invisibility, etherealness, astral travel\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional to genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral good\nSIZE: L (9' or taller at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 180 + 2-24\nAttack/Defense Modes: B, E / F, G, I\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/4900 + 18/hp\n\nBaku are great elephant-like beings seldom seen in the wild, for most move invisibly among the settlements of mankind. On the Prime Material Plane they prefer semitropical forests, where groups of 2-5 may rarely be found. Their true home is on the neutral Upper Outer Planes.\n\nThough normally timid and peace-loving, baku hate evil and will openly combat malicious monsters. In this way they secretly protect humankind. Despite their size, they move rapidly. Their attacks consist of a goring butt and two trampling foreleg attacks, the latter usable only against man-sized or smaller foes. Their short prehensile trunks can manipulate simple items, so baku often carry magic weapons or devices.\n\nA baku can become invisible at will and remain so until it acts. It can also become ethereal and travel astrally. Its psionic powers include 12th-level animal telepathy, 6th-level body control, body equilibrium, 12th-level fighter cell adjustment, 12th-level detection of good or evil, 12th-level reduction, and shape alteration.\n\nOnce every 4 melee rounds, a baku may utter a trumpeting roar. All evil creatures within 4\" suffer 1-8 points of damage and must save vs. paralyzation or flee in panic as though affected by a fear spell cast by a 12th-level magic-user.\n\nA baku has an elephant-like head and short trunk, tusks curving backward from the lower jaw, rhino-like forelegs, leonine hind legs, and a draconian body covered with horny dorsal plates.",
    "id": "monster_manual_ii_baku"
  },
