      "npc_notes": "BARGHEST\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2 (1)\nARMOR CLASS: 2 to -4\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 6+6 to 12+12\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8 plus number of hit dice as bonus damage\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Life-devouring growth, spell-like powers\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Hit only by +1 or better magic weapons; special canine-form fire effect\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 5% per hit die (ignore pluses)\nINTELLIGENCE: High to genius\nALIGNMENT: Evil (lawful)\nSIZE: M to L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n6+6 HD = VII/1275 + 10/hp\n7+7 HD = VII/2000 + 12/hp\n8+8 HD = VIII/3450 + 14/hp\n9+9 HD = VIII/3600 + 14/hp\n10+10 HD = IX/6100 + 16/hp\n11+11 HD = IX/6250 + 16/hp\n12+12 HD = IX/7300 + 18/hp\n\nBarghests are among the most common and feared monsters of the rifts of Gehenna. Each tends to rule its own stronghold with a body of servants. At times a barghest spawns a litter of six whelps, which are sent to the Prime Material Plane to feed and grow by devouring the lives of men.\n\nYoung barghests are found alone or in pairs near isolated human settlements or among bands of goblins. In their natural form they closely resemble large goblins, and goblins recognize and worship them. Other races usually cannot tell them apart from ordinary goblins. Goblin hosts bring them human sacrifices, while barghests slay the goblins' stronger enemies and enrich their followers.\n\nA whelp begins with 6d8+6 hit points. For every energy level of human life it slays and devours, it gains 1 hit point; eight such levels effectively equal another hit die and +1 hit point per die. Zero-level humans count only as half an energy level. As the barghest grows, its armor class, strength, magic resistance, intelligence, and damage all increase. Upon attaining full power, it can shift itself back to Gehenna and establish its own valley-rift stronghold.\n\nBarghests can assume the form of a large dog or their goblin-like natural shape at will. They also possess the following spell-like powers at will, one operation per round: shape change to canine or goblin form, change self, levitation, misdirection, and projected image. Once per day they may use charm person or monster, dimension door, and emotion.\n\nIn canine form a barghest moves at up to double speed, passes without trace, and is 75% likely to go unnoticed when still, allowing surprise on 3 in 6. They are harmed only by +1 or better magic weapons. Fire does no damage to them, but if a barghest in canine form fails its save against magical fire such as fireball, flame strike, or meteor swarm, it is hurled back to Gehenna. A weak barghest so banished is often enslaved or slain there, and cannot return without outside aid.\n\nA whelp looks like a large goblin. As it matures its skin darkens from yellow toward bluish red, and fully grown adults are blue-skinned. In canine form they are nearly indistinguishable from large dogs, though other dogs instinctively fear and attack them.",
