      "npc_notes": "BASIDIROND\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 5+5\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: Incidental\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8 (+ smothering)\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Hallucinatory spores\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to mental attacks; cold slows and suppresses spores\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Special\nINTELLIGENCE: Unratable\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (evil)\nSIZE: M (6'-7' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/475 + 6/hp\n\nBasidironds are multi-stemmed fungoid monsters with leathery orange bodies and cone-shaped upper parts resembling inverted umbrellas, their undersides being sooty black. In combat they lash forward with these caps, striking for 2-8 points of damage and ejecting spores.\n\nA struck victim must save vs. poison or inhale spores that clog the respiratory tract. Unless cure disease or equivalent magic is applied, the victim will smother in 2-5 rounds.\n\nBasidironds may also release hallucinatory spores, but only while standing still. Each creature creates an invisible cloud with a radius of 20-35\". Creatures within the cloud must save vs. poison each round or hallucinate. The effect lasts while they remain in the cloud and for 1-4 rounds thereafter. Examples include believing one is sinking in a swamp, being attacked by spiders, shrinking, holding a snake, suffocating, fearing diseased companions, melting, or being attacked by something clinging to the back.\n\nBecause basidironds have no real minds, spells such as charm monster, hold monster, and similar mental attacks are ineffective. Cold attacks do no damage, but they slow the creature to half normal movement and prevent all spore attacks.",
