      "npc_notes": "BEE, GIANT (BUMBLEBEE)\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"/24\" (MC:E)\nHIT DICE: 6+4\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6 + poison\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Sting\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/400 + 8/hp\n\nGiant bumblebees dwell in nests rather than hives. A nest contains 7-12 giant bumblebees. There will also be a combative queen of 8+6 hit dice doing 1-8 points of damage per sting. Poison from soldiers and bumblebees is stronger than that of workers, and saving throws are made at -1; a queen bumblebee's poison is -2 on the saving throw. A successful save vs. poison still inflicts an additional 2-8 points of damage. Failure causes an additional 5-20 points of damage, +1 for soldiers and bumblebees and +2 for queen bees.\n\nHoney in hives or nests is present in proportionate quantities. Bee bread is excellent food and equal to iron rations. Royal jelly is found only 20% of the time and is equal to 2-5 potions of extra-healing, each also curing disease. It can also be prepared as an unguent that preserves youthful appearance for up to 1 year. Two to five such preparations can be made from royal jelly, and each jar commands 3,000-8,000 gp on the open market.",
