      "npc_notes": "CAT (DOMESTIC)\n\nFREQUENCY: Common\nNO. APPEARING: 1 or 2-12\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 5\"\nHIT DICE: 1-5 hit points\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2/1\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Rear claws for 1-2\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/5 + 1/hp\n\nDomestic and wild cats are closely related and most species can interbreed. Domestic cats are found nearly everywhere in temperate to tropical climes; some have gone wild. The smaller domestic variety has only 1 effective attack with forepaw claws. If the forepaw claw attack succeeds, it gains rear claw rakes for 1-2 points of damage.\n\nBoth sorts of felines surprise prey on 3 in 6. Both are surprised only on a 1 in 6. Both species are agile climbers and can move up and along tree limbs at half their normal movement rate. Domestic cats will not normally attack medium or large creatures.",
