    "npc_notes": "DIREBURR\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-5\nARMOR CLASS: 0 (carapace) / 8 (underside)\nMOVE: ½\" on ground; leap to 20' from tree\nHIT DICE: 2-6\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1 point\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Lignification\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to mind-affecting spells\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (2'-3' across)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: As barkburr\n\nDireburrs are the corrupted form of barkburrs produced by unwholesome woods and evil forests. In all respects they are identical to ordinary barkburrs except in two critical ways.\n\nFirst, a direburr attacks any humanoid coming within 20 feet, regardless of alignment or any past deed against the forest.\n\nSecond, any victim successfully lignified by a direburr always ends as a dry, dead, leafless tree. This final form cannot be reversed by anything short of a full wish.",
