      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "FIRE BAT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 11-20\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 6\"/20\" (MC: B)\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: I\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Attachment attack; automatic burning and blood-drain for 3 rounds\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to fire\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2/hp\n\nFire bats are natives of the Elemental Plane of Fire and only rarely appear on the Prime Material Plane. They are about 2 feet long with nearly 4-foot wingspans, and their entire bodies burn with intense heat. Their bite damage chiefly reflects burning rather than blood loss.\n\nThey live in colonies, usually 12-24 strong, inhabiting volcanoes, hot springs, and similar fiery places. Some sages believe they occasionally accompany summoned fire elementals, though they are never under the summoner's control. They reproduce by fission after feeding on blood, so even a single escaped fire bat may found a colony if prey is available.\n\nWhen attacking, they swoop down and try to fasten themselves to victims. Once attached, they automatically inflict damage for a total of 3 rounds: the hit round plus 2 more. After feeding, they drop off and return to the lair. If a victim dies early, unsated bats shift to another target, but no individual bat ever drains more than 3 rounds' worth in total.\n\nFire bats detect invisible opponents by advanced sonar and infravision and attack such targets without penalty. Unlike normal bats, bright light does not trouble them. They are allies of fire elementals and never attack them.\n\nThey hunt in coordinated packs. The attacking bats distribute themselves as evenly as possible among all available victims. If their active numbers drop below 25% of their starting force, whether by death or by satiated withdrawal, all survivors immediately retreat toward the lair. If cornered there, they fight to the death. Upon death each erupts in flame and its body is returned to the Elemental Plane of Fire, where it is reborn.\n\nTheir lairs are rocky, maze-like, and full of side passages, with one obvious main entrance. Their treasure is usually gems and jewelry, especially rubies, jacinths, and carnelians. If a hunting pack is wiped out, 1 or 2 young may remain in the lair; each has half the hit dice and damage of an adult.\n\nOn land they hop awkwardly, but fly efficiently by means of true flight aided by hot internal gases. Water frightens them. It takes at least 10 gallons of cool water to extinguish one fire bat. Once doused, it must spend 10 rounds drying before reigniting; during that time it cannot fly and inflicts only 1-4 damage per successful attack. They may glide through lava or magma without harm.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
