    "npc_notes": "GIANT, FIRBOLG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4 or 4-16\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 13+2-7\n% IN LAIR: 45%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals M (x10), Q; in lair E, Y\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type +10 (Strength bonus)\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 15%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (chaotic good)\nSIZE: L (10 1/2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/3650 + 18/hp\n\nOf the minor races of giantkind, the firbolg is the most powerful. They are cautious, crafty, and possess considerable magical power. They have learned to distrust, and fear, humans, and will be found only in remote and wild places. Ninety percent of encounters will be with small groups or a lone wanderer. Ten percent of the time the meeting will be with an enclave of several groups gathered for some purpose.\n\nFirbolgs prefer two-handed swords and great halberds as weapons. All firbolg weapons are very large, so they use preferred human-made weapons with just one hand and their own with one or two hands. Their double-sized clubs, axes, spears, and the like inflict double normal weapon damage when used with both hands.\n\nFirbolgs with one hand free are able to bat away missiles such as arrows, bolts, bullets, darts, and stones, or catch such projectiles as javelins, spears, and boulders. They can do this twice per round, succeeding on a 6 or better on 1d20, a 75% chance.\n\nIn addition to magic resistance, each firbolg has innate spell-like powers usable at will, 1 per round, when not engaged in melee. These are: detect magic, diminution as potion, double effect and duration maximum, fool's gold, forget, and alter self. Each is usable once per day.\n\nThere is a 5% chance per firbolg encountered that 1 in the group will be a shaman. In addition to standard shaman spells, firbolg shamans are able to use 2 first-level illusionist spells per level, determined randomly. At 6th and 7th levels, firbolg shamans gain 2 second-level illusionist spells, likewise determined randomly.\n\nThese human-looking giants will not always greet strangers warmly, but they usually will not try to kill them unless provoked. They do enjoy appearing as little people and duping humans out of treasure.",
