      "npc_notes": "GIANT, FOMORIAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 13+1-3\n% IN LAIR: 45%\nTREASURE TYPE: D, Q (x10)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 4-32\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: L (13 1/2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2750 + 18/hp\n\nFomorians are the most hideous, deformed, and wicked of all giantkind. They tend to be solitary, dwelling in forlorn places such as mountain caves or abandoned mines. Their thick hairy hides, combined with the pelts and odd metal bits they wear for protection, give them their effective armor class.\n\nAlthough these deformed monsters move but slowly for their size, they can do so with considerable stealth and have +1 to +3 on surprise depending upon terrain. If encountered in the lair, there is a 25% chance there will be 1-2 females for every male, and 1-3 young per female. Female fomorians are equal to males but get no bonus hit points. Young are as follows: small, age 1, 7d4 and damage 2-8; half-grown, ages 2-3, 13d4 and damage 4-16; near-adult, ages 4-6, 13d6 and damage 4-24.\n\nAlthough their deformities prevent them from hurling rocks, those same handicaps aid them so that fomorian giants can never be surprised under normal circumstances. Oddly placed eyes, huge ears, and oversized noses enable them to detect any normal approach.\n\nWeapons range from huge clubs to chains with heavy metal balls attached. The strongest may have crude shields and better armor, so armor class 2 or even 1 is possible.\n\nA fomorian will have terrible deformities, such as one misplaced arm, huge feet on short legs, eyes on the side like a fish's or one in the back of the head, a hump, a pointed long head, flapping ears, a tiny or gaping mouth, a huge nose or snout, and so on. They have scattered patches of hair as tough as wire.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
