      "npc_notes": "GORGIMERA\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 5/2\nMOVE: 12\"/15\" (MC:E)\nHIT DICE: 10\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: F\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 5\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-3/1-3/2-8/2-12/3-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapons (2)\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (5' tall at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2557 + 14/hp\n\nAlthough similar in appearance to a chimera, a gorgimera is a more fearsome monster. This sterile hybrid has the hindquarters and head of a gorgon, the forequarters and head of a lion, and the mid-body, wings, and head of a red dragon. Only the lion parts have armor class 5. The gorgimera can attack with its claws, bite with its lion head, butt with its gorgon head, and bite with its dragon head.\n\nAdditionally, the gorgon head can breathe petrifying breath twice per day, a 3\" long by 1\" wide base cone, while the dragon head can breathe fiery breath twice per day, a 5\" long by 2\" wide base cone. The monster will always use one breath weapon against opponents 10 feet or more distant, as it understands breath ranges and effects. If in melee, there is a 1 in 6 chance it will use fire and a like chance it will use petrification. Dragon breath does 3-24 points of damage; save vs. breath weapon for half. Gorgon breath turns victims to stone unless a save vs. petrification succeeds.\n\nGorgimerae speak a very limited form of red dragon language. The gorgon head can see into the Astral and Ethereal Planes, and its breath weapon extends therein. A gorgimera looks almost exactly like a chimera, except its gorgon parts are metallic blue. Gorgon eyes are pale blue rimmed in red.",
