      "npc_notes": "GREENHAG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -2\nMOVE: 12\"//12\"\nHIT DICE: 9\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: M (x100), N (x10), Q (x5), X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 7-8/7-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 35%\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1600 + 12/hp\n\nGreenhags are a race of evil creatures related to both annis and night hags. Like annis, they dwell on the Prime Material Plane. While many live in forests and lonely moors, some inhabit swamps and rivers. These latter are often called shellycoats. The lair is always a small cave, possibly one dug in earth. Greenhags attack by clawing with rock-hard talons. They have Strength 18/00 and thus add +6 to the damage inflicted by each attack.\n\nIn order to lure victims, greenhags typically use their mimic ability. This allows imitation of the voice of a mature or immature male or female, human or demihuman. Calls for help, crying, and similar sounds are common deceptions. They can also mimic common animal sounds such as those of barnyard fowl, cats, dogs, goats, sheep, and cattle.\n\nGreenhags have the following spell-like powers, usable 1 at a time, at will, 1 per round: audible glamer, dancing lights, invisibility, pass without trace, change self, speak with monsters, water breathing, and weakness. Each is used at 9th level of ability.\n\nBecause of their coloration and the fact that they are 90% likely to move silently and hide in foliage, even underwater vegetation, greenhags surprise on 5 in 6, or 19 in 20 if attacking from invisibility. Because of their highly acute senses, including infra- and ultravision, they are surprised only on a 1 in 20. They speak their own language, a dialect of Annis, as well as Ogre, common Giant, and Common.\n\nA typical greenhag appears to be a nighthag with green skin. Hair ranges from near black to olive green. Eye color ranges from amber to orange. They often dress as peasants.",
