      "npc_notes": "GRIG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-12 (or 5-50)\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 6\" (or 12\" leap)\nHIT DICE: 1/2+1 (2-5 hit points)\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: X, Y\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3 or 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Spells\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 30%\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (good)\nSIZE: S (1 1/2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/50 + 1/hp\n\nThe leaping grigs appear to be some form of sprite. Found only in sylvan woodlands and meadows, they are shy of strangers but otherwise good-natured and friendly. They are nocturnal and in most instances are encountered in a glen. There, with 1 or several other bands of grigs or a tribe of atomies or both, they will meet to play and dance in the moonlight. There is a 30% probability for other grigs or atomies to be present: 1-15 = 5-50 grigs, 16-25 = 2-12 grigs and 30-120 atomies, 26-30 = 5-50 grigs and 30-120 atomies. One or more grigs will play bowed string instruments while the others enjoy circle dances and other pastimes.\n\nThe grigs' high armor class is due to size, Dexterity, and leaping ability. Their legs are more like a cricket's or grasshopper's than a sprite's, and these limbs give them the ability to leap long distances assisted by their small gauze-like wings. Attack is made only against evil enemies or those who molest them. It is typically a combination of missile release and melee. Due to their skill and Dexterity, grigs attack at +2 to hit when hurling missiles. Each carries at least 6 small darts. These are hurled during hopping flight. Then the grigs alight and thrust with needle-like daggers. Their small darts are equal to large darts when used by grigs, but in other hands do only 1 point of damage. Similarly, the grig dagger is merely a knife unless wielded by a grig, in which case it inflicts short sword damage.\n\nGrigs have the following spell-like powers usable at will, 1 at a time, 1 per round: change self, entangle, invisibility, pyrotechnics, trip, and ventriloquism. These are used at 6th level of ability. Grigs enjoy using these dweomers for jolly fun as well as self-protection, and many practical jokes are reported from encounters with them.\n\nGrig fiddlers are 25% likely to be able to play a tune whose effect equals Otto's irresistible dance. A saving throw vs. spell applies to all within a 30-foot radius of the playing grig. Failure means the victim must dance until the grig ceases playing or the victim drops from exhaustion. Grigs can play for hours.\n\nGrigs are 90% likely to surprise and only 10% likely to be surprised. Their hearing is double human norm, they have infravision to 180 feet, and ultravision. In addition to their own tongue, grigs speak Atomie, Brownie, Pixie, and Sprite. They also speak Common if they choose to slow their speech and lower the pitch.",
