      "npc_notes": "GRIM\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 18\" or /36\" (MC:C in owl form)\nHIT DICE: 4+2-8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: See below\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 25%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral good\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/285 + 5/hp\n\nThe grim are guardians who watch for and oppose evil. They are night creatures, usually frequenting the fringes of human habitations or burial grounds. Grim will be encountered in any of the following forms: black cat, as a giant lynx for attacks 1-2/1-2/1-4 plus raking; black dog, as a war dog for attacks 2-8; and black owl, as a giant owl for attacks 2-8/2-8/2-5.\n\nEach grim must stay in the chosen form for a full night. In daylight they become ethereal and await sunset. Damage sustained the previous day is alleviated as the sun sets. In addition to the attack modes of the chosen form, grim are able to turn undead as if clerics of 8th level, with +2 on the die if versus creatures of evil from the Lower Outer Planes. They can be hit only by +1 or better magical weapons. Each grim radiates protection from evil within a 10-foot radius and can detect evil at 7\". Thus, they are never surprised by evil creatures, and their senses allow them to surprise others on a 1 in 10.\n\nGrim typically ward off evil-natured creatures and warn the good of imminent peril from such monsters. This is done by their weird call, whether yowl, howl, or hoot, of mournful tone. They do not otherwise communicate or do anything else with humans or demihumans unless an immediate confrontation is at hand. In that case, they will always assist in combat against evil.",
