      "npc_notes": "HEXTON (HIERARCH MODRON)\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (of 36)\nARMOR CLASS: -2\nMOVE: 12\"/12\" (MC:C)//12\"\nHIT DICE: 14+14\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 6\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-13 (x6)\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +3 or better weapons to hit\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 50%\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IX/8250 + 18/hp\n\nThere are 36 hextons, each a general commanding one of the armies of Nirvana. These armies are maintained to preserve order and prevent invasion from Acheron, Arcadia, and the Plane of Concordant Opposition. One hexton and army are assigned to each region, 2 serve directly under each viceroyal quarter, 3 serve the tertians as special police, and the remaining 9 serve Primus.\n\nHextons appear as humanoids with 6 arms: 2 large human arms with 6 fingers each, and 4 tentacles below tipped with sharp claws. They have thin fan-like folded wings joined at the shoulders.\n\nHextons use spells as 18th-level clerics but have no additional special spell-like abilities beyond those common to all hierarch modrons. They are immune to all psionic attacks.\n\nThere is a 75% chance that any hexton is accompanied by its guard, a staff of 12-48 special pentadrones who are fanatically dedicated to preserving its life.",
