      "npc_notes": "HOLLYPHANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: -4\nMOVE: 9\"/42\" (MC:B)\nHIT DICE: 8+8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-3/1-3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 60%\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: Good (lawful)\nSIZE: S (2'+ long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 201-300\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/3750 + 14/hp\n\nHollyphants are creatures of the Upper Outer Planes. They are used as messengers and helpers by the deities, and as such are sometimes encountered on the Prime Material Plane. When so seen, there will be from 1 to 3 hollyphants flying, for it is only 5% probable that a hollyphant will be going by foot. The sight of these strange golden-furred creatures engenders great fondness and desire to cooperate in good characters, unease in those of neutral standing, and loathing tinged with fear in evil characters. This reaction is caused by a sort of telepathic aura surrounding hollyphants. No saving throw is permitted. Hollyphants desire to aid good, dislike neutral, and will seek to destroy evil. Normal attack is by means of their upward-jutting tusks, but hollyphants have far more effective attack and defense modes.\n\nThree times per day each hollyphant can trumpet through its trunk. Each blast can produce one of the following results as desired: blasting as per horn of blasting; deafening as per drums of deafening, but in a cone 1\" x 3\" x 7\"; and sun-sparkles, a cone-shaped blast of positive energy particles 1\" x 2\" x 5\" that inflicts 8d6+8 points of damage on undead and creatures of the Lower Outer Planes. Hollyphants are also able to use the following spell-like powers, one at a time, one per round, at will, at 16th level of ability: banishment once per day; bless; cure serious wounds twice per day; flame strike once per day; heal once per day; light; protection from evil within a 10-foot radius twice per day; raise dead once per day; and teleport with no error. A banishment spell forces creatures from another plane to return instantly to their own abode. More than one creature can be forced away if within 2\" and the total hit dice affected are 32 or less. If the target saves, the hollyphant suffers 2-12 points of backlash damage and is stunned for 2-12 segments.\n\nLive hollyphants are always protected by a globe of invulnerability radiated by their fur. Their tusks give them immunity to all diseases and poisons, though the tusks do not grant this to others. They are harmed only by +1 or better magic weapons. They automatically detect evil in a 2\" radius. Hollyphants can gate, 50% success, another hollyphant, 70%, or an appropriate deva, 30%. Psionic disciplines are usually 4 minor and 2 major, never duplicating their spell-like or other powers. Communication is by their own speech or by a limited form of telepathy. Hollyphants are travelers of the Astral and Ethereal planes in the course of their duties. Their golden fur seems to glow. Their wings are also golden and their small tusks are ivory-colored. Hollyphant eyes are amber to glowing brown, large, and kindly.",
