      "npc_notes": "MOBAT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-8\nARMOR CLASS: 7 (2 in clear flight; 10 on ground)\nMOVE: 3\"/15\" (MC: C)\nHIT DICE: 4-6\n% IN LAIR: 15%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Painful screech\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Sonar, silent flight, variable AC by position\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (evil)\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/150 + 5/hp\n\nMobats are huge omnivorous bats found chiefly in warm climates where large caverns provide shelter and prey is plentiful. They prefer warm-blooded prey and kill with their fangs.\n\nWith wingspans of 12-16 feet they require broad areas for takeoff, but once airborne their sonar allows them to navigate narrow passages in total darkness. Their flight is swift and comparatively silent, allowing them to surprise prey 50% of the time.\n\nIf prey resists, a mobat emits a piercing screech with a 20-foot radius. Any victim hearing it must save vs. paralysis or spend the round covering its ears rather than fighting. In open flight the mobat's agility and sonar give it AC 2. In crowded aerial conditions its AC is 7. On the ground it is AC 10.\n\nMobats possess a dim, malign intelligence and are attracted to shiny objects.",
