      "npc_notes": "MOLD, RUSSET\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 patch\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 0\"\nHIT DICE: 12-16 hp/10 square feet\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 0\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 0\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spores\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S to L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: Not ratable\n\nFound only in damp underground areas, this mold is often mistaken for rust at distances greater than 30 feet, 70% chance. It is immune to all attacks involving weapons, fire, and cold, but is vulnerable to applications of alcohol, acid, and compounds harmful to plants, such as salt. It can be killed instantly by casting cure disease or continual light upon it.\n\nRusset mold makes no physical attacks but emits a barely visible cloud of spores within a 3-foot radius; beyond this radius the spores settle inertly to the floor. If the mold is touched, it injects these spores. All creatures passing within 3 feet or touching it take 5-20 points of damage from the toxicity and must save vs. poison. Failure results in a sickness that kills in 2-5 turns unless cure disease is cast.\n\nAny character who dies from touching russet mold undergoes a transformation. The body first begins to sprout new mold growths from the spores left at contact. Then, when entirely encased in mold, a vegepygmy will rise from the remains. The entire process takes 21-24 hours, 1d4+20. A hold plant spell will halt the mold's growth for the duration of the spell. If the mold grows for more than 1 hour, the victim cannot be recovered except by a wish spell. Russet mold is golden-brown to rust-red in color. Its lumpy texture resembles cold porridge, and it is covered by short hair-like growths that stand upright and constantly waver as if in a gentle breeze",
