      "npc_notes": "MONODRONE (BASE MODRON)\n\nFREQUENCY: Common\nNO. APPEARING: 12-144\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 6\"//6\" or 6\"/18\" (MC:D)\nHIT DICE: 1+1 or 1-1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 or Nil\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to illusion and mind control\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: S (3'-6\")\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2/hp\n\nMonodrones make up the bulk of the population of Nirvana. They are single-function modrons and are generally assigned simple labor or serve together to form the regiments of the Nirvanan Army. Thousands of spherical monodrones armed with spears, fauchards, and crossbows are impressive when marshaled against a foe, as is their unswerving, single-minded performance. They exist for their work, and what limited conversations they can carry on usually concern their functions.\n\nMonodrones are usually assembled in units of 12 and supervised by a duodrone or tridrone. One-twelfth of all monodrones lack the spider-like arms and instead possess fan-like wings joined to the body at a single point. These faster, smaller creatures are used as messengers. They can relay perfectly any message of up to 48 words. Unlike their armed relatives, messenger monodrones cannot exist in liquid environments.\n\nMonodrone senses are slightly less than those of a normal human, though they possess a limited form of infravision with a 30-foot range.",
