  "monster_manual_ii_mud_man": {
    "name": "MUD-MAN",
    "source": "Monster Manual II",
    "sheet": {
      "frequency": "Very rare",
      "no_appearing": "2-12",
      "armorclass": "10",
      "movement": "3\"",
      "monsterHD": "2",
      "percent_in_lair": "100%",
      "treasure_type": "Nil",
      "no_of_attacks": "1",
      "damage_attack": "Nil",
      "special_attacks": "Mud-throwing",
      "special_defenses": "Need magical weapons to hit; immune to certain spells",
      "magic_resistance": "Standard",
      "intelligence": "Non-",
      "alignment": "Neutral",
      "size": "S (c.4')",
      "psionic_ability": "Nil",
      "attack_defense_modes": "Nil/nil",
      "level_xp_value": "II/28 + 2/hp",
      "monsterhd": "2",
      "monsterhd_bonus": "",
      "morale_base": "",
      "morale": "",
      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "MUD-MAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-12\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 3\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Mud-throwing\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Need magical weapons to hit; immune to certain spells\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (c.4')\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2/hp\n\nMud-men are formed in pools of mud where enchanted waters, even mildly enchanted ones such as a stream eroding a magical structure, collect and evaporate, concentrating the dweomer. Physically they are animated mud, taking on a stocky humanoid form when roused. Slow moving and unable to leave their pool of mud, mud-men have but one aim in life: to kill any creature entering the pool who is more mobile than themselves. Virtually all creatures, and certainly all humans and demihumans, fall into this category.\n\nIn their dormant state, mud-men lie below the surface of their pool with the substance of their bodies spread throughout, feeding on the dweomer in the mud. In this state they are immune to attacks with weapons, magical or otherwise, though they are susceptible to spell attacks. When a creature enters the mud pool, the mud-men sense its presence immediately and take 1 round to draw themselves together and rise, ready to attack in the next round. Once fully formed and standing, they may be harmed by magical weapons.\n\nMud-men attack by hurling mud at opponents, who are treated as armor class 10, modified by Dexterity, for purposes of being hit. The mud hardens on impact and slows movement. At first the mud-men hurl blobs of mud, maximum range 6\". Each hit slows the victim's movement by 1\". However, while hurling blobs, mud-men move toward opponents at full rate. Once within 1\", they will hurl themselves rather than a mere blob. A successful hit means the death of the mud-man but also slows the victim's movement by 4\". A miss means that the mud-man must spend the next round reforming in order to attack again.\n\nA victim is unable to move and begins to suffocate once movement rate reaches zero, taking 1-8 points of damage per round until the mouth and/or nose is clear. The victim dies from suffocation after 5 rounds unless rescued. The hardened mud can be broken away from wholly or partly immobilized creatures, restoring movement at a rate of 1\" per 5 rounds. Mud-men cannot sense creatures outside their pool and will not attack them. Once no living opponents remain within the pool, roused mud-men sink back below the surface until the pool is re-entered.\n\nMud-men are affected by all spells which cause damage directly to living creatures, such as cause light wounds, magic missile, fireball, and flame strike. Dispel magic and dig act as fireballs cast by a magic-user of the caster's level. Transmute mud to rock kills all mud-men it can affect, with no saving throw. Mud-men are immune to poison, whether magical or normal, and are unaffected by mind-affecting spells or psionics. So long as mud-men are not fully formed from their pool, damage from spells without area effect is divided evenly among them, fractions rounded down, since the substance of their bodies is spread through the mud.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
    "npc_notes": "MUD-MAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-12\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 3\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Mud-throwing\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Need magical weapons to hit; immune to certain spells\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (c.4')\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2/hp\n\nMud-men are formed in pools of mud where enchanted waters, even mildly enchanted ones such as a stream eroding a magical structure, collect and evaporate, concentrating the dweomer. Physically they are animated mud, taking on a stocky humanoid form when roused. Slow moving and unable to leave their pool of mud, mud-men have but one aim in life: to kill any creature entering the pool who is more mobile than themselves. Virtually all creatures, and certainly all humans and demihumans, fall into this category.\n\nIn their dormant state, mud-men lie below the surface of their pool with the substance of their bodies spread throughout, feeding on the dweomer in the mud. In this state they are immune to attacks with weapons, magical or otherwise, though they are susceptible to spell attacks. When a creature enters the mud pool, the mud-men sense its presence immediately and take 1 round to draw themselves together and rise, ready to attack in the next round. Once fully formed and standing, they may be harmed by magical weapons.\n\nMud-men attack by hurling mud at opponents, who are treated as armor class 10, modified by Dexterity, for purposes of being hit. The mud hardens on impact and slows movement. At first the mud-men hurl blobs of mud, maximum range 6\". Each hit slows the victim's movement by 1\". However, while hurling blobs, mud-men move toward opponents at full rate. Once within 1\", they will hurl themselves rather than a mere blob. A successful hit means the death of the mud-man but also slows the victim's movement by 4\". A miss means that the mud-man must spend the next round reforming in order to attack again.\n\nA victim is unable to move and begins to suffocate once movement rate reaches zero, taking 1-8 points of damage per round until the mouth and/or nose is clear. The victim dies from suffocation after 5 rounds unless rescued. The hardened mud can be broken away from wholly or partly immobilized creatures, restoring movement at a rate of 1\" per 5 rounds. Mud-men cannot sense creatures outside their pool and will not attack them. Once no living opponents remain within the pool, roused mud-men sink back below the surface until the pool is re-entered.\n\nMud-men are affected by all spells which cause damage directly to living creatures, such as cause light wounds, magic missile, fireball, and flame strike. Dispel magic and dig act as fireballs cast by a magic-user of the caster's level. Transmute mud to rock kills all mud-men it can affect, with no saving throw. Mud-men are immune to poison, whether magical or normal, and are unaffected by mind-affecting spells or psionics. So long as mud-men are not fully formed from their pool, damage from spells without area effect is divided evenly among them, fractions rounded down, since the substance of their bodies is spread through the mud.",
    "id": "monster_manual_ii_mud_man"
  },
