      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "MYCONID (FUNGUS MAN)\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-12 (20-200)\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1-6\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: S (x2)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 to 6-24 (d4 x HD)\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spore clouds\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Poisonous skin\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: S to L (2' per hit die)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: 1 HD = I/14 + 1/hp; 2 HD = II/28 + 2/hp; 3 HD = II/50 + 3/hp; 4 HD = III/150 + 4/hp; 5 HD = IV/205 + 5/hp; 6 HD = V/425 + 6/hp\n\nThe myconids, or fungus men, resemble walking toadstools in humanoid form. Their flesh is bloated and spongy and varies in color from purple to gray. Their skin, except on their hands, oozes a substance poisonous to animal flesh. Personal contact with a myconid in most places results in 1-4 points of damage to the creature doing the touching. Each of their pudgy hands has 2 stubby fingers and a thumb on either side. Myconids live deep underground under conditions suitable to fungi. They never venture onto the surface and have a deathly fear of direct sunlight.\n\nMyconid society is based on circles, extremely tight social groups linked by work and melding sessions. Each circle's day is rigidly structured: 8 hours of rest, 8 hours of farming fungus crops or other necessary work, and 8 hours of melding. For myconids, melding is entertainment, worship, and social interaction combined. The fungoids gather in a tight circle, and the elder members release rapport and hallucinator spores. The entire group then merges into a collective telepathic hallucination for 8 hours. Myconids consider melding the reason for existence. Only distress spores will bring a circle out of meld early.\n\nA myconid circle usually consists of 20 members, 4 of each hit-dice size from 1-5. As myconids age, they continue to grow in height and weight, gaining 2 feet of height per hit die. A 1-hit-die myconid is 2 feet tall, but the 6-hit-dice king stands 12 feet tall. The damage they do in melee also increases with size. Fungus men fight by clubbing with clasped hands, doing 1d4 points of damage per hit die of size. Thus 1-hit-die myconids do 1-4 points and the 6-hit-dice king inflicts 6-24 points.\n\nMyconids can spew specialized clouds of spores. The number and kind increase as they grow. Each myconid can emit each of its spore types a number of times per day equal to its hit dice. Distress spores alert other myconids to danger and expand to a maximum of 120 feet; this ability is gained at 1 hit die. Reproducer spores are emitted only at the proper time for growing new myconids and are automatically ejected by a dying myconid; this ability is gained at 2 hit dice. Rapport spores are used in melding but can also allow mind-to-mind communication with other species if the recipient fails a save vs. poison or deliberately chooses to fail; duration equals the hit dice of the myconid originator in turns; this ability is gained at 3 hit dice. Pacifier spores affect a single creature, which if it fails a save vs. poison becomes totally passive for a number of rounds equal to the hit dice of the myconid; this ability is gained at 4 hit dice. Hallucinator spores affect a single creature which, if it fails a save vs. poison, suffers violent hallucinations for a number of turns equal to the hit dice of the myconid; this ability is gained at 5 hit dice. Animator spores are gained only at 6 hit dice, achieved only by the king, and are used to infect a dead person or animal, eventually animating the corpse in zombie-like fashion, though it is not undead and cannot be turned.\n\nThe myconid king is always the largest member of the colony and the only member at 6 hit dice. It is also the only myconid not part of a circle. The others regard separation from one's circle with horror and pity the lonely king. Leadership is seen as an unpleasant duty. When the old king dies, the strongest 5-hit-dice myconid becomes the new king. The king must remain outside circle affairs to retain objectivity and attend to leadership duties. It animates guardians for the colony so that the myconids need not commit violence, coordinates work schedules, watches outside affairs, and practices fungal alchemy, brewing special potions for times of trouble.\n\nIn general the myconids are a peaceful race, desiring only to work and meld in peace. In combat they avoid killing if they can, as violence adversely affects their melding hallucinations. However, accord has never been reached between fungoid and humanoid. Each views the other as a disgusting threat, and population pressure in the underworld inevitably causes conflict.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": "-6"
    },
