      "npc_notes": "NUPPERIBO (LEAST DEVIL)\n\nFREQUENCY: Common\nNO. APPEARING: 10-100\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 or 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2/1-2 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Regenerate 1 point/round\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Special (unratable for spell effects)\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/18 + 1/hp\n\nNupperibos exist by the hundreds of thousands throughout the Hells. They are the remains of all lawful evil creatures not sufficiently malignant to be changed into lemures. They are blind, deaf, and unable to speak. They are sensitive to mental commands from stronger devils, and they also sense the presence of their own kind. They readily obey all commands in order to lessen the pain and torment which is the normal lot in the Infernal Region.\n\nThe normal attack mode of a nupperibo is 2 clawing rakes with its hands. However, when an infernal army is gathered, each member is given some sort of weapon, usually a club, spear, or polearm. The creatures then march and attack blindly but effectively because of the vast numbers gathered into legions and directed by more powerful devils. If uncommanded, hordes of nupperibos will continue to march and attack all things not of the Nine Hells.\n\nIn the Infernal Region or areas of total evil, nupperibos regenerate at 1 hit point per round, but elsewhere this power is lost. If a holy object, water or weapon, is used against them, regeneration is not possible.\n\nNupperibos slain in the cause of evil are 99% likely to be re-formed as nupperibos. There is, however, a 1% chance they will be re-formed as a special sort of lemure, one from which lesser devils are formed. One spending a mere millennium as one of these lemures might attain devilhood.\n\nBecause of the limited sensory capabilities of nupperibos, no intelligence per se can be assigned them. The possible range, were their status changed, would vary from semi- to exceptionally intelligent.",
