      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "OGRE, AQUATIC (MERROW)\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 2-24\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 6\"//12\"\nHIT DICE: 4+4\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: A\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3 or 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6/2-8 or by weapon\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Camouflage\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (9' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/130 + 5/hp (IV/250 + 6/hp)\n\nThis aquatic ogre is generally faster, tougher, and fiercer than its land-based kin. Aquatic ogres typically attack with a piercing spear in a swimming charge at +1 to hit, causing 2-12 points of damage, followed by melee with talons and teeth. Aquatic ogres use their green coloration to hide, becoming effectively invisible 10-80% of the time depending on terrain, and attack from cover, surprising on 4 in 6.\n\nAquatic ogres dwell in relatively shallow waters of 50-250 feet depth. They lair in caves, often in association with scrags. They can survive out of water for up to 2 hours, so they sometimes raid the land. Of 7-12 ogres, 1 will have 31-36 hit points; of 13-18, 2 will have 31-36 hit points; and of 19-24, 3 will have 31-36 hit points.\n\nIn the lair of a group of merrow there will be 1 chief, AC 3, 6+6 hit dice, +2 damage; 2 sub-chiefs, AC 3, 5+5 hit dice, +1 damage; 2-24 females, AC 5, 3+3 hit dice, damage 1-2/1-2/1-6; 1-12 young, AC 6, 2+2 hit dice, damage 1-2/1-2/1-4; and 1 shaman, male or female. Aquatic ogres are able to speak Ogre as well as their own dialect. They are greenish and scaled with sloping shoulders, very thick long necks, huge mouths, undershot jaws, and webbed hands and feet.",
