      "npc_notes": "OPHIDIAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 3-12\nARMOR CLASS: 5 or better\nMOVE: 9\"//18\"\nHIT DICE: 3-4\n% IN LAIR: See below\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 and 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type and 1-3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to very\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/125 + 4/hp\n\nOphidians, or snakemen, are typically encountered in tropical jungles. Unlike nagas, ophidians have human-like arms and hands and can employ weapons, shields, and magic items usable by fighters. They attack first by weapon and then with a fanged bite. The latter requires a saving throw vs. poison or the victim will suffer a lycanthrope-like affliction. This affliction begins in 2-5 days, lasts 8-16 days, and ends by turning the creature into an ophidian if it was human or humanoid, or by killing it otherwise. The process can be prevented by a cure disease spell.\n\nIt is unusual for ophidians to appear in self-determined groups. They are usually servants of spirit nagas or similar creatures. Ophidians appear to be short-tailed, thick-bodied snakes, with arms protruding about 2 feet below the neck. These arms are human-like and end in 4-fingered hands. Their color ranges from gray-black to black, dark brownish green, or pale blue-green.",
