      "npc_notes": "ORDINARY BAT\n\nFREQUENCY: Common\nNO. APPEARING: 1-100 (100-1000)\nARMOR CLASS: 8 (4 in free flight)\nMOVE: 1\"/24\" (MC: B)\nHIT DICE: 1-2 hit points\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Swarming confusion if startled\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Sonar\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/1\n\nThe ordinary bat entry includes many bat species. They attack only if cornered. If startled, they become confused and frightened, swarming about and colliding with creatures and objects. Such swarms may extinguish torches, disrupt spell casting, and generally cause confusion.\n\nBat sonar permits flight in total darkness. Under favorable flying conditions, their armor class improves from 8 to 4. In great caverns, their numbers may reach 1,000 or more.",
