      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "OWL\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1 or 2\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 1\"/27\" (MC:D)\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 10% (daylight only)\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2/1-2/1\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (4'-5\" wingspread)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/30 + 1/hp\n\nVarious types of owls are found in every climate. While some are smaller than those covered by this data, most encounters will be with large specimens. Attack is by talon and beak. When plummeting from a height of 50 feet or greater, attack is at +2 to hit and damage inflicted is twice normal, but no beak attack is possible. Owls have double normal ultravision, quadruple normal hearing, and fly in total silence. They are likely to surprise prey on 5 in 6 and are never surprised during dusk or darkness. In twilight to daylight brightness, owls see at slightly less than human standard. Thus, despite their hearing, they are surprised on 3 in 6 if discovered in their hidden daylight roosting place.\n\nWhile they cannot be trained to hunt, they can be somewhat domesticated if taken young enough and accustomed to human presence. Because daylight birds, such as crows and ravens, flock to attack an owl discovered in daylight, owls are sometimes used as decoys by hunters. The anger and determination of the attacking birds causes them to lose caution in their desire to kill the decoy owl.\n\nPARA-ELEMENTAL\n\nThe para-elementals are the inhabitants of the para-elemental planes of Ice, Ooze, Magma, and Smoke, which lie between the major planes of Earth, Air, Fire, and Water. Para-elementals are summoned much as normal elementals are, except that there is a chance of not getting the summoned elemental but one from either adjoining major elemental plane. This chance is 100% minus 5% per level of the summoner.\n\nConjured para-elementals fall into 3 hit-dice strength categories like their major-plane brethren: 16 HD by spell, 12 HD by summoning device, and 8 HD by staff. Para-elementals are impervious to attacks from weapons of less than +1 enchantment or by creatures without magical ability of 4 hit dice or less. As with ordinary elementals, control must be maintained at all times or the para-elemental will turn on its summoner. Material components are: a lens of clear crystal or glass for Ice; a damp cloth for Ooze; volcanic glass for Magma; and dry ash for Smoke.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
