      "npc_notes": "PARA-ELEMENTAL, MAGMA\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 8, 12, or 16\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 4-24\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +1 or better weapons to hit\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2850 + 15/hp\n\nMagma para-elementals, often called heat para-elementals, are natives of the Para-elemental Plane of Magma, a rocky volcanic place located at the edges of the Elemental Planes of Fire and Earth. Para-elementals summoned from this plane are humanoid from the waist up, while their legs and lower torsos are molten rock. The eyes and mouths of these creatures glow with a reddish light from the fires within.\n\nThe heat from a magma elemental is similar to the druidic heat metal spell, affecting all within 20 feet. During the first round of exposure, metal grows hot. During the second, metallic armor and weapons do 1-4 points of damage to their wielders. On the third and succeeding rounds, metal-using characters take 2-8 points of damage and nonmetal-using characters take 1-4. Leaving the area causes the damage to drop one level immediately and disappear completely the following round. Wood and other flammable objects brought into contact with either the para-elemental or metal heated by it burst into flame.\n\nThe Para-elemental Plane of Magma is a lonely volcanic plain spotted with volcanoes, and its denizens work in packs with no fixed leader, though there may be exceptional para-elementals with magical power.",
