      "npc_notes": "PARA-ELEMENTAL, OOZE\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 36\" (MC:A)\nHIT DICE: 8, 12, or 16\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 constrict\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-16\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +1 or better weapons to hit\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2850 + 15/hp\n\nThe ooze para-elemental, also called the mud elemental, appears as a liquid mass of dark writhing tendrils. If it hits, it has wrapped a tendril around its opponent and will constrict for 2-16 points of damage per round until dispelled, defeated, or commanded to release its victim. Any number of opponents may be constricted, but only one may be attacked and ensnared at a time. A captured character may still attack, but can be swept off his feet and carried away. The ooze para-elemental's form is mutable, and it can fit into tight crevices and beneath doorways with ease.\n\nThe Elemental Plane of Ooze is a cloudy gray plane at the borders of Water and Earth. Both water and earth creatures may be found there. Ooze para-elementals have no fixed ruler, but there are a number of contending slime-barons vying for control.",
