      "morale": "",
      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "PECH\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 5-20 (double in lair)\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 5%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon +3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 25%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (good)\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/240 + 4/hp\n\nNo one knows what the pech actually are, or whether they are from the Prime Material or Elemental Planes. In any event, these spindly creatures dwell in dark places and work stone. Their flesh is nearly as hard as granite. In their lair there will be several larger pech, females equal in number to males, and young amounting to 20-50% of the females. There will also be 50-100 gems plus various dishes and ornaments worked from ornamental stone and raw metal, 5-30 pieces of jewelry of the lowest base value, averaging 150 gp each. The pech use picks and peat hammers, treated as war hammers, for both work and combat, and are usually equipped with equal numbers of each.\n\nEach pech is able to cast 4 stone shape and stone tell spells per day. Four together can cast a wall of stone spell as if they were 16th-level magic-users. Eight together can cast a stone to flesh spell. These group spells can be cast only once per day by any group. Pech are immune to petrification. If engaged against a lithic monster such as a stone golem, pech are quite capable of knocking it to rubble, as their knowledge of stone allows them full normal attack capability. Pech are basically good creatures who desire to be left to themselves. They hate bright light and open skies. They possess both infra- and ultravision.\n\nPech are thin, with long arms and legs. Their broad hands and feet are excellent for bracing and using tools to work stone. They have pale yellowish skin and red or red-brown hair. Their eyes are large and pupilless.",
