      "npc_notes": "SEPTON (HIERARCH MODRON)\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (of 49)\nARMOR CLASS: -1\nMOVE: 9\"//9\"\nHIT DICE: 13+13\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 7\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-10 (x7)\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +2 or better weapons to hit\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 40%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IX/8250 + 18/hp\n\nSeptons are the officials who maintain order and ensure that all regulations are obeyed. One serves each quinton, 4 serve each secundus, and 8 serve Primus directly. They travel from place to place as inspectors and examiners of work and records and are charged with transferring information from outlying areas to the towers of the regions, quarters, and the central tower itself.\n\nSeptons appear as humanoids with large bald heads. They have shoulder collars similar to those of octons, though smaller, and while insufficient for air travel, they make for excellent underwater transport.\n\nTo perform their duties, each septon has 7 senses operating continuously: hearing, sight, smell, taste, touch, ESP at 30 feet, and detect magic. They are also mighty spellcasters, having clerical spells at 16th level and magic-user spells at 12th level.\n\nLike all high hierarchs without psionic ability, septons are completely immune to psionic attacks and combat.",
