      "npc_notes": "SKELETON, ANIMAL\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-20\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 1-1\n% IN LAIR: 85%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S to M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/10 + 1/hp\n\nAnimal skeletons are animated from small vertebrate creatures by means of an animate dead spell. They are produced at the rate of 1-1/2 per experience level of the caster. They are typically created to serve as minor guardians. Thus, they do not usually have treasure nearby, save possibly what remains incidentally from earlier encounters. Usual animal skeletons range from the size of domestic cats to the size of large dogs. Nothing larger than a human can be animated by the spell.\n\nAnimal skeletons have no special attack forms. They are, of course, immune to charm, cold, death magic, hold, and sleep. Blunt weapons inflict normal damage, but edged weapons inflict only half normal damage. They are turned as normal skeletons, but at +1 in the cleric's favor, and 1d6+6 will be turned or destroyed.",
