      "npc_notes": "SOLIFUGID, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 6+6\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: N (x4), Q\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 or 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 4-16\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Grip\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/350 + 8/hp\n\nVariously known as false spiders, camel spiders, or sun spiders, solifugids are arachnids. They have powerful hooked beaks and 10 legs, the first pair ending in sucker-like clamps. When in combat, a solifugid attempts to attack with each of its 2 front legs. If either scores a hit, no damage is done but the character struck is caught in the grip of the solifugid. On each melee round thereafter, the beak attack gains +3 on its to-hit roll; only the beak does actual damage, the amount indicated above. This bonus continues as long as a character is held. The only way to break the grip is to sever a limb by rolling 3 or more above the normal number needed to hit.\n\nWhenever solifugids are encountered outdoors, there is a 60% chance that they are of the nocturnal variety, normally venturing out only at night. These creatures flee from lights brighter than a torch or lantern and attack at -2 in daylight. Solifugids live in warm desert climates. They are indiscriminate eaters and, if hungry, attack anything that moves.",
