      "npc_notes": "SPIDER, GIANT MARINE\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 7+7\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: Incidental only\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/650 + 12/hp\n\nGiant marine spiders inhabit shallow seas and ocean waters in semitropical and tropical areas. Much as their freshwater cousins do, these creatures build huge air-filled underwater nests from webs and vegetation. They hide in seaweed, rush out and seize prey, paralyze it with a poisonous bite, and carry it back to their nest lairs. In all respects other than those noted, giant marine spiders resemble giant water spiders.",
