      "no_of_attacks": "3",
      "damage_attack": "7-12/1-3/1-3",
      "special_attacks": "See below",
      "special_defenses": "Camouflage",
      "magic_resistance": "Standard",
      "intelligence": "Semi-",
      "alignment": "Neutral",
      "size": "L",
      "psionic_ability": "Nil",
      "attack_defense_modes": "Nil/nil",
      "level_xp_value": "V/3000 + 16/hp",
      "monsterhd": "12",
      "monsterhd_bonus": "",
      "morale_base": "",
      "morale": "",
      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "SQUEALER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (or 2-4)\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: 15%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 7-12/1-3/1-3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Camouflage\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/3000 + 16/hp\n\nSquealers inhabit only temperate to tropical forests. They are usually solitary, although there is a 10% chance that an encounter with a mated pair and up to 2 young will occur. Young have 1-2 hit points per die and can bite only, doing 1-4 points of damage. Although a squealer cares nothing for treasure, most prey is dragged near the lair to be devoured, so there can be items of value there.\n\nA squealer can imitate many sounds perfectly, so it imitates distress calls, death shrieks, mating calls, and the like to attract prey. Squealers are voracious beasts and attack any carnivores or herbivores. Typically, the squealer crouches upon a low branch and, when a victim comes near, grasps the limb it is upon with 3 of its appendages and swings head down to bite and claw prey. If both claw attacks succeed, the squealer has grasped and held its victim and falls upon it next round doing 5-8 points of crushing damage and 2 additional clawing attacks. The attack mode is bite, claw, claw, claw, claw, 7-12/1-3 x4. The squealer has 18/00 Strength and weighs 400 pounds or more.\n\nWhen amidst foliage, the squealer's bulk is 75% invisible due to coloration, stillness, and care in concealment. If attacking by surprise, it adds +2 both to hit and damage with each attack. It is 50% likely to surprise a victim. A squealer is very fierce. When full grown, it is about the size of a large gorilla and a match for almost anything. The fur is long and colored yellow and green in alternating splotches. Its form is topped by hunched shoulders and a thrust-forward pig-like head. The head is about 2 feet long and is mostly mouth filled with sharp tushes. Arm-like forelimbs sprout from the hunched back, the rear limbs come from high up on the hindquarters, and a 5th limb grows from the middle of the back and can be turned either forward or rearward. All limbs are tipped with 3 clawed digits. The forelimb and back appendage digits are prehensile.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
    "npc_notes": "SQUEALER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (or 2-4)\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: 15%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 7-12/1-3/1-3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Camouflage\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/3000 + 16/hp\n\nSquealers inhabit only temperate to tropical forests. They are usually solitary, although there is a 10% chance that an encounter with a mated pair and up to 2 young will occur. Young have 1-2 hit points per die and can bite only, doing 1-4 points of damage. Although a squealer cares nothing for treasure, most prey is dragged near the lair to be devoured, so there can be items of value there.\n\nA squealer can imitate many sounds perfectly, so it imitates distress calls, death shrieks, mating calls, and the like to attract prey. Squealers are voracious beasts and attack any carnivores or herbivores. Typically, the squealer crouches upon a low branch and, when a victim comes near, grasps the limb it is upon with 3 of its appendages and swings head down to bite and claw prey. If both claw attacks succeed, the squealer has grasped and held its victim and falls upon it next round doing 5-8 points of crushing damage and 2 additional clawing attacks. The attack mode is bite, claw, claw, claw, claw, 7-12/1-3 x4. The squealer has 18/00 Strength and weighs 400 pounds or more.\n\nWhen amidst foliage, the squealer's bulk is 75% invisible due to coloration, stillness, and care in concealment. If attacking by surprise, it adds +2 both to hit and damage with each attack. It is 50% likely to surprise a victim. A squealer is very fierce. When full grown, it is about the size of a large gorilla and a match for almost anything. The fur is long and colored yellow and green in alternating splotches. Its form is topped by hunched shoulders and a thrust-forward pig-like head. The head is about 2 feet long and is mostly mouth filled with sharp tushes. Arm-like forelimbs sprout from the hunched back, the rear limbs come from high up on the hindquarters, and a 5th limb grows from the middle of the back and can be turned either forward or rearward. All limbs are tipped with 3 clawed digits. The forelimb and back appendage digits are prehensile.",
    "id": "monster_manual_ii_squealer"
  },
