      "npc_notes": "TARRASQUE\n\nFREQUENCY: Unique\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -3\nMOVE: 9\" (+6\" rush)\nHIT DICE: 300 hp\n% IN LAIR: See below\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 6\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-12/1-12/2-24/5-50/1-10/1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: \"Sharpness\" bite, terror\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (50' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil (immune to psionics)\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: X/37,500\n\nThe legendary tarrasque is possibly the most dreaded monster of all, for when active it ravages the countryside for miles. All vegetation and animal life is devoured or driven away. The land through which the monster passes becomes a barren waste requiring years to recover. The tarrasque eats voraciously and continually, and all living things are food to it, though it prefers warm-blooded creatures.\n\nIts normal attacks are 2 foreclaw attacks, a sweeping tail lash for 2-24 points of damage, a savage bite, and 2 thrusting horn attacks for 1-10 points each. The bite resembles a sword of sharpness in effect, for a to-hit score of 18 or better indicates some portion of the victim is severed, such as a limb, head, or torso. The rush of the tarrasque is possible only once every turn, because the monster is so large and ponderous.\n\nThe mere sight of the tarrasque is so terrifying that creatures under 3 levels or hit dice are paralyzed until it is out of sight, with no saving throw. Creatures of 3 or more levels or hit dice flee in panic, though those of 7 or more levels or hit dice who save vs. paralyzation are not affected.\n\nThe tarrasque has a carapace of exceptional hardness and reflectivity. Bolts and rays such as lightning bolt, cone of cold, and even magic missile are useless against it. On a 1 in 6 chance such attacks reflect directly back at the caster; otherwise they bounce harmlessly away. Fire of any sort has no effect. The monster regenerates 1 hit point per round after taking damage and can be struck only by +1 or better magic weapons.\n\nThe tarrasque is said to be slayable only if reduced to -30 hit points or fewer and then subjected to a wish for its death. Otherwise even the slightest piece of it regenerates the monster completely. Legend says that great treasure can be extracted from its body. The upper carapace, treated with acid and heat, yields 10-100 diamonds of 1,000 gp base value each. The underbelly material, mixed with the creature's blood and meteoric iron, produces a metal forgeable by dwarven smiths into 1-4 shields of +5 magical power.\n\nIt is fortunate that the tarrasque is active only for short periods. Typically it forages for a week or two, ravaging all but a few square miles of land, and then seeks a hidden underground lair and lies dormant for 5-20 months. Once every decade or so, the monster stays active for several months. Thereafter its dormancy becomes 4-16 years unless disturbed. The ratio of active to dormant state is about 1:30.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": ""
    },
