      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "TERMITE, GIANT HARVESTER WORKER\n\nFREQUENCY: See below\nNO. APPEARING: 6-60\nARMOR CLASS: 2/10 (head/body)\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1+2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (3' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2/hp\n\nGiant termites are found in subtropical and tropical forests and jungles where large amounts of vegetation are available. The nest is a stone-hard mound about 100 feet in diameter and 200-500 feet high. Numerous circular openings near the top, each 5-8 feet in diameter, lead to vertical, diagonal, and horizontal passages connecting to underground chambers. Termites are nocturnal and shun light. A group of more than 30 workers is always accompanied by 3-16 soldier termites.\n\nThe worker is weak-jawed and bites for only 1-2 points of damage. Soldier termites have strong jaws and can spit an irritating fluid similar to kerosene. This liquid blinds any creature struck unless a save vs. poison succeeds. Blindness lasts 5-20 rounds. The fluid burns if exposed to flame or heat; one quantity spit on a target and ignited inflicts 5-16 points of burning damage. The fluid can be spit only once per turn, with a range of 1\" and a volume of about 1 pint.\n\nIn the lair there will always be 10 times the number of workers and soldiers first encountered, spread throughout the nest. Additional termites are: 5-30 worker attendants in the egg chamber; 2-12 soldier guards in the egg chamber; 4-24 worker attendants in the royal chamber; 2-8 soldier guards in the royal chamber; 1 king, AC 5, MV 6\", HD 6+6, hp 30 or more, 1 attack, damage 3-18, size L, with double range and quantity fluid spit possible every other round; and 1 queen, AC 4, MV 3\", HD 8+8, hp 40 or more, 1 attack, damage 5-30, size L. The king and queen are found only in the royal chamber near the bottom of the underground nest. The egg chamber is nearby and contains as many eggs as workers and soldiers combined.\n\nIf either the egg or royal chamber is entered by intruders, all regular termites begin moving to the violated area. Those already there fight fiercely to protect it. All such workers and guards gain +1 to hit and +1 to damage, including those entering later. Somewhere near the royal chamber there is a shaft leading to a repository well where unusable metal and mineral items are dumped. Incidental treasure may rarely be found there, usually of small value. Giant termites communicate by touching antennae, but in crisis situations they send a broadcast telepathic call. Their worst enemies are formians, who are larger, more intelligent, hate termites, and enjoy eating their eggs.",
