royal chamber near the bottom of the underground nest. The egg chamber is nearby and contains as many eggs as workers and soldiers combined.\n\nIf either the egg or royal chamber is entered by intruders, all regular termites begin moving to the violated area. Those already there fight fiercely to protect it. All such workers and guards gain +1 to hit and +1 to damage, including those entering later. Somewhere near the royal chamber there is a shaft leading to a repository well where unusable metal and mineral items are dumped. Incidental treasure may rarely be found there, usually of small value. Giant termites communicate by touching antennae, but in crisis situations they send a broadcast telepathic call. Their worst enemies are formians, who are larger, more intelligent, hate termites, and enjoy eating their eggs.",
