      "npc_notes": "WILLOW, BLACK\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 1/4\"\nHIT DICE: 12-19\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 7-12 (within 30' of trunk)\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 each\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (evil)\nSIZE: L (6'-9' diameter trunk)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/2400 + 20/hp\n\nThe black willow is a mobile, sentient tree of evil disposition. Although it inhabits areas where normal willows grow, it gets only a portion of its nourishment from sun, air, water, and earth. The monster is carnivorous, relishing elves, gnomes, and humans particularly. It is 90% unlikely that a creature will recognize a black willow as such, for it can alter its trunk and limbs to appear as normal trees of various willow sorts. Sometimes it will have a smooth trunk and broad, inviting limbs; other times it will show safe-looking trunk cavities at the base or high on the upper trunk. Treants can spot a black willow instantly, but even druids cannot do so without magical aid, such as locate plants.\n\nTreasure is sometimes found buried beneath this tree-monster along with bones and other indigestible matter. This assumes the victims had treasure which weak acid could not digest and that the black willow has stayed in one locale for weeks.\n\nNormal attack is with lashing whip-like branches, but there are 2 special attack forms, one generally employed earlier. If a creature has climbed onto a safe-looking limb, the black willow generates an aura of drowsiness within a 20-foot radius, making tired creatures fall into natural sleep. No saving throw is possible. A hole opens underneath, and one or more victims are taken into the hollow limb. The limb then tilts to slide them into the trunk cavity.\n\nThe trunk's safe-looking openings also serve to close and trap victims in the digestive cavity of the trunk. The stomach is coated with sticky, nonflammable sap. Digestive sap then oozes up from the roots, filling the cavity at the rate of 1 foot per 10 rounds until the entire 8-foot cavity is filled. The juice is acidic and inflicts 1-4 points of damage per round until death occurs. Digestion is complete at -12 hit points or lower, and resurrection thereafter is impossible. Creatures trapped inside can use only short, sharp weapons because of the confined space. Maximum normal damage is 1 point per round; magical and Strength bonuses apply. Rescue usually must come from outside. A black willow regenerates at 1 point per turn.",
