prout a growth resembling a small furry creature to attract prey. The lure-growth is moved so as to \"look\" at approaching prey and then \"freezes\" so as to be \"unnoticed.\"\n\nThe body appears to be a grayish-brown tree stump 2-3 feet in diameter. Eyestalks are 10-15 feet long, brown near the base, green at the tips, and with pinkish or violet flower-like eyes. Roots are 9-12 feet long. The vertical maw in the trunk has jagged teeth and thick black lips. When shut, it appears to be an old scar on a normal tree stump.",
