      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "WORM, TENEBROUS\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 1\nMOVE: 1\"\nHIT DICE: 10\n% IN LAIR: 0%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Acid\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Poison bristles\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M (6 feet long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: None\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2400 + 20/hp\n\nThese insectoid predators inhabit most of the Plane of Shadows, though they are more common in forested areas. They seek warm-blooded prey but hesitate to attack humans.\n\nTenebrous worms are formidable opponents. Their heads are equipped with powerful mandibles that drip a highly caustic acid secreted from glands behind the creature's multi-faceted eyes. Any opponent struck by the mandibles is also subject to the secretion, save vs. poison at -3 or take double damage from the bite.\n\nThe head and forebody are covered with stiff bristles poisonous to mammals. Any opponent who strikes the protected area with an open hand or similar attack, such as claw, bite, or cause wounds, immediately suffers 1-4 points of damage from the bristles. The victim must also save vs. poison or be paralyzed from the contact. Such victims must receive a neutralize poison or slow poison spell within 1-4 rounds or the contact will be fatal. Opponents striking with a weapon gain the benefit of armor against this defense. To determine contact, multiply the attacker's armor class, ignoring shield and Dexterity bonuses, by 10 to determine a percentage chance. Contact occurs if that number or lower is rolled on percentile dice. There are fewer bristles on the head, reducing the chance of contact by 20%.\n\nTenebrous worms look like huge, partially bare caterpillars. The front section is covered with lusterless black bristles, while the hind parts are a wet, nauseating gray. The many facets of the creature's eyes reflect the half-light of the Plane of Shadows with a luminous glimmer, the only warning of their presence. Their small black legs allow rapid movement. Their great maws are flanked by huge pearly mandibles. These tusk-like weapons are quite beautiful if cut into sheets and inlaid, as with mother of pearl, and have a value of 1000-3000 gp per set.\n\nFor the adult stage of this monster, see \"Gloomwing.\"",
