      "no_of_attacks": "4",
      "damage_attack": "1-3 (x3), 4-16",
      "special_attacks": "Surprise on a 1-5",
      "special_defenses": "Immune to fire, cold attacks",
      "magic_resistance": "Standard",
      "intelligence": "Average",
      "alignment": "Neutral",
      "size": "S (4' tall)",
      "psionic_ability": "Nil",
      "attack_defense_modes": "Nil/nil",
      "level_xp_value": "V/355 + 8/hp (the source line appears OCR-damaged)",
      "monsterhd": "5",
      "monsterhd_bonus": "5",
      "morale_base": "",
      "morale": "",
      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "XAREN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 1\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 5+5\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 4\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-3 (x3), 4-16\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Surprise on a 1-5\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to fire, cold attacks\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/355 + 8/hp (the source line appears OCR-damaged)\n\nThe xaren are relatives of the xorn. They exist on the Elemental Plane of Earth but enjoy travel to the Prime Material Plane to feed. Their favorite metals are iron, copper, silver, gold, and electrum, in that order. Magic metal gives them 1 permanent hit point for every plus on an eaten item. Items that are not plus-enchanted neither help nor harm a xaren unless they are aligned to harm neutral creatures. This increase from +1 to +5 for eating a shield, for example, is limited so that total hit points can never exceed 45. Yet they still crave magic metal and are eager to obtain it. They are intelligent enough to understand the relationship between magic metal and their health.\n\nXaren, like xorn, blend with rock-like surroundings and thus are very likely to surprise others in such settings. They like to snack on metal, even in ore form, and can smell ore at 20 feet and magic metal at 40 feet. They do not eat much at a single meal, and metal weighing 5-8 pounds is enough to sate one for 1-4 days. Xaren speak a bizarre tongue, but telepathy or tongues can aid in understanding them. They will approach and seek a handout. They become highly aggravated if they smell magic metal which is not offered to them; in such a case they are 80% likely to attack. Failure to offer ordinary metal produces an attack 40% of the time.\n\nXaren are not harmed by fire and cold, even magical varieties, but lightning deals half or no damage. Move earth, flesh to rock, and dig kill them instantly. Rock to mud lowers their armor class to 10 in 1-4 rounds. Sharp weapons do only half damage, but blunt weapons do full damage. If attacked with a magic weapon, a xaren is 40% likely to try to bite the weapon, considering it armor class -2 for this attempt. A xaren bite destroys any weapon utterly, but the weapon's owner is allowed a saving throw vs. crushing blow with no bonus.\n\nXaren can move to the Elemental Plane of Earth at will and can move through solid rock at 9\" per round. It takes a xaren 1 full round to adjust its molecules so it can do this.\n\nThose residing on the Prime Material Plane are usually near treasure or ore of some kind. They hoard treasure for emergencies and eat it only if no other metal is at hand. Treasure is 40% for 2-200 of each type of coin except platinum; 20% for 1-8 gems, 10 gp base value; 10% for 1-2 magic items not made of metal and valued under 10,000 gp. Occasionally nonmetal magic items might be in their hoard. Their lair may be a room inside solid rock, for they can burrow through rock at 3\" per round. If so, 70% likely, it will not be very deep in the earth, only 10 feet or so. Xaren losing a melee flee to their lair and, if found there, escape to the Elemental Plane of Earth.",
