 Rock to mud lowers their armor class to 10 in 1-4 rounds. Sharp weapons do only half damage, but blunt weapons do full damage. If attacked with a magic weapon, a xaren is 40% likely to try to bite the weapon, considering it armor class -2 for this attempt. A xaren bite destroys any weapon utterly, but the weapon's owner is allowed a saving throw vs. crushing blow with no bonus.\n\nXaren can move to the Elemental Plane of Earth at will and can move through solid rock at 9\" per round. It takes a xaren 1 full round to adjust its molecules so it can do this.\n\nThose residing on the Prime Material Plane are usually near treasure or ore of some kind. They hoard treasure for emergencies and eat it only if no other metal is at hand. Treasure is 40% for 2-200 of each type of coin except platinum; 20% for 1-8 gems, 10 gp base value; 10% for 1-2 magic items not made of metal and valued under 10,000 gp. Occasionally nonmetal magic items might be in their hoard. Their lair may be a room inside solid rock, for they can burrow through rock at 3\" per round. If so, 70% likely, it will not be very deep in the earth, only 10 feet or so. Xaren losing a melee flee to their lair and, if found there, escape to the Elemental Plane of Earth.",
