      "monsterhd": "5",
      "monsterhd_bonus": "-8",
      "morale_base": "",
      "morale": "",
      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "XEG-YI\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 5-8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 7-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Energy drain\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: +1 or better weapon to hit; see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 15%\nINTELLIGENCE: High (mindless by human standards)\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 120 + 10 to 60\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/1100 + 10/hp\n\nXag-ya are creatures from the Positive Material Plane, and xeg-yi are from the Negative Material Plane. They are much alike, being reverse images of each other. Xag-ya are silver and fiery. Their touch brings a surge much like a bolt of lightning that causes combustion of highly flammable materials such as parchment, cloth, and wood.\n\nEvery other round, a xag-ya can loose a bolt of energy equal to its touch up to 10 feet at a single target. The bolt heats metallic objects to glowing. Metallic items of magical nature do not heat if their owners succeed on a saving throw vs. lightning. Base is 11 for hard metal and 16 for soft, with pluses to the die roll for magic components. Heated metal must be dropped and worn metal discarded. Damage per segment of contact with such metal is 1-4 points.\n\nThe touch of a black, lifeless xeg-yi causes cell death, mild life-energy drain, and aging and rotting of materials burned by xag-ya. Xeg-yi send identical tendrils of negative current which chill metal and inflict damage. Normal metal, magical properties, and magical metals which fail their save against the energy melt are lost. That which fails against the negative current of xeg-yi shatters or decays due to corrosion.\n\nSlaying either type releases a burst of energy or negative force in a 10-foot radius. This inflicts double damage, 14-24, on all within the area, and saving throws must be made as if a bolt had actually touched the affected creatures. If a xag-ya and xeg-yi should ever meet, they rush together and destroy each other in a huge 30-foot-radius explosion that inflicts 28-48 points of damage, 4d6+24, in the blast area.\n\nOnly magic weapons affect these creatures. Xag-ya are affected by magic creating cold, xeg-yi by magic creating heat. Both are subject to disintegrate and magic missile. Negation and absorption are effective against xag-ya attacks, while a mace of disruption and rod of cancellation are effective against xeg-yi attacks without harm to the devices used. A shield spell prevents the attack of either creature. A circle of protection, spell, magic circle, thaumaturgic triangle, or pentagram, repulses attacks of either kind. All other magic or spells have no effect except abjure, alter reality, banishment, dismissal, dispel magic, treat as magic of a level equal to twice the creature's hit dice, holy word or unholy word, limited wish, plane shift, and wish.\n\nXag-ya and xeg-yi are often used as guardians of magic. They can be ensnared by magic summons and linked to an object. When the object is torn, broken, or opened without properly negating the summoning link, the xag-ya or xeg-yi appears and attacks all within a 3\" radius of the object.\n\nBoth creatures are spherical with many radiating tentacle-like protrusions. Xag-ya have glowing golden eyes. Xeg-yi have dull metallic orbs.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": "-8"
    },
