      "monstermorale": "",
      "npc_notes": "YUAN TI\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4/0\nMOVE: 12\" or 9\"\nHIT DICE: 6-9\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spells\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 150\nAttack/Defense Modes: B, D/F, I, J\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: Variable\n\nInhabitants of tropical jungles, the yuan ti are a degenerate and corrupt race of creatures who were once human. All are devout demon worshipers who hold reptiles in high regard. Through dark and unknown practices, their blood has become fouled and they produce monstrosities. There are 3 types of yuan ti: purebloods, halfbreeds, and abominations.\n\nPurebloods are the weakest of the yuan ti, having only 6 hit dice. They are human in appearance except for slight differences, such as scaly hands, a forked tongue, or a somewhat reptilian look. They can pass as humans 80% of the time. Purebloods usually handle affairs with the outside world and may travel far and wide doing so.\n\nHalfbreeds are highly distinctive. Some part of the body is that of a snake while the rest is human. Appearance may be determined by rolling once or twice on the source table: snake head; torso can bend and move like a snake's; no legs, torso ends in a snake's tail; has snakes instead of arms; body is covered by scales; snake tail is growing from backside. Impossible results should be ignored or replaced by the DM.\n\nIn attacks, a halfbreed with a snake head bites for 1-10 points of damage, one with snake-headed arms bites for 1-6 points, and one with a tail constricts for 1-4 points. Otherwise the yuan ti can handle weapons as normal humans. All snake parts have armor class 0. Halfbreeds have 7-8 hit dice.\n\nAbominations are the strongest of the yuan ti. All have 9 hit dice. In appearance they are often confused with nagas and other snake creatures. Abominations are either totally snake-like or have only one human feature, such as a head or arms. Their bite, unless from a human head, does 1-10 points of damage.\n\nAll yuan ti with human legs move 12\" per turn. Those with snake bodies move 9\" per turn and can coil around pillars and the like. Human-headed yuan ti can cast the following spells once per day: cause fear, darkness within a 15-foot radius, snake charm, stick to snakes, neutralize poison, suggestion, and polymorph other.\n\nYuan ti speak their own language. They may also speak with any snake or snake-like monster. Those with human heads also speak Chaotic and Common.",
