      "npc_notes": "ZORBO\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 10 (see below)\nMOVE: 15\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 4+2\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: P, Q, X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 claws\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2 each + special\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Absorption\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Absorption\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (3' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/280 + 5/hp\n\nThis carnivorous beast likes human and demihuman flesh. A zorbo has poor armor class and attack damage when first encountered, but it can absorb the natural armor class of its surroundings in one round: earth = AC 7, wood = AC 5, metal = AC 3, stone = AC 0.\n\nThe new armor class lasts 10 rounds and also gives the zorbo a damage bonus equal to its original armor class 10 minus the new armor class. When a zorbo hits an opponent it can absorb the armor class and defensive bonuses of 1 random protective item, armor, shield, ring of protection, and so on, turning that item to dust with no save. If this would make the zorbo's current armor class worse, the item is destroyed but the armor class is not absorbed.\n\nFor example, if a zorbo is attacked in a cave and on the first round absorbs the armor class of stone, this gives it armor class 0 and a damage bonus of 10. The next round it hits and absorbs its opponent's shield +2. This gives it a new armor class of -2 and a damage bonus of +12. The third round it hits the opponent's plate mail, armor class 3, which turns to dust but does not change the zorbo's armor class or damage.",
      "source": "Monster Manual II",
      "monsterHD_bonus": "2"
    },
    "npc_notes": "ZORBO\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 10 (see below)\nMOVE: 15\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 4+2\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: P, Q, X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 claws\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2 each + special\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Absorption\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Absorption\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (3' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil/nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/280 + 5/hp\n\nThis carnivorous beast likes human and demihuman flesh. A zorbo has poor armor class and attack damage when first encountered, but it can absorb the natural armor class of its surroundings in one round: earth = AC 7, wood = AC 5, metal = AC 3, stone = AC 0.\n\nThe new armor class lasts 10 rounds and also gives the zorbo a damage bonus equal to its original armor class 10 minus the new armor class. When a zorbo hits an opponent it can absorb the armor class and defensive bonuses of 1 random protective item, armor, shield, ring of protection, and so on, turning that item to dust with no save. If this would make the zorbo's current armor class worse, the item is destroyed but the armor class is not absorbed.\n\nFor example, if a zorbo is attacked in a cave and on the first round absorbs the armor class of stone, this gives it armor class 0 and a damage bonus of 10. The next round it hits and absorbs its opponent's shield +2. This gives it a new armor class of -2 and a damage bonus of +12. The third round it hits the opponent's plate mail, armor class 3, which turns to dust but does not change the zorbo's armor class or damage.",
