    "npc_notes": "ALEAX\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: See below\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: See below\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: See below\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Regeneration; see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Nil\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: See below\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: See below\n\nAn aleax is a physical manifestation of the vengeance of certain gods. There is but one aleax for each such god, sent to punish and redeem those who stray from alignment, fail to sacrifice enough treasure, or otherwise anger their god. An aleax will never be met by chance. It appears in human form and closely resembles its intended victim. To that victim, the aleax appears bathed in shimmering light whose colour varies according to the god’s alignment. On appearing, the aleax attacks its intended victim. It cannot be detected in any way by others, nor will physical or magical attacks touch it except those from its victim. To observers, the victim appears to be struggling with a totally invisible, totally invulnerable being. To the victim, the aleax is in all respects his own duplicate, having the same characteristics, hit points, armour, weapons, and so on, except for two differences: once wounded, it regenerates at 1 hit point the next round, then 2, then 4, then 8, and so on until slain or fully restored; and any hit scored on an unmodified 19 does double damage, while an unmodified 20 does quadruple damage. A victim killed by an aleax loses all treasure and half his experience points, is automatically raised, and begins again at the appropriate experience level, but all magical possessions are stripped of power. If the victim kills the aleax, he is taken to serve his god personally for a year and a day, and on return regains his possessions and will almost certainly receive an additional divine reward. An aleax will utter only a few brief words in the victim’s alignment language to announce divine punishment and otherwise never converse.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_aleax"
  },
