    "npc_notes": "ALGOID\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: D (x%)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-10/1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to edged weapons of less than +2 bonus\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Immune to fireballs and lightning; otherwise standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-intelligent\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 101-120\nAttack/Defense Modes: A\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/280 + 5 per hit point\n\nThis creature appears as a green humanoid with coarse, rough features, but is actually a colony of algae assembled into temporary humanoid form, with some mobility and rudimentary intelligence. It is immune to psionic attacks but can deliver one mind blast per day. It attacks with its powerful fists, each inflicting 1-10 hit points of damage. Edged weapons pass through an algoid without effect unless they are magical and at least +2, in which case they inflict half normal damage; blunt weapons do full damage whether magical or not. The algoid also controls certain trees near its watery habitat, in much the same way a treant controls trees. It may control two willows, water-oaks, cypresses, or similar trees, each moving at 9\" and striking twice per round for 1-10 hit points per blow. Despite its immunity to fireball and lightning, it is especially vulnerable to purify water and lower water spells, each of which inflicts 1-6 hit points of damage per caster level.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_algoid"
  },
