    "npc_notes": "AL-MI'RAJ\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-20\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 18\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 5%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (3' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/10 + 1 per hit point\n\nThe al-mi'raj generally roams pastures and woodlands, though it is sometimes found in dungeons. Its lair is usually a small cave just below ground. It resembles a large yellow hare with a long black horn, about 1½-2 feet in length, protruding from the centre of its forehead like that of a unicorn. In melee it stabs with this horn, whose nimbleness gives it the damage potential of a dagger, inflicting 1-4 hit points. Its intellect is very limited and its behaviour unpredictable, and it may attack for no good reason. If captured young, however, it shows surprising aptitude for training, and its fearlessness makes it a useful companion. It also has a particularly acute sense of smell and sharp eyesight.",
