    "npc_notes": "APPARITION\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 24\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Can only be hit by magical or silver weapons\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/7,000 + 10 per hit point\n\nThis ghastly undead creature exists mainly on the Ethereal Plane, though when making its “attack” it can be hit, as if armour class 0, by magical or silver weapons. An apparition is turned as a spectre and is reluctant to approach mirrors or anything made of silver. It has an emotive ESP ability that lets it sense potential victims up to 100 feet away. It surprises on 1-5 on d6 by emerging from wall, floor, or ceiling, using the surprise to close with its target. When seen, it appears as an insubstantial skeletal being in a thin white robe. It cannot physically attack, but its chosen victim feels bony claw-like fingers at the throat, even through armour. No “to hit” roll is required. The victim must roll 3d6; if the total is under intelligence, the suggestion fails and the victim becomes immune to that individual apparition. If the total equals or exceeds intelligence, the victim is stricken with horror and must roll 3d6 again against constitution. If the total is less than constitution, the victim flees in terror for 1-4 melee rounds; if equal to or greater than constitution, the victim suffers a massive heart seizure and dies instantly. A slain victim may be raised, but if the body is left or no attempt is made within one hour to do so, it rises as an apparition in 2-8 hours. Characters able to move and fight on the Ethereal Plane may attack the apparition normally there, but on the Prime Material Plane it appears for only one melee round per victim attacked, and only during that period can it be struck by non-ethereal means.",
