    "npc_notes": "ASTRAL SEARCHER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 4-24\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: All victims AC 5\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 50%\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Any\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/73 + 2 per hit point\n\nAstral searchers are mindless shells of nebulous humanoid shape created by concentrated or traumatic human thought. Violent death, spells cast on the Astral Plane, and astral combat often result in their creation, usually without the knowledge of the person or event that caused them. Driven by their past connection to material beings, they roam the Astral Plane seeking weak points between the Astral and Prime Material Planes, clustering at such singularities until they can cross over. Once on the Prime Material Plane, they attack the nearest living humanoids in an attempt to possess their bodies. Their attack is psychic, so all victims are treated as armour class 5 regardless of physical or magical protection, though the victim believes the attack to be physical and suffers damage accordingly. All such damage is illusory and disappears 3-12 rounds after the attack ends. If an astral searcher reduces a victim to 0 hit points or below, the victim’s mind and personality are destroyed and the searcher possesses the body, gaining its physical abilities and hit points, but not its former personality. Alignment should then be redetermined at random. Astral searchers can be exorcised, but the original psyche is gone forever and the victim cannot be raised or restored. If driven from a body, the empty shell may then invite possession by a demon or similar being. Astral searchers are not undead. Since they exist simultaneously on two planes, they are 50% resistant to magic.",
