    "npc_notes": "BABBLER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 6\" or 12\" (see below)\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 15%\nTREASURE TYPE: B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6/1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average but high cunning\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (8' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/130 + 5 per hit point\n\nWeird mutations of lizard men, babblers are large, ponderous marsh-dwellers, known as marsh-gibberers to native tribes living near their swamp habitat. Their predominant colour is a dirty yellow, with grey undersides and mottled grey patches forming bizarre patterns across their muscular bodies. In shape, the babbler resembles a small gorgosaurus with a flexible, tough tail used to keep it stable while erect. In melee it stands upright in order to use its two foreclaws, which inflict 1-6 hit points of damage each, and its bite, which inflicts 1-8 hit points. It has a particularly large mouth filled with rows of sharp teeth. When moving on its belly, the babbler is difficult to detect, with a 25% chance to remain unnoticed, though animals will smell it at some distance. If undetected during approach, it can strike from behind as a 4th-level thief, doing double damage and gaining +4 on the to hit roll. The babbler is especially fond of human flesh and attacks humans unless outnumbered by more than two to one. Raiding parties of marsh-dwelling lizard men have been observed led by one, two, or even three babblers in search of human prey. It communicates with its own kind in a quasi-lingual babbling tongue that humans have never been able to analyse or learn, though it understands the common tongue in a crude fashion. Its normal movement is a surprisingly fast 12\" slither on its stomach, but in melee it must stand erect, reducing movement to 6\".",
    "id": "fiend_folio_babbler"
  },
