    "npc_notes": "BAT, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 3-18\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 3\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 1-4 hit points or 1\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2 or 1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/5 + 1 per hit point, or I/14 + 1 per hit point\n\nThese creatures are giant versions of ordinary carnivorous bats, with bodies about 3 feet long and wingspans of 5 to 6 feet, dwelling in dark caverns, usually underground. In flight they emit a high-pitched whistling sound that serves as a navigational aid and compensates for poor eyesight. Giant bats are highly manoeuvrable in flight; anyone with a dexterity of less than 13 firing a missile at a flying giant bat does so at -3 to hit. For aerial combat purposes they are manoeuvrability class C. The creature must land, usually on its victim, to bite, inflicting either 1-2 or 1-4 hit points of damage depending on size. One percent of victims bitten by giant bats contract rabies. Only 10% of giant bats are of the 1 hit die variety.",
