    "npc_notes": "BLINDHEIM\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: See below\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4+2\n% IN LAIR: 5%\nTREASURE TYPE: B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Blinding stare\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/130 + 5 per hit point\n\nThis subterranean creature is a yellow, frog-like humanoid with huge eyes that shine like searchlights. While at rest, it keeps its eyes “turned off” by means of an extra eyelid, but it can attack instantaneously by opening them, and its acute hearing usually tells it the direction of its target. Those caught within its beams at 30 feet or less must save as against wands or be blinded for 11-20 turns. Anyone with infravision in that range saves at -3. Those not blinded still cannot look directly at the creature, so its effective armour class is 1; however, if an attacker is immune to bright light, the blindheim’s true armour class is 3. At close quarters it bites for 1-8 hit points of damage. It is coloured in varying shades of yellow, with darker shades on the back and lighter ones on the underbelly. If the eyes of a dead blindheim are opened, they are seen to be a dull gold in colour.",
