    "npc_notes": "BLOOD HAWK\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 4-15 (d12+3)\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 24\"\nHIT DICE: 1+1\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: Q x2\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4/1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2 per hit point\n\nBlood hawks resemble normal hawks in size only, for their beaks are razor-sharp and their talons unusually strong. Their wings are more like those of an eagle, giving them considerable speed in flight. They attack with their beaks for 1-6 hit points of damage and with two sets of talons for 1-4 hit points of damage each, swooping swiftly and silently upon their victims. They are fond of human flesh and continue attacking humans even when the melee is going badly for them. They also pick at the dead bodies of their prey not only for food but for gems, with which they line their nests as an allurement to blood hawk females; all other treasure is ignored. Their colour is a uniform medium grey.",
