    "npc_notes": "BLOODWORM, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 5\"\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: 0\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8 + blood drain\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (20' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/225 + 6 per hit point\n\nGiant bloodworms are usually found in the shallow pools of underground caverns. They cannot swim, but propel themselves along the bottom of such pools or across nearby firm ground. Their underbelly is a dark slimy brown, while the upper surface is mottled green. Lying half in and half out of a pool, a giant bloodworm is easily mistaken in dim light for a moss-covered boulder. It attacks only if hungry, as they feed once a week, or if trodden on. When it does attack, it attempts to fasten its large suckered mouth onto a victim. If successful, it drains blood automatically in subsequent rounds, doing 1-8 hit points of damage each round until it dies or releases its grip. The initial attack requires a successful to hit roll and causes no damage. Giant bloodworms are especially vulnerable to fire, taking double damage from all fire attacks and saving at -2 against magical fire. A successful fire attack is the only way, short of killing the creature, to force it to relax its grip, though if it survives it attempts to reattach itself immediately.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_bloodworm_giant"
  },
