    "npc_notes": "BONESNAPPER\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 5\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8/1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M (5' high)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/60 + 4 per hit point\n\nThe bonesnapper is a small descendant of a long-extinct class of carnivorous dinosaur, as stupid as it is aggressive. Its large jaws contain many sharp teeth with which it inflicts 1-8 hit points of damage in melee, while its tail sweeps around to deliver 1-4 hit points of damage to the same victim. Its aggressive nature causes it always to fight to the death. Though non-intelligent, it has inherited a primeval instinct for collecting human bones, particularly jawbones, which it uses to decorate its subterranean lair. The number of such bones in a lair gives a good indication of the creature’s status among its kind. It is grey-green, mottled with dark grey spots and patches, with tiny scarlet eyes and yellow-white teeth.",
