    "npc_notes": "BOOKA\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 12\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 1-4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 75%\nTREASURE TYPE: J\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Nil\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 10%\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (chaotic good)\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/5 + 1 per hit point\n\nBooka are sprite-like creatures given to dwelling in attics, eaves, and on sunny rooftops. They hate cold, and in colder climates remain indoors near chimneys. On bright sunny mornings they sweep the stairs or porch of the place where they live, always making sure nobody is present to observe them. If disturbed while doing so, they become angry and immediately move to a new home. Booka are very fast-moving and can also fly. They can become invisible at will, even while running or flying. They hate evil creatures and play tricks on them when possible, hiding valued objects, tangling rope, hair, or clothing, and generally causing trouble. If a booka is captured or harmed, others of its kind who learn of it will bring dozens more booka to plague the offender until the captive is freed or amends are made with a valuable gift, such as gold, jewellery, or even a magical item, placed on a rooftop and left for a day. Failure to placate angry booka eventually results in some sort of fatal accident, for they will set snares and traps for the offender. A booka is only about 1 foot tall. Both males and females tend to have large features and thin bodies, and can charitably be described as homely. For aerial combat purposes they are manoeuvrability class A, though they avoid combat whenever possible through invisibility.",
