    },
    "npc_notes": "BULLYWUG\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 10-80\nARMOR CLASS: 6 (or better)\nMOVE: 3\"//15\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: J, K, M, Q (x5), and C (magic only) in lair\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3 or 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2/1-2/2-5 or by weapon\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Hop\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Hop\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: S to M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nRegular = I/18 + 1 per hit point\nLeader = II/36 + 2 per hit point\nShaman or Great Chief = III/80 + 3 per hit point\n\nThe bullywugs are a batrachian race of bipedal monsters which inhabit wet places: rainy forests, marshes, damp caves, or nearly any other shady or dark place with water nearby, since bullywugs must dampen their skins from time to time. Some groups are more intelligent than others. The more intelligent groups tend to live in caves or deserted human habitations, and usually possess armour, shields, and various weapons; use the example of human bandits for arms and armour. The less advanced bullywugs hate their more intelligent fellows and wage war on them. Unless encumbered by armour and shield, a bullywug is able to swim rapidly. Even with such encumbrance, it can swim at 9\". With or without gear, it can hop forward 3\" or upward 1½'. In doing so, it gains +1 on its to hit roll or rolls. If it is using an impaling weapon, a successful hopping attack inflicts double damage. The hopping attack with a weapon is their normal means of melee. However, bullywugs without access to weapons, or those which have been disarmed, will still hop to the attack, in which case they use two claws for 1-2 hit points of damage each and a bite for 2-5 hit points of damage. Bullywugs have a chameleon-like power; their skin can become grey, green, or brown in light or dark shades. Thus, if motionless and in an area allowing use of this camouflage, a bullywug is 75% unlikely to be noticed, and this applies even to infravision because the colour alteration also alters body heat. When attacking unnoticed from camouflage, the bullywug has a 3 in 6 chance of surprising its victim, or 5 in 6 if hopping to the attack. Their major weakness is that unless they are using long weapons, their attacks always take place after those of their opponents because of slow movement or exposure while hopping; a weapon can be set against a hop just as against a charge. Bullywugs form organised bands and are always led by a large individual with a full 8 hit points. If 30 or more are encountered, there will be at least 5 large individuals and a leader of 10-13 hit points, effectively a 2 HD monster, doing +1 damage on all attacks. Those using armour and equipment also have a 10% chance per ten creatures in the group of having a tribal shaman of 11-14 hit points. Groups of 60 or more will have a great chief of 16-19 hit points doing +2 damage on all attacks. They readily serve chaotic evil masters. It is rumoured that bullywug-human crossbreeds are viable and that certain degenerate humans live in mixed communities with them, serving unnamed things from deep caverns beneath the earth. Bullywugs have their own primitive language, and the more intelligent ones can converse haltingly in the common tongue. Sahuagin despise them and will sometimes raid a bullywug lair for sport and malice, eating captives alive. Lizard men rarely associate with bullywugs, though there is no open hostility.",
