    "npc_notes": "BUNYIP\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (chaotic good)\nSIZE: M (6' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/90 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe bunyip is an aquatic beast resembling a seal covered in thick black fur, with a black mane and unusually powerful jaws. It lives in lakes, marshes, and sluggish rivers. It is a mischievous creature of playful intent, but it is large and strong enough to tip over a small boat. It can sense the approach of humans and may, with a 50% chance, rise momentarily above the surface to roar at a nearby party; all members of the party below 4th level must save at -2 versus wands or flee in panic. If a small creature such as a dwarf is struggling in the water, the bunyip will usually, with 30% chance, bite in an attempt to sever and swallow a limb, but it will not attack anything larger than a dwarf except in self-defence or unless the victim is already bleeding. A successful bite inflicts 1-6 hit points of damage. If it attacks on an unmodified 20, a limb is severed, determined randomly or by circumstance.",
