    "npc_notes": "CARYATID COLUMN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-12\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 22 hit points\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: All saving throws +4\nINTELLIGENCE: [unresolved]\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M (7' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/280\n\nCaryatid columns are similar to stone golems in that they are created either by means of a magical tome or by a magic-user of 16th level or higher, using the same spells required for a stone golem. However, the cost is somewhat higher and the time required is doubled because of the intricacy of their construction. The result is a slim decorative stone pillar about 7 feet high. At a glance it seems to be nothing more than ornamental stonework, perhaps standing beside an identical partner at the entrance to a chamber, chapel, or throne room. Closer examination reveals that the column is not radially symmetrical and has the very slender shape of a human female. Once this is noticed, the observer can make out that one of the figure’s hands, held close to its side, carries a slender sword that blends almost invisibly into the stone. A caryatid column always has a specific defensive role and is never encountered as a wandering monster. It may guard treasure, bar access to a forbidden area, or serve a similar purpose. If its creator is nearby when it animates, the creator can direct it with simple verbal commands; otherwise it follows simple predetermined courses of action. It activates as soon as an act occurs that its task forbids. When it animates, it takes on a fleshy appearance, shrinks to about 5½ feet in height, expands slightly, and appears as a fair young maiden. The formerly stone sword becomes steel, and with it the creature attacks as a 5 HD being for 2-8 hit points of damage. It does not always fight, however; if it can achieve its function without combat, it may misdirect intruders into traps, monsters, or spell attacks arranged by its creator. If combat is unavoidable, it attacks. Normal weapons do only half damage to it. Magical weapons do full damage, but without their magical plus. Any weapon striking the creature has a 25% chance of snapping, not cumulative, and each magical plus reduces that chance by 5%; magical weapons without a plus are treated as +1 for this purpose. When the task is complete, the caryatid column returns to its original position and becomes stone again. If killed, it immediately reverts to stone where it stands, as does its sword.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_caryatid_column"
  },
