    "npc_notes": "CATERWAUL\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 6 (see below)\nMOVE: 18\" or 24\" (see below)\nHIT DICE: 4+2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: N, R, S, U\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4/1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Screech; multiple attacks\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: [unresolved]\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/170 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe caterwaul is a solitary, vicious, feline bipedal predator with short midnight-blue fur, yellow eyes, and a long tail. Its lair is usually a cave littered with twigs and rushes. Its treasure consists only of shiny objects, and it is especially fond of gems. The walls of its cave are covered with long scratch marks where it has honed its claws. Its agility varies from individual to individual; percentile dice determine both armour class bonus and attacks per round. This dexterity bonus also applies to dodging ability and to saving throws against fireball, lightning bolt, and similar attacks. Attacks per round are handled exactly like the multiple attack table for fighters, rangers, and paladins. The creature moves swiftly on two legs, and can reach 24\" speed in short bursts by dropping to all fours. It can climb nearly any surface, with only a 5% base chance of slipping, move silently 75% of the time, and hide in shadows 75% of the time. Its preferred tactic is to lurk above and spring down on unsuspecting prey. It has keen hearing and an exceptional sense of smell and is difficult to surprise, with only a 10% chance. Its initial attack, and only its initial attack, is always accompanied by a high-pitched keening screech that inflicts 1-8 hit points of damage on all hearing creatures within 60 feet, unless they save versus breath, in which case no damage is suffered. It attacks with two claws for 1-4 hit points each and a bite for 1-6 hit points, each round or more often as indicated by its agility result.",
