    "npc_notes": "CIFAL\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 6\" (see below)\nHIT DICE: 8 or 10 (see below)\n% IN LAIR: 15%\nTREASURE TYPE: Q\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Damage from edged weapons reduced; see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,350 + 14 per hit point\n\nThe cifal, whose name is acronymic for “colonial insect-formed artificial life,” is an agglomeration of several swarms of insects, several hundred thousand to a swarm, joined into a single amorphous man-sized creature. The mass as a whole has 8 hit dice, while another 2 hit dice provide the nuclear energy needed to keep the swarms locked in one body. Initial damage is taken from the hit points of that binding force; if these hit points are lost, the body separates into its component insects and they fly away at 24\" speed. The insects attack and defend only while in mass-body form. The hit points of the binding force can be replenished from the remaining mass-body hit points at a rate of 2 per melee round. The cifal attacks by means of countless tiny bites which collectively inflict 1-12 hit points of damage. Edged weapons, magical or not, inflict only 1 point of damage regardless of type, while blunt weapons inflict full normal damage. Strictly speaking, the creature does not fly; the movement rate listed is ground movement, though it results from the restricted flying speed of the component swarms maintaining shape coherence. The cifal has no aerial manoeuvrability class, though the constituent insects are class A.",
