    "npc_notes": "CLUBNEK\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 2-8\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 12\" (see below)\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6/1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2 per hit point\n\nThese creatures are mutated forms of the ostrich with hard, bony beaks that inflict 1-8 hit points of damage. They also fight with two claws, each inflicting 1-6 hit points of damage. They can make occasional bursts of high speed, achieving a movement rate of 24\" for one melee round in every five. Clubneks are coloured in varying shades of green and have yellow beaks. They are not normally aggressive unless threatened, but their behaviour is erratic and unpredictable. Normally herbivorous, they are rarely found underground, preferring meadowland and woods.",
