    "npc_notes": "COFFER CORPSE\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 80%\nTREASURE TYPE: B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Can only be hit by magical weapons\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/36 + 2 per hit point\n\nThese foul undead creatures are found in stranded funeral barges or wherever a corpse has failed to return to its maker. Though resembling a zombie, a coffer corpse is treated as a wraith on the cleric/undead table. Normal weapons appear to do damage, and if struck for more than 6 hit points by normal weapons in a single melee round, it falls to the ground apparently finished. In fact, normal weapons do no damage at all, and if it falls in one round it rises the next and continues fighting; at that moment, all engaged in melee with it must save versus fear or flee in panic. A coffer corpse is occasionally, 25% of the time, found with a weapon that it will use in combat. Otherwise it attacks with bare hands, treated as a single attack inflicting 1-6 hit points of damage. If it hits with bare hands, it has locked its hands around the victim’s throat. Each subsequent round it inflicts 1-6 hit points automatically until it is killed or the victim dies. Nothing releases this grip once established. Sleep, charm, and other mind-affecting spells do not affect coffer corpses. Magical weapons inflict damage normally, including their usual bonuses.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_coffer_corpse"
  },
