    "npc_notes": "CRABMAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-12\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 9\"/6\"\nHIT DICE: 3\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: K\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (9' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/35 + 3 per hit point\n\nCrabmen are amphibious creatures usually found in sea-shore caves. They are humanoid in form but have a hard reddish-brown exoskeleton. Instead of hands they have two pincers, each inflicting 1-4 hit points of damage. Crabmen greatly value silver and will go to great lengths to obtain it, even attacking characters suspected of carrying silver objects. Otherwise they are generally peaceful, though at times some instinct drives them inland in savage raiding bands of 30 or 40, pillaging everything in their path and attacking defenders without hesitation. Crabmen are often raided by sahuagin, who consider them a delicacy, but the sahuagin’s usual net tactics are ineffective because crabmen can quickly cut through nets with their pincers.",
