    "npc_notes": "CRYPT THING\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Z\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/275 + 6 per hit point\n\nA crypt thing is a pale, solitary skeletal being that always wears a brown hooded robe. It remains permanently in its lair and does not attack if left undisturbed. Its special power is an unfailing ability to cast an improved teleportation effect on a party, once per party encountered. Those failing their saving throws are instantly teleported according to a percentile table: 01-20 sends them 100-1000 feet north, 21-40 south, 41-60 east, 61-80 west, 81-90 one dungeon level up, and 91-00 one dungeon level down. Distance and direction are determined separately for each victim. Victims never arrive inside solid matter, but are placed in the nearest open space, and they need not arrive at floor level. Those who make their saves may attack the crypt thing, but it can only be hit by magical weapons. It then attacks in return with a two-handed clawing motion for 1-8 hit points of damage. It can communicate in the neutral tongue, but if questioned about vanished party members it claims they were disintegrated rather than revealing its power. Rumours speak of aberrant crypt things that paralyse victims and simultaneously turn them invisible instead of teleporting them. Neither type feeds on victims; they seem motivated purely by the pleasure of causing confusion and dissent.",
