    "npc_notes": "DAKON\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 6-60\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 16\"\nHIT DICE: 1+1\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-10/1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2 per hit point\n\nA dakon is a shabby but intelligent ape with a reasonable grasp of the common tongue. It never attacks except in self-defence or to recover treasure stolen from it. When it does attack, it gains +2 to hit because of its strength and sharp claws, each of which inflicts 1-10 hit points of damage. Dakons are usually light brown with green eyes and black hands. They are found in all types of terrain except near large expanses of water. They are normally on good terms with lawful humans and near-humans, though suspicious of humanoids and unwilling to communicate with them.",
