    "npc_notes": "DARK CREEPER\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (20-80, see below)\nARMOR CLASS: 0 (or 8, see below)\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1+1\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/110 + 2 per hit point\n\nThe dark creeper is a slightly built humanoid about dwarf height. The race always dresses in sombre dark clothing, concealing as much of its pallid skin as possible. It hates light and dwells deep underground, usually living alone, though rumours speak of villages of up to 80 individuals, including 20%-25% females, always ruled by a dark stalker. Dark creepers are especially fond of small magical items such as rings and magic daggers. Solitary individuals carry 25% of their treasure in the many pockets of their cloaks, so any one encountered has a 15% chance of a magic dagger, 5% chance of a magic ring, and 10% chance of 1-4 gems or 1-2 items of jewellery. In lair, multiply these possible items by the number of resident males, and add 1-100 platinum pieces and 50-500 gold pieces. A dark creeper has the abilities of a 4th-level thief, as well as the ability to detect magical items within 15 feet. It attacks with a normal dagger or a magical dagger if it possesses one. It also has the innate power to create darkness three times per day. When used, all torches, lanterns, and other non-magical lights within 50 feet are extinguished and cannot be relit for one hour. During this time the creeper’s priorities are to destroy lanterns, tinderboxes, oil flasks, and anything else that would permit new illumination, and to steal small magical items it detects. Self-preservation ranks only slightly above these aims. Magical light sources may also be affected; they receive a saving throw against magical frost, and if they fail they are extinguished for one hour before returning to normal. Even infravision is useless during this darkness, though the creeper does not use the power against parties not relying on artificial illumination, so elves using infravision may pass unmolested. The darkness can be countered by spells such as light, and if the creeper is attacked in normal illumination its AC is 8. If killed, its body undergoes spontaneous combustion so intense that all within 10 feet are blinded for 1-6 full turns unless they save versus magic. All traces of the creature are destroyed. Metal items normally survive, with an 80% chance, but magical items lose their dweomer if they fail a save against magical fire.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_dark_creeper"
  },
