    "npc_notes": "DARK STALKER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0 (or 8 — see below)\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 2+1\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/200 + 3 per hit point\n\nDark stalkers are the rarely seen leaders of the dark creepers. They are nearly a race apart, breeding almost exclusively among themselves, and are immediately noticeable among dark creepers because they are man-sized and stand head and shoulders above their underlings. There is an average of one dark stalker to every 25 dark creepers, and each dark creeper village contains at least one stalker ruler. They are seldom encountered alone, though this sometimes occurs when a stalker is engaged in some mysterious personal mission. Dark stalkers possess all the powers of dark creepers and in addition can create a wall of fog twice per day. If forced to fight, they use short swords, and 25% of these are magical. All of their treasure is carried: there is a 7% chance of a magical ring and a 12% chance of 2-5 gems or 1-2 items of jewellery on any individual encountered. If attacked in normal illumination, the dark stalker has AC 5. If killed, it explodes in a blinding flash equal to a 5-dice fireball.",
