    "npc_notes": "DEATH DOG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 5-50\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2+1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-10/1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Disease\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral with evil tendencies\nSIZE: M (4' high at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/115 + 5 per hit point\n\nLarge black hounds with two heads, death dogs usually hunt in packs in deserts or dry underground regions. Each head can bite independently for 1-10 hit points of damage. Any victim bitten must save against poison or die from a slow, rotting disease in 4-24 days; cure disease is an effective remedy. When attacking, a death dog usually aims for the legs. A natural 19 or 20 on the hit roll against a man-sized or smaller victim means the victim is knocked to the ground and attacks at -4 until able to rise, which takes one round if the victim is not knocked down again. These vicious hounds usually attack humans and near-humans on sight, with an 85% chance, and their loud, penetrating double bark is said to support the belief that they descend from Cerberus.",
