    "npc_notes": "DEATH KNIGHT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: Variable\nHIT DICE: 9 (10-sided dice)\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 75% (see below)\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to genius\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: MW\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/3,300 + 16 per hit point\n\nThere are only twelve death knights known to exist. Each is a horrifying form of lich created by a demon prince, thought to be Demogorgon, from a fallen human paladin. A death knight cannot be turned or dispelled, though it is affected by holy word, and it commands undead as a 6th-level cleric. It has 75% magic resistance, and if 11 or lower is rolled on percentage dice, a magic spell is reflected back at the caster; this roll is made each time a spell is attempted. The death knight wears light armour, moving 9\" or 12\" depending on encumbrance, but is always treated as AC 0. It has 18/00 strength and usually attacks with a sword, with an 80% chance that the weapon is magical. It is usually mounted on a nightmare, one of which it can summon every ten years to serve it as a paladin’s horse serves a paladin. It continually radiates fear in a 5' radius, can create a wall of ice at will, and has innate powers of detect magic and detect invisibility. Twice per day it can dispel magic and gate in a type I demon (20%), type II (25%), type III (30%), type IV (20%), or type VI (5%), with a 75% chance that the gate opens. Once per day it can use any one power word spell, a symbol of pain or fear, and create a 20-dice fireball. Where applicable, its magic is cast at 20th level. A death knight speaks 3-6 languages in addition to common and its alignment tongue.",
