    "npc_notes": "DENZELIAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 1\"\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Nil\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: Not applicable\n\nThe denzelian is a peaceful rock-eater. It is very thin but broad, roughly 10' x 10' x 3\", and tunnels through solid rock at the rate of 1' per week, slowly wearing it away. A male and female usually tunnel near one another. Denzelians avoid metal, detouring around even small deposits, so their tunnels tend to meander. Because they resemble stone, smell repulsive, and are indigestible, they are rarely bothered by flesh-eaters. During its thousand-year lifespan, a female denzelian ovulates only once. If a male is nearby, which usually he is, the resulting litter contains 3-8 eggs that hatch in 100 years. The eggs look like nondescript fist-sized stones. The chance of finding a single egg in an area frequented by a female is 1 in 1,000. Such an egg is worth 1,000 gp or more to certain wealthy mine-owners.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_denzelian"
  },
