    "npc_notes": "STYX DEVIL, GREATER DEVIL\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2\nARMOR CLASS: -1\nMOVE: 6\"/15\"\nHIT DICE: 6+6\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: Q, R\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Cannot be hit by normal weapons; see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 50%\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 121\nAttack/Defense Modes: B,D/F,G,H\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,275 + 8 per hit point*\n*for destroying Material Plane form only; if actually killed permanently, multiply X.P. by 10.\n\nResidents of the fifth plane of Hell, styx devils are humanoid, with disproportionately large ugly heads and black wings trimmed with silver. Their principal task is to search for souls to bring back to Geryon, but from time to time they tour the Material Plane intending to destroy any humans they meet. They are invulnerable to ordinary weapons, but may be harmed by silver weapons and magical weapons of +1 or better. Their touch does 2-8 hit points of damage and has a 50% chance of inflicting an imprisonment spell with no saving throw allowed; treat it as cast at 22nd level, and assume the styx devil has perfect knowledge of the victim’s identity. To dispel a styx devil requires holy word. For aerial combat purposes, the styx devil is manoeuvrability class C.",
