    "npc_notes": "DEVIL DOG\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 4-16\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 30\" maximum\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Throat attack\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M (3' at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/350 + 6 per hit point\n\nStark-white hounds with blue eyes, devil dogs live in cold regions and are invisible beyond 30' when encountered in snow or frost. They roam in packs in constant search of food and always attack human parties, using their coloration to the best advantage. They attack with a vicious bite aimed at the throat. Normal damage is 2-8 hit points, but if the hit roll exceeds what was needed by 4 or more, or if a natural 20 is rolled, the victim is struck in the throat, takes double damage, falls comatose for 2-8 turns, and must receive cure light wounds or stronger aid during that time or die at the end of the period. Of course, the initial damage may kill the victim outright. When attacking or giving chase, devil dogs emit a terrible baying that causes fear in any character of 3rd level or lower unless a save at -4 versus magic is made. They can sustain their high 30\" speed for three turns, after which they must “rest” for three turns at a maximum speed of 12\".",
