    "npc_notes": "DIRE CORBY\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-12\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: G (x5), J — mainly rubies\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2 per hit point\n\nThis subterranean race of huge black bipedal birds contains ferocious fighters who never check morale. Long ago dire corbies lost the power of flight, but they make up for this with strength and ferocity, always attacking and fighting to the death. What were once wings have developed into two powerful arms ending in sharp, rock-hard claws, each of which inflicts 1-6 hit points of damage. They hunt in flocks, running down their prey while emitting horrifying shrieks. They possess a rudimentary language, and their attack cry can be recognized by those familiar with it as “Doom! Doom!” Dire corbies live in large underground caverns. Formerly they warred openly with giant bats, but this has now settled into an uneasy truce.",
