    "npc_notes": "DISENCHANTER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below; special effect only\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Disenchants; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Can only be hit by magical weapons\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M (5' high at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: [unresolved]\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/205 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe disenchanter resembles a spindly dromedary-like animal with a long, flexible, muscular snout that can extend as much as 5' in attack. It is pale electric blue and slightly translucent, sometimes visibly shimmering. The creature detects magical dweomer on armour, shields, swords, and the like, and feeds upon it. It is discriminating enough to distinguish between different strengths of magic and will choose the most potent item available. If it encounters an adventuring party, it attempts to fasten its snout onto the most powerful magical item it can reasonably reach. If it hits, it drains the item’s enchantment, leaving it physically unchanged but permanently non-magical. Referees must judge how easy it is for the creature to reach a particular item; generally it prefers an accessible shield to a more powerful item buried in a pack or sheath. Only magical weapons can hit the beast, but striking it with such weapons does not disenchant them; only its snout attack drains magical items. No one has ever discovered a disenchanter lair or reached any proven conclusion about its metabolism.",
