    "npc_notes": "DOOMBAT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-8\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 18\"\nHIT DICE: 6+3\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Shriek\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/400 + 7 per hit point\n\nThis giant bat is found in dismal underground caverns. The monstrous black creature has a wingspan of 25' and can carry off objects weighing up to 300 pounds, or 3,000 gold pieces weight. At night it flies into the outer world to hunt, always attacking and seeking to kill any living thing. For aerial combat it is manoeuvrability class C. Its bite inflicts 1-6 hit points of damage, and it lashes with a barbed tail for 1-4 hit points. The tail can be very long, with reports of specimens having tails up to 12'. The normal bat’s sonar cry has developed into a terrifying shriek of great sonic power. Each doombat can shriek continuously for 2-5 rounds, and while the shriek lasts, all within 100' who can hear cannot concentrate, making spellcasting impossible and causing all attacks to suffer -1. No saving throw is allowed, and multiple doombats shrieking do not stack these effects. Bright light, such as a light spell, keeps a doombat at bay, though torchlight or lantern-light does not.",
