      "monsterhd_bonus": ""
    },
    "npc_notes": "ORIENTAL DRAGONS, GENERAL\n\nOriental dragons are related to, though different in some respects from, other dragons. They vary in colour, possibly white, red, yellow, blue, green, or black. Their powers vary with type, and each sort of dragon is treated individually. Oriental dragons, like other dragons, have three general size categories (small, average, huge) determined by rolling d8: 1-2 small; 3-7 average; 8 huge. This also indicates hit dice. They pass through eight ages: very young, young, sub-adult, young adult, adult, old, very old, and ancient, with hit points per die increasing from 1 to 8 accordingly. Oriental dragons never sleep and have continual ESP at a range in feet equal to five times their age level. All except yu lung can polymorph into human form and back at will, and can become invisible at will, though they become visible when attacking. Only yu lung can be subdued. Certain types have scaly command over unintelligent scaly water creatures. Certain others have water fire, an unearthly burning aura while in contact with water. Like other dragons except yu lung, adult and older oriental dragons radiate a fear aura. Multiple dragon encounters follow the usual mated pair or young rules. Treasure scales upward with age. Saving throws are modified by actual hit points per die once an oriental dragon attains 5 or more hit points per die.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_oriental_dragons_general"
  },
