    "npc_notes": "LI LUNG, EARTH DRAGON\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 3\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 7-9\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: H\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8/2-8/1-20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spells; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (18' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n7 HD: VI/575 + 8 per hit point\n8 HD: VI/925 + 10 per hit point\n9 HD: VII/1,400 + 12 per hit point\n\nThe li lung is the only oriental dragon with wings. It has a lion’s body and a dragon’s head with human features. It lives underground and can swim, though it cannot breathe water. It attacks with two claws doing 2-8 hit points each and a bite doing 1-20 hit points. It has no breath weapon, but once per day it can cause an earthquake, as the spell but with no chance of being dispelled, affecting an area whose width and length in tens of feet are equal to three times the dragon’s age level; a sub-adult, for example, creates a 30' square effect. Such quakes may collapse the cavern in which it lives, but li lung are never harmed by earthquakes, though they may be inconvenienced by rubble. Their powerful claws allow them to burrow through solid stone at 1\" per turn and through earth at six times that rate. In the air they are manoeuvrability class E.",
