    "npc_notes": "LUNG WANG, SEA DRAGON\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 0\nMOVE: 3\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 11-13\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: H (x2)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-12/1-12/6-36\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapon and spells; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (up to 30' diameter)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n11 or 12 HD: VIII/4,550 + 16 per hit point\n13 HD: IX/6,350 + 18 per hit point\n\nThese solitary brutes are oriental relatives of the dragon turtle, with a turtle’s body, a crested neck, and a head like a shen lung. They rule large bodies of water and can breathe either air or water. They are strong enough to lift any ship they get under, or to ram like the largest warship. Their ordinary attacks are two claws for 1-12 hit points each and a bite for 6-36 hit points. They can breathe a cone of steam 100' long and 50' wide at the base up to three times per day. This breath weapon inflicts damage equal to the dragon’s current hit points. Lung wang possess the scaly command power over 4-40 creatures multiplied by the dragon’s age level, but do not have water fire. They have no spells other than those general to oriental dragons. As rulers of the seas, they demand tribute from every passing ship. Regular travelers may make arrangements by dumping treasure overboard at a set place. They also have their own language.",
