    "npc_notes": "T’IEN LUNG, CELESTIAL DRAGON\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -2\nMOVE: 9\"/48\"//6\"\nHIT DICE: 11-13\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: H (x2)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6/4-40\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapon and spells; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Lawful neutral\nSIZE: L (48' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n11 or 12 HD: VIII/4,550 + 16 per hit point\n13 HD: IX/6,350 + 18 per hit point\n\nT’ien lung live on high mountain peaks and in cloud castles and are rulers of the air. Their usual colouration is yellow. Though wingless, they fly by using the same kind of magical organ in the brain possessed by shen lung. They normally attack with two claws, each doing 1-6 hit points of damage, and a bite that does 4-40 hit points of damage. They breathe fire in a 90' by 30' cone up to six times a day, inflicting damage equal to the dragon’s current hit points. They may also cast control weather a number of times per day equal to twice the dragon’s age level. T’ien lung of old age and older have a 60% chance of being accompanied by 1-6 wind walkers, who are fanatically loyal and will defend or avenge their master. T’ien lung are very fond of opals and pearls and react favorably to mortals offering such delicacies. In the air they are manoeuvrability class D. They speak their own language, their alignment language, and the common tongue.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_t_ien_lung_celestial_dragon"
  },
