    "npc_notes": "YU LUNG, CARP DRAGON\n\nNOTE: The OCR columns on this page were inconsistent. The stat line below is the final corrected yu lung stat line used in the conversation, while the descriptive text on the page also showed a conflicting set of attacks. This discrepancy remains unresolved in the source.\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Kiss of death\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Only damaged by magical weapons\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 30%\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/400 + 6 per hit point\n\nThese shy creatures live in fresh water and have a dragon’s head, two forelegs, and a giant carp’s body and tail. They cannot fly, polymorph, or turn invisible. They have no breath weapon and can breathe only water, though they may emerge awkwardly onto land for up to one hour. When determining age, all age levels of 5 or above are reduced to adult. There are no older yu lung; at 101 years they metamorphose into another type of oriental dragon, with equal chance of each type. Of the oriental dragons, only yu lung can be subdued.",
