    "npc_notes": "DRAGONFISH\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/65 + 2 per hit point\n\nDragonfish are mottled brown flatfish about 2 feet long, lurking on the bottoms of shallow freshwater pools and slow-moving streams or rivers. They are very hard to spot, only a 15% chance even if searchers know what they are looking for, because they blend so well with the bottom. They have a fringe of horny spines tipped with highly toxic poison; the saving throw is at -1. These spines snap off in any victim who steps on them or puts a hand on them, and they are strong enough to penetrate leather boots. In melee dragonfish bite for 1-6 hit points of damage. The spines themselves inflict no ordinary damage apart from the poison effect.",
