    "npc_notes": "DUNE STALKER\n\nNOTE: The OCR columns on this page were inconsistent. The stat line below is the final corrected dune stalker stat line used in the conversation, while the descriptive text on the page clearly belongs to dune stalker but conflicts with the stat box from the page layout.\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 6\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 5-7\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4/2-16\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (18' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n5 HD: III/130 + 5 per hit point\n6 HD: IV/225 + 6 per hit point\n7 HD: V/350 + 8 per hit point\n\nA vile, naked human-like creature, bony and long-fingered with clawed toes, the dune stalker roams deserts in service to high-level evil magicians. It attacks only good characters. It is a faultless tracker, as the invisible stalker once set on a mission. Its usual attack is sonic vibration at 60 feet for 2-12 damage with no saving throw. In close contact it can deliver the kiss of death by placing its lips on exposed skin; the victim must save versus spells or die instantly. A successful save negates the effect. Dune stalkers can only be harmed by magical weapons.",
