    "npc_notes": "CRYONAX, PRINCE OF EVIL COLD CREATURES\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -6\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 90 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 55%\nTREASURE TYPE: H, V, X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 5-20/5-20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Cold damage; spells\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 75%\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: L (15' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 200\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: X/28,000\n\nCryonax lives in a huge castle of ice, quartz, and glass, situated at the juncture of the planes of Air and Water and drawing power from the Negative Material Plane. He appears as a 15' tall yeti with tentacles covered with suction cups in place of arms. He continually radiates 1-6 points of cold damage to all within 15'; creatures resistant to cold take half damage, but there is no save. He attacks as a 20 hit dice monster with two tentacles, each inflicting 5-20 hit points of damage. In addition, the victim must save versus paralysis or be frozen in place for 3-12 full turns. Cryonax can only be damaged by +2 or better weapons. There is a cumulative 10% chance that any particular weapon hitting him will shatter; if it breaks, the damage from that hit is negated. Once per day he may summon one of the following groups: 1-4 white dragons, 1-4 frost giants, or 1-6 yeti. Three times per day he may produce a triple-strength wall of ice, hold person, and cast an ice storm of 4-40 points. Once per day he may unleash a 15-dice blast of cold. Fire attacks against Cryonax are at +2 hit probability and do an additional point of damage per attack die. Cold attacks add to his hit points in an amount equal to the intended damage, up to but not beyond his original 90 hit points. He is completely immune to poison and cannot be turned to stone.",
