    "npc_notes": "YAN-C-BIN, PRINCE OF EVIL AERIAL CREATURES\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: -6\nMOVE: 48\"\nHIT DICE: 85 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 75%\nTREASURE TYPE: U, Z\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-20/2-20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spells, whirlwind, monk's abilities\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 90%\nINTELLIGENCE: Genius\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: L (10' diameter)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 220\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: X/25,650\n\nYan-C-Bin is naturally invisible, causing only a slight disturbance in the air as he flies. He has no definite shape, though he is about 10 feet in diameter. He attacks as a 19 hit dice monster twice each round for 2-20 hit points per attack, and has the same chance as an 8th level monk to stun or kill outright. Only +2 or better weapons can harm him. For aerial combat he is manoeuvrability class A. As prince of evil aerial creatures, he may summon once per day 1-3 air elementals, 1-4 cloud giants, 1-4 invisible stalkers, or 1-3 wind walkers. Lightning is ineffective against him. Fire attacks are at +1 to hit per four levels of the attacker. He cannot be harmed by objects cast into the air and is immune to petrifaction. He can form a whirlwind, a truncated reverse cone 2\" across at the bottom, 6\" across at the top, and 16\" high. If full height cannot be reached, the whirlwind is half strength. A full-strength whirlwind kills all creatures under 3 hit dice and inflicts 4-32 hit points on all non-aerial creatures not killed outright; half strength inflicts 2-16. He can maintain this form for 2-5 rounds. Forming or dismissing the whirlwind takes one full round. He lives in a great airy palace on the Elemental Plane of Air.",
