    "npc_notes": "DROW, DARK ELF\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare (at best)\nNO. APPEARING: 5-50\nARMOR CLASS: 4 (and better)\nMOVE: 12\" (females 15\")\nHIT DICE: 2 (and better)\n% IN LAIR: 0\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals: N(x5), Q(x2)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 or 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 50% (and better); all saving throws at +2\nINTELLIGENCE: Mean: highly intelligent\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M (5' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Unknown\nAttack/Defense Modes: Unknown\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II and up / Variable\n\nThe drow are the exiled dark elves who withdrew beneath the earth after ancient wars with the other elven peoples. They dwell in vast underground realms and retain bitter hatred for elves and faeries of the surface. All drow are at least 2nd level fighters, with males reaching as high as 7th level as fighters and 12th as magic-users, while females may reach 9th level as fighters and very high clerical power. They wear fine black mesh armour of adamantite alloy, typically equivalent to +1 chainmail or better, and often carry bucklers, daggers, short swords, crossbows with sleep-poisoned darts, maces, or poisoned javelins. They move silently, possess superior infravision, save at +2 against magic, and gain additional magic resistance by level. All can use dancing lights, faerie fire, and darkness once per day. Those above 4th level also use detect magic, know alignment, and levitate once daily. Females additionally may use clairvoyance, detect lie, suggestion, and dispel magic once per day. They dislike bright light and suffer penalties in strong illumination, often withdrawing if exposed to it. Drow also use a sophisticated silent sign language and communicate by posture and expression. Their special arms and armour decay in sunlight and eventually become ordinary items even if shielded from it.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_drow_dark_elf"
  },
