    "npc_notes": "ENVELOPER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 3, 5, 7, etc.\n% IN LAIR: 85%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8/1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Variable\nINTELLIGENCE: Variable\nALIGNMENT: Variable\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Variable\nAttack/Defense Modes: Variable\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III and up / Variable\n\nThe enveloper is a mass of malleable flesh, usually a rough cylinder 8 feet high and 3 feet in circumference. It can reshape itself to form up to five appendages, and when humans or near-humans are present it adopts an approximate humanoid form. In its base state it is of animal intelligence, neutral alignment, standard magic resistance, and no psionics. It attacks with two fists for 1-8 hit points each. If it kills a victim, it immediately falls upon and consumes the body in one melee round, leaving gear behind. After three more rounds it gains that victim’s abilities, knowledge, experience, speech, and memorized spells. It also gains 1-3 hit points per hit die of the victim. As it consumes more victims, it accumulates more powers; conflicting traits are discarded randomly until conflict is removed. It tends toward the alignment of its most recently consumed victim. As it ages, it gains hit dice in increments of 2; in theory there is no upper limit.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_enveloper"
  },
