    "npc_notes": "ETTERCAP\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-2\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-3/1-3/1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Traps — see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/165 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe ettercap is a roughly man-sized biped with very long arms, a protruding pot belly, short legs, hairy skin, clawed hands, and two poisonous fangs projecting beside the mouth. It is cruel, cunning, and treacherous. It attacks with two claws and a poisonous bite. Silk glands near the anus secrete a thin but extremely tough silvery cord that it uses to make lariats, nets, garottes, tripwires, and other traps. Each ettercap has its own preferences, but all will prepare ambushes and traps if they have time. Ettercaps get along well with all kinds of spiders.",
