    "npc_notes": "EYE KILLER\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4, or 2-8\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Death stare\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/150 + 4 per hit point\n\nAt birth, the eye killer is limbless and almost spherical; later it develops a bat-like upper torso on the body of a large snake. Its stunted wings cannot support flight. The upper body is dark grey-green, the lower medium green flecked with dull yellow, and its eyes are huge and apparently lidless. It hates daylight and bright flame, dwelling underground. Its behavior depends on illumination. Against infravision-only or dimly lit foes it attacks with its coils, inflicting 1-6 points and continuing to crush automatically each round after a successful hit. Against torch or lantern bearers, it may use its death stare out to 50 feet, gathering and amplifying incoming light into a lethal beam. The beam strikes as though against AC 10; the victim must save versus death ray or die instantly. A successful save still results in 3-18 hit points of damage. The stare can be reflected, though that only lets the eye killer amplify and redirect it again. It can use the death stare only once per day. If intense light comes too close, it tries to flee.",
