    "npc_notes": "EYE OF FEAR AND FLAME\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: See below\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: See below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2,850 + 16 per hit point\n\nThe eye of fear and flame is a hooded, man-sized figure whose face is always hidden by blackness within the hood. It stalks the underworld seeking lawful or lawful-neutral individuals and parties, commanding them to perform evil deeds in the proper alignment language. If attacked, or if its commands are disobeyed, it casts back the hood to reveal a bare skull with a red jewel in one eye socket and a black jewel in the other. The red gem produces a 12-dice fireball once every three melee rounds, while the black gem functions as a fear wand every round. The gems are worth 1,000-2,000 gp each, but lose their powers when removed or when the creature dies. If melee goes badly, the creature can transfer to the Ethereal Plane, taking two rounds to do so, and flee. It has no hand-to-hand attack. If blindness or power word, blind is cast on it, the spell is reflected back at the caster at full strength. It is said there are only about twenty of these beings.",
