    "npc_notes": "FIREDRAKE\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-8\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 80%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapon\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (4' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/125 + 4 per hit point\n\nFound only in rocky places, the firedrake is a small dragonet resembling a miniature red dragon. If disturbed, even peacefully, there is a 50% chance it attacks. It does not use its claws in combat, but bites for 2-8 hit points. It can also breathe a cone of fire 60 feet long and 10 feet across at the base, up to five times daily, inflicting 2-16 damage, save for half. Its blood burns fiercely in air and is the source of the breath weapon. If kept in a container under water, it remains inert. Swords dipped in the blood become flaming swords for 3-6 melee rounds, though there is a cumulative 2% chance each blow that the weapon breaks. Firedrakes have short lifespans compared to dragons and do not use dragon age-based hit point scaling. For aerial combat they are manoeuvrability class C.",
