    "npc_notes": "FIRENEWT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 10-100\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 2+2\n% IN LAIR: 75%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals K, M; in lair F\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breathe fire\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nNormal: III/90 + 3 per hit point\nElite: III/125 + 4 per hit point\nPriest: IV/190 + 4 per hit point\nOverlord: IV/165 + 5 per hit point\n\nFirenewts, also called salamen, are distant relatives of lizard men who live in hot, dry, rocky, volcanic, or sulphurous places. Warriors usually wear chainmail and carry pike and sword, sword alone, pike and hand axe, or battle axe. For every ten warriors there is one elite warrior of 3+3 hit dice and AC 3. For every thirty there is, in addition, one priest of 3+3 hit dice and AC 5 with druidic spell powers once per day each: animal friendship, faerie fire, predict weather, produce flame, heat metal, and pyrotechnics. Elite warriors carry battle axes; priests use maces. Many above-ground firenewts, especially elites and all priests, ride giant striders. All firenewts have a limited breath weapon usable once per turn against a foe within 5 feet directly ahead, for 1-6 fire damage, save for half. They resist fire strongly, saving at +3 and reducing damage by 1 point per die, but are especially vulnerable to cold, saving at -3 and taking +1 per die. They are cruel marauders who delight in torturing and roasting victims alive. In a lair there are many females, young, and eggs, with a guarded hatching ground watched by 1-3 young fire lizards. The lair is ruled by an overlord of 4+4 hit dice and AC 3 with four elite guards. Typical coloration is mottled sepia, darkest along the spine and paling toward the belly, with deep crimson eyes.",
