    "npc_notes": "FIRETOAD\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 4+1\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Variable\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/165 + 5 per hit point\n\nA firetoad is a large red toad about 4 feet high, covered with warty purple excrescences. It shuns water and inhabits dry places above or below ground. Throwing liquid, even ordinary water, at it causes it to retreat, but while retreating it concentrates two fireball attacks in that same melee round on the one who did so. Its only attack is to breathe small fireballs with 30' range and a 5' blast radius, usable at will. The fireball does damage equal to the number of hit points the firetoad has remaining, with a normal saving throw for half damage. It rarely attacks, only a 20% chance, unless threatened, molested, or defending its treasure.",
