    "npc_notes": "FLIND\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-24\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2+3\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: A\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6 or 1-4; see below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Disarming; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: M (6½' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nNormal: II/35 + 3 per hit point\nLeader: III/60 + 4 per hit point\n\nFlinds are relatives of the gnolls, powerful 6½-foot humanoids that always attack at +1 to hit because of their strength. Most of their characteristics and behaviour resemble those of gnolls, who regard flinds as higher beings. Large groups of gnolls are sometimes led by one or more flinds. A normal flind usually attacks with a club doing 1-6 hit points of damage. Twenty-five percent of those encountered instead carry chain-linked iron bars called flindbars, which they wield so rapidly that they gain two attacks per round. If either attack hits, the victim takes 1-4 hit points of damage and must save as against wands or his weapon becomes entangled and he is disarmed. The flindbar can be used by any character with both strength and dexterity of 13 or better, provided he has practiced with it and selected it as a weapon proficiency. One leader appears for every 15 flinds; such leaders are 3+3 hit dice, have 17 strength and high intelligence, and are treated as having 18 charisma by gnolls. Leader-types always use the flindbar. Flinds speak the same tongues as gnolls and are on friendly terms with orcs, hobgoblins, bugbears, and ogres, but they dislike trolls and will not cooperate with them.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_flind"
  },
