    "npc_notes": "FORLARREN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 8\"\nHIT DICE: 3\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Heat metal; see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/90 + 3 per hit point\n\nThese creatures are descendants of the offspring of a good nymph and the greater devil who enslaved her. They wander alone, seeking vengeance on good and evil alike, hating their own existence in a kind of limbo. They attack characters on sight, using their fists like cudgels for 1-4 points of damage each. A forlarren can also use heat metal once per day by contact, and uses this on the first opponent in metal armour it meets in melee. For the purpose of this attack, all armour classes are treated as AC 10. If the attack hits, the victim suffers 3-18 hit points of damage per round if wearing plate mail, or 2-16 per round if wearing lighter metal armour, including magical metal armour. Once contact is made, it is maintained until either the forlarren or the victim dies. A successful saving throw versus dragon breath halves the damage. Once it kills a character, however, the ambivalent nature of the forlarren is revealed: it becomes remorseful and offers its services and powers to any survivors. After a variable period, the dominant evil half resumes control and it leaves the party it had aided. Thereafter it again attacks on sight, including that same party if it meets them later. As an approximation, this period of friendship lasts 1-6 days, though there is a 10% chance it lasts only 13-24 hours or as long as 7-10 days. It can speak a rudimentary form of the common tongue.",
