    "npc_notes": "GALLTRIT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 3\"/13\"\nHIT DICE: 2 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: 1-3 gems\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-2\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Blood drain; anticoagulant; anaesthesia\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: S (1' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/32\n\nThe galltrit is a small winged gremlin with a nasty disposition. It is stone-grey, and its size and coloration make it difficult to detect: humans and most demi-humans notice it only on 1 chance in 8, elves on 1 chance in 6. Galltrits are found in places containing dung, carrion, or offal. They attack when disturbed, usually by flying onto a victim, preferably unnoticed, and biting for 1-2 hit points of damage while locking their teeth into the skin. If a galltrit gains surprise before attacking, its initial bite is at +3 to hit. In aerial combat it is manoeuvrability class B. Its saliva has an anaesthetic effect, deadening the local nerves and skin for a full turn, during which it sucks blood at the rate of 1 hit point of damage per melee round. Every four melee rounds the anticoagulant in the saliva reduces the victim’s constitution by 1 point for as many days as the number of hit points drained. A galltrit rarely remains attached for more than one full turn even if unnoticed, and flees as soon as its presence is detected. If the initial attack was not noticed, the victim will not become aware of the creature afterward because of the anaesthesia, though later he will sense blood loss and weakening constitution. If a victim loses 3 constitution points, he collapses and the galltrit’s presence is almost certainly revealed. Recovery from collapse takes two full turns, while the lost constitution returns after 12 days.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_galltrit"
  },
