    "npc_notes": "GARBUG\n\nBLACK GARBUG\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 2+2\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1 and 6\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 and special\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (9' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/145 + 3 per hit point\n\nVIOLET GARBUG\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 6\"/9\"\nHIT DICE: 3+1\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 and 6\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6/1-6 and special\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (9' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/190 + 4 per hit point\n\nBoth types of garbug resemble wasp-bodied lobsters. They can fly clumsily on flimsy wings, but normally move on six legs. Six tentacles surround the mouth, each 2' long and coated with a paralysing secretion; a victim struck must save versus paralysis or the effect takes hold. In melee, both types attack with their tentacles as well as their special natural weapons. The tentacles themselves do no hit point damage, only delivering the paralysing effect. For aerial combat, both types are manoeuvrability class D. The black garbug is a uniform glossy black. In addition to its tentacles, it has a proboscis it uses within 5', inflicting 1-4 hit points of damage, and this may be delivered in the same round as the tentacle attacks. The violet garbug lacks the attacking proboscis, but instead attacks with two large pincers positioned like those of a lobster, each doing 1-6 hit points of damage. The violet garbug is a striking uniform violet except for its deep yellow claws.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_garbug"
  },
