    "npc_notes": "FOG GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4 (rarely 1-6)\nARMOR CLASS: 1\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 14\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 4-24\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Hurling rocks for 2-20 points of damage\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to high\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (good 50%, evil 50%)\nSIZE: L (18' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VIII/3,950 + 18 per hit point\n\nFog giants are cousins to the cloud giants, and if as many as 6 fog giants are encountered, they will always be accompanied by a cloud giant. They have keen hearing and a highly developed sense of smell, and so are surprised only on a 1 on d6. They can also blend into fog, gaining surprise on opponents 80% of the time. They inhabit foggy places such as marshes, swamps, dense forests, and sea coasts. Fog giants have milk-white skin, silvery-white hair, and black penetrating eyes. They love massive ornate swords and prefer armour made from white dragon hide studded with silver. In melee they fight either with those swords or with their fists, in either case inflicting 4-24 hit points of damage. Their armour, if worn, does not affect their AC, which is always treated as 1. Like cloud giants they can hurl rocks from 1\" to 24\", doing 2-20 hit points of damage, and have a 45% chance of catching similar missiles. They speak their alignment language and their own dialect of giant, which is unintelligible to other giants except cloud giants.",
