    "npc_notes": "GIANT, MOUNTAIN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-4\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 12\n% IN LAIR: 90%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 4-40\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Hurling rocks for 2-16 points of damage\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: L (14' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2,850 + 16 per hit point\n\nMountain giants are rarely encountered away from their lair, which is a huge cave carved into the heart of a rocky mountain. In addition to their normal speech, all can speak the ogre language. Like hill giants, they hurl rocks from 1\" to 20\", inflicting 2-16 hit points of damage, and can catch similar missiles 30% of the time. In melee they strike with huge clubs for 4-40 hit points of damage. A mountain giant can summon and control other monsters, usually 6-15 ogres, sometimes 4-9 trolls, or even 1-4 hill giants. If encountered in its lair, there is a 75% chance that these creatures are present as servants and guards. Giantesses and young are rarely found; if 4 mountain giants are met in their lair, there will also be one female and one young giant, each with hit dice of 8+1-2 and one attack for 2-16 hit points. Otherwise all encountered are adult males. Mountain giants have light tan to light reddish-brown skin and dress in rough hides or skins, like hill giants.",
