    "npc_notes": "STRIDER, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8/1-10\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Fireball\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard, but +2 bonus on saving rolls and immune to magical fire\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: L (6-7' tall at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/73 + 2 per hit point\n\nThese large, flightless, featherless birds resemble heavy ostriches. Beside each of their two dull red glowing eyes is a small duct from which the beast can project a small fireball which does 1-6 hit points of damage. Each giant strider can project two such fireballs per hour, one from each duct, with the accuracy of a +4 longbow, a maximum range of 50', and a burst radius of 10'. In addition, it can bite to its front or flank for 1-8 hit points, or kick to its rear for 1-10 hit points. It cannot coordinate both attacks in the same melee round, and will generally attack in the direction from which it was last struck. Giant striders are immune to fire, magical or otherwise, and their bodies have adapted to draw sustenance from warmth. As a result they are most at home in deserts and volcanic regions. Intense heat, flames, and fireballs act as a cure light wounds spell on them once every three rounds. Conversely, cold spells do an additional 2-7 hit points of damage, and water, if drunk, is poison to them. Even cold liquid thrown over the body causes damage, normally 1-2 hit points depending on circumstances. Giant striders are used as steeds by fire newts. They are generally fearless and never check morale.",
