    "npc_notes": "GIBBERLING\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 40–400\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: D\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: S (4'–5' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/14 + 1 per hit point\n\nPale, hunched, naked humanoids with short legs and long arms, gibberlings are usually found in desolate woods or in dark underground caverns. The subterranean variety loathe bright light and are particularly afraid of fire. Gibberlings attack in great numbers, uttering ghastly howls and insane chattering noises which cause even the boldest hirelings to check morale each round, though player characters are not affected. They fight with normal swords and gain +1 to hit with them. They always fight to the death, relying on sheer numbers to overwhelm almost any creature entering their territory. Although they clearly possess some primitive means of communication, no discernible language has yet been identified, and no true leader-types have apparently been found.",
