    },
    "npc_notes": "GITHYANKI\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–4\nARMOR CLASS: Variable\nMOVE: Variable\nHIT DICE: Variable (upper limit of 11)\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals N; lair A, Z (x2)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Variable (as human)\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional or genius\nALIGNMENT: Variable but always evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 150–250\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all but J\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV and up / Variable\n\nThe githyanki are descendants of the evil humans once enslaved by mind flayers, later freed after a long rebellion under the leadership of Gith. They now dwell on the Astral Plane but project themselves to the Prime Material Plane, establishing temporary underground refuges from which they raid humans and mind flayers alike. They advance as fighters, magic-users, or fighter/magic-users, and also possess a knight class, but have never been known to progress beyond 11th level. They are ruled by a lich-queen of immense magical power.\n\nThey use armour and weapons as men do, though the ornateness of their design is often notable. On war expeditions they wear +4 splint mail but do not carry shields. Fighters and fighter/magic-users of 6th level and above often carry +1 two-handed swords; fighters of 7th level and above commonly carry +2 or +3 longswords; knights of 7th level and above always have silver swords, and supreme leaders wield special silver swords that are +5, fully vorpal, and affect mind-barred victims. These silver swords are non-aligned, intelligent, and fiercely guarded; if a special silver sword is lost, a powerful recovery party is formed at once.\n\nOutside their Prime Material Plane lairs, githyanki are rarely encountered in parties larger than four. A typical small party consists of two trainees of any of the three classes, one fighter of 4th–6th level, and a fighter/magic-user leader of 7th/6th level. Rarely, a special mission party will instead be led by an 8th-level knight. A lair contains 21–30 githyanki with a structured mix of supreme leader, captains, knight, warlocks, sergeants, gish, and lower-level members. Large purposeful parties are stronger and may be led by the supreme leader of the lair.\n\nGithyanki have normal human chances for magic item distribution other than swords. A Prime Material Plane lair will contain 5–10 magical items selected as appropriate to the mission. Small parties usually have one magical item; larger parties may have 1–10. They also maintain a pact with red dragons, which serve as steeds for them on the Prime Material Plane in exchange for food, shelter, and treasure. On the Astral Plane, githyanki move at 96\".",
    "id": "fiend_folio_githyanki"
  },
