    "npc_notes": "GITHZERAI\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–4\nARMOR CLASS: Variable\nMOVE: Variable\nHIT DICE: Variable (upper limit of 9)\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: A\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Variable (as human)\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 50%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: 121–250\nAttack/Defense Modes: All/all\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II and up / Variable\n\nThe githzerai are inhabitants of Limbo and are in constant vicious warfare with the githyanki, though both races descended from the same people freed from mind flayer bondage. They are generally somewhat weaker than the githyanki, but their magic resistance helps offset this. They share similar class limits, though some specialize as monks and they have no anti-paladin counterpart. They use silver swords and other weapons much as the githyanki do, but have not developed the special silver swords of their enemies.\n\nTheir political organization is similar to that of the githyanki, and they are ruled by an undying wizard-king said to be a 16th/23rd level fighter/magic-user who prevents progression beyond 9th level. All githzerai possess astral projection, mind bar, probability travel, and energy control at 6th-level mastery, and have all psionic attack and defense modes. Their parties, lairs, and strongholds follow the distributions given in the source text. They have normal human chances for magic items other than swords, and a lair contains 2–16 magical items.",
