    "npc_notes": "GOLDBUG\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–20\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 1\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/45 + 1 per hit point\n\nThe goldbug is a beetle with a flattened circular body and a golden shell, the exact size and shape of a gold piece. It is very sluggish and spends most of its time asleep, often choosing a pile of gold coins as its bed. Only very close examination distinguishes it from the coins it rests upon. Although it has no treasure of its own, it habitually inhabits the treasure of others. When disturbed it inflicts a poisonous bite like that of a large spider, dealing 1–4 hit points of damage, and the victim must save versus poison or die.",
