    "npc_notes": "GORBEL\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1–20\nARMOR CLASS: 3 (10 — see below)\nMOVE: 18\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4 or 1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral with chaotic tendencies\nSIZE: S (3' diameter)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/32 + 2 per hit point\n\nA gorbel appears as a red globe of thin rubbery material about 3 feet in diameter, with a tiny mouth, six tiny eyes on short retractable stalks around the upper hemisphere, and two clawed legs with which it moves at remarkable speed. When attacking, it tries to attach itself to a victim’s back with its claws. A successful initial hit means it has done so, inflicting 1–4 hit points of damage. Thereafter it cannot be detached until dead and it automatically hits the victim each round for 1–6 points of clawing damage. It initially attacks as a creature of 2 hit dice.\n\nA hit with a blunt weapon does no harm to a gorbel, but a hit with a pointed or edged weapon causes it to burst apart, killing it and inflicting 1–4 hit points of blast damage on anyone within 5 feet. When attached to a victim it loses its dexterity bonus and its AC becomes 10. Gorbels are mischievous, fickle, and irritable creatures.",
