    "npc_notes": "GORILLA BEAR\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 2–7\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–8/1–8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Hugs for 2–8 hit points of damage\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (9' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/85 + 4 per hit point\n\nThese monsters have the head, body, and legs of a gorilla with the sharp teeth and powerful arms of a bear. They have the aggressive disposition of the grizzly bear and the carnivorous tendencies of the cave bear. Their hearing, smell, and eyesight are excellent, so they are rarely surprised, only a 15% chance. Their dexterity is also high, accounting for their improved AC.\n\nA gorilla bear attacks with its two paws, and a paw hit scored with an 18 or better indicates that the beast also hugs for additional damage. If an 18 is insufficient to hit, the hug occurs only on a 19, or on a 20 if that too is insufficient; a natural 20 always means a hug. Unlike a normal bear, the gorilla bear does not continue fighting after its hit points are reduced below zero.",
