    "npc_notes": "GRELL\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 11\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 10 × 1–4 / 1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to lightning\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: [UNRESOLVED]\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/840 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe grell is a dreadful creature with a body like a giant exposed brain about 5 feet in diameter and a frontal beak, below which trail ten 6-foot tentacles. It flies by levitation, with small inflections of the tentacles controlling horizontal movement, and is manoeuvrability class D. Grell are usually found underground, though they are occasionally seen in ruined or abandoned buildings. They are particularly dangerous and vicious, dropping upon victims from above whenever possible.\n\nAll ten tentacles are brought to bear on a single victim. Each inflicts 1–4 hit points of damage and carries small spines that can inject venom; this paralyses the victim unless a saving throw versus paralysis is made at +4. If any one tentacle succeeds in paralysing a victim, then in each melee round thereafter two tentacles remain anchored while the other eight lash for 1–4 hit points each and the beak rends for 1–6 hit points. None of these later attacks requires a to hit roll.\n\nAny hit on a tentacle renders it inoperative, though it regenerates in 1–2 days if the creature survives, and tentacle damage does not reduce the grell’s hit points. Only hits on the body damage the creature in the normal way. The body and tentacles are all AC 4. Grell are immune to lightning but otherwise have standard resistance to normal and magical attacks. The body is drab olive streaked with white, and the tentacles are pale olive-green.",
