    "npc_notes": "GRIMLOCK\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 20–200\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals K, L, M; in lair B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Save as 6th level fighter (and see below)\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: [UNRESOLVED]\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nWarriors: II/28 + 2 per hit point\nLeaders: II/50 + 3 per hit point\nChampions: III/85 + 4 per hit point\n\nThese fierce subterranean humanoid warriors dwell in deep caverns and emerge only in raiding parties at night to butcher and devour humans. Their eyes are blank and sightless, but they possess highly developed hearing and smell, giving them effective “vision” within 20 feet. They are immune to spells affecting the visual nerves, such as phantasmal force, darkness, invisibility, and mirror image. Spells such as audible glamer partially “blind” them, reducing this range to 10 feet and their hit probability by 2; snuff and similar inhaled irritants have the same effect.\n\nFor every 10 grimlocks encountered there is one leader of 3 hit dice and AC 4, and for every 40 there is also a champion of 4 hit dice and AC 3. In a lair there are females equal to an additional 80% of the males, each with 1 hit die and AC 6, and young equal to an additional 100% of the males, each with 1 hit point, AC 5, and noncombatant. Grimlocks rarely consort with others, though there is a 10% chance they allow medusae to share their lair and a 2% chance that a wandering group is accompanied by 1–2 mind flayers. They are therefore especially hated by githyanki.\n\nGrimlocks prefer edged blood-letting weapons, though they can fight bare-handed for 1–6 hit points. Ninety percent are armed, with the weapon distribution given in the original text. Leaders and champions wield battle-axes or two-handed swords. If encountered in rocky terrain, they can blend with the surroundings while motionless and cannot be detected except by detect invisibility unless physically bumped into. All grimlocks, whether warrior, leader, or champion, make all saving throws as if they were 6th level fighters. They are powerfully built humanoids with thick scaly grey skin, dark rags, long black unkempt hair, and particularly sharp white teeth.",
