    "npc_notes": "GRYPH\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–6\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 21\"\nHIT DICE: 2–4\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2–12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n2 HD: II/28 + 2 per hit point\n3 HD: II/50 + 3 per hit point\n4 HD: III/85 + 4 per hit point\n\nThe gryph is a bird with multiple legs, usually four, though specimens with six or even eight have been seen. It is about the size of an eagle and has a razor-sharp beak with powerful jaws. Its bite inflicts 2–12 hit points of damage, and it normally attacks at high speed from high in the shadows of an underground cavern. For aerial combat it is manoeuvrability class B.\n\nIf three or more are encountered, one will be female, and there is a 35% chance that she will be ready to lay eggs. If such a female attacks, she will attempt to grapple the victim with her legs and, if a hit is scored, inject her small eggs into the bloodstream. In such an attack the beak is not used and the victim takes no normal damage, the eggs being injected through a thin tube projecting from the bird’s abdomen.\n\n[ENTRY INCOMPLETE: the rest of the special attack description continues beyond the available page.]",
