    "npc_notes": "GUARDIAN DAEMON\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–3\nARMOR CLASS: 1\nMOVE: 9\" (but see below)\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6/1–12/1–12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: Variable\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,275 + 10 per hit point\n\nThese daemons vary in size and form, examples having resembled type II or type IV demons, large bears, and wild cats. They are summoned by evil high priests to guard treasure and are constrained never to leave the treasure they guard unless released by the summoner, though their melee movement is 9\". Despite variation in form, they always share certain traits: immunity to charm, hold, sleep, polymorph, and fear; immunity to non-magical weapons and magical weapons of less than +2; ability to speak and understand all languages; and the ability to breathe fire in a cone 30' long with a 10' base diameter for 5–30 hit points of damage, save for half.\n\nIn melee they attack with a bite for 1–6 hit points and two claws for 1–12 hit points each, since they cannot use their breath weapon on a target within 10'. Their summoning usually, 80% of the time, leaves them invulnerable to one additional attack form such as fire or swords. Guardian daemons have no treasure of their own on the Prime Material Plane and always guard the treasure of their summoner; that treasure will usually include at least one clerical scroll or clerical magical device.",
