    },
    "npc_notes": "GUARDIAN FAMILIAR\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 1 (9 lives)\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6/1–4/1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Any (see below)\nSIZE: S (see below)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,800 + 12 per hit point\n\nThe guardian familiar takes the form of a small black cat set to guard the treasure of a high-level wizard, and its alignment is always the same as that of its summoner. It never leaves its place atop the treasure or chest, and attacks only if it is attacked or if attempts are made to get at the treasure. It attacks with two raking claws for 1–4 hit points each and a bite for 1–6. During its attack it grows progressively larger, eventually resembling a bobcat, and reverts to normal size if melee is suspended.\n\nIts magic resistance varies with the level of its master: 50% for a 10th-level magic-user, varying by 5% per level in either direction, so 30% at 6th level and 75% at 15th level. Magic-users of 4th level or lower cannot secure one. The guardian familiar has nine lives. Each time it is slain, up to the ninth time, it is instantly reborn stronger than before: add 1 hit die, reroll hit points, add 2\" movement, improve AC by 1, and add 1 point of damage to each attack. This can be stopped by disintegrate, flesh to stone, temporal stasis, wish, or alter reality, if its magic resistance is overcome. Holy word or unholy word banishes it back to its plane of origin. If attackers break off melee, it does not pursue but simply returns to its post. If slain a ninth time, it remains dead. It is not the same as a normal familiar from find familiar.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_guardian_familiar"
  },
