    "npc_notes": "HELLCAT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 7+2\n% IN LAIR: 30%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2–5/2–5/2–12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Special invisibility and see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20% and immune to charm, sleep, and similar spells\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/1,000 + 10 per hit point\n\nHellcats are the associates and familiars of devils and are usually found on their native levels of Hell. They sometimes journey to the Prime Material Plane to serve powerful lawful evil characters. The hellcat is invisible in the presence of any light source, but in darkness can be seen as a faintly glowing, wraith-like outline with blazing crimson eyes, in the form of a domestic cat the size of a tiger.\n\nIt can only be harmed by magical weapons, and even then magical damage bonuses do not apply. It has 20% magic resistance and is completely immune to mind-controlling spells such as charm, hold, sleep, and suggestion. It attacks with two claws for 2–6 hit points each and a bite for 2–12 hit points. In return for service, it demands one living human victim per week as a meal; if the master fails to provide this, the master becomes the victim. It serves only intelligent lawful evil creatures. It may transfer allegiance to a more powerful lawful evil master if accepted, and after a year and a day on the Prime Material Plane it must return to Hell. If encountered by a party with no lawful evil member, it either flees from evil parties or attacks wholly non-evil ones. It communicates telepathically with its chosen master at 9\" range.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_hellcat"
  },
