    "npc_notes": "HOAR FOX\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–6\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapon\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (4' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2 per hit point\n\nHoar foxes inhabit cold regions and are usually encountered in small packs. They are rarely aggressive unless threatened, only a 10% chance, but their beautiful silver-grey pelts are highly valued, bringing 100 gp if undamaged, so adventurers often threaten them. They bite for 1–6 hit points, but their main weapon is a narrow cone of cold with 30' range, wide enough for only one victim, doing 2–12 hit points of damage, save for half. For purposes of the breath attack, the target’s AC is treated as 10, though dexterity modifiers still apply. Hoar foxes are immune to cold attacks but take double damage from fire, and fire naturally ruins the pelt.",
