    "npc_notes": "HOOK HORROR\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2–12\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: P\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–8/1–8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (9' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/190 + 5 per hit point\n\nHook horrors are large powerful bipeds with vulture-like heads and a hard plated mottled-grey exoskeleton. They inhabit deep underground corridors and chambers. Though their vision is very poor, their hearing is extremely acute and there is only a 10% chance of surprising one. Their arms end in sharp hook-like talons, each inflicting 1–8 hit points of damage in melee. They cannot speak, but communicate with others of their kind by making eerie clacking noises with the exoskeleton, sounds which can be alarming as they echo through dungeon corridors.",
