    "npc_notes": "HORNET, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2 in flight, 4 when settled\nMOVE: 24\"\nHIT DICE: 5\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison; incapacitation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/165 + 5 per hit point\n\nThis very aggressive creature has a body 5' long and wingspan of 10' or more. It attacks on sight with a vicious sting that inflicts 1–4 hit points of damage, 5–30 poison damage if the victim fails a save, and incapacitation for 2–12 hours if a separate save is failed. One saving throw is rolled against poison and another against incapacitation. Giant hornets naturally inhabit coniferous forests, though they are occasionally encountered underground.\n\nSmoke and flame reduce the hornet’s effectiveness, causing it to strike at -2 and -4 respectively. Fortunately, its buzz is loud and can be heard 150' away in dungeon corridors, halved for each intervening door up to three doors. For aerial combat it is manoeuvrability class B.",
