    "npc_notes": "HOUND OF ILL OMEN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: Not applicable\nMOVE: Not applicable\nHIT DICE: Not applicable\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Special\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M (5' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: Not applicable\n\nOne of the legendary beasts whose appearance portends death, the hound of ill omen appears as a dark shadowy wolfhound 5' tall at the shoulder. It appears instantaneously and remains visible only for a few seconds, and even then only to one member of an adventuring party. Because of its brief appearance and shadowy form, it cannot be harmed in any way, and rumor claims there is only one of these creatures in existence.\n\nThe one who sees it hears a booming howl before it vanishes. There is no saving throw against the effect of the howl, though remove curse cast within one turn halves the effect. The howl curses the victim so that the next 1–10 wounds suffered do quadruple damage; if remove curse has been cast, only the next 1–5 wounds do so. Until the required number of wounds has been taken, no healing, such as cure wounds, has any effect. It is said the hound appears only if a character has seriously offended his deity, such as by a flagrant act out of alignment.",
