    },
    "npc_notes": "IMORPH\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare (at best)\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 5 (see below)\nMOVE: 6\" (see below)\nHIT DICE: 5 (see below)\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4/1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/130 + 5 per hit point\n\nThe natural form of the imorph is a grey-green lumpy cylinder about 4' high and 1' in average diameter. A short leg with a suction cup trails behind the main body, and other suction cups under the body permit a jerky movement. Two 5' tentacles emerge from the top, but there are no visible eyes, ears, or similar features. The whole creature is a constantly changing mass of rubbery dough-like substance the colour of bilious human flesh.\n\nIt normally does not attack unless threatened, and then strikes with its tentacles for 1–4 hit points each. In melee it shows a startling power of imorphism. At the beginning of each melee round after the first, it changes hit dice and armour class by 1 point each toward those of its opponent, while gradually changing shape to resemble that opponent. When its hit dice, AC, and appearance match, it instantly alters its attack and movement to fit the subject physically. It copies only physical appearance, not true abilities; it still strikes as two tentacles for 1–4 each, though those tentacles may look like armed limbs. Its hit points remain constant even when its hit dice change, though its hit probability changes to fit the new HD. Once it perfectly matches its opponent, it uses the appropriate attack matrix for that form. When melee ends, or when reduced to 8 hit points or fewer, it reverts by the reverse process.\n\nIf faced with multiple attackers, it chooses one at random to emulate. Inside its body is a rubbery green organ containing a liquid which, mixed equally with water, becomes a potion of polymorph self. A single imorph yields 1–3 draughts.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_imorph"
  },
