    "npc_notes": "JACULI\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 11–20\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (8'–12')\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/10 + 1 per hit point\n\nJaculi are agile serpents with chameleon-like camouflage abilities. They are usually found in woods and forests, being basically arboreal and feeding on tree mosses and insects, though some swarms have adapted to pillared halls and similar settings. Although not naturally vicious, swarms are highly territorial and excitable, resenting more than a brief intrusion. Because of their camouflage, only 1 chance in 4 detects them even when they are in plain view.\n\nThe serpent has a long muscular body and a broad flat head with a ridge of razor-edged bone on either side. It can project itself from a high point with the force and accuracy of a javelin, surprising its victim unless previously detected. Its “flying” speed is 15\", but after such an attack it cannot attack again from ground level and must crawl up another tree or pillar first.",
