    "npc_notes": "JERMLAINE\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 12–48\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 1–4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: Special\nTREASURE TYPE: Per 10 individuals O, Q; in lair C, Q(x5), S, T\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–2 or 1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Average (with genius-level cunning)\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil (with slight lawful tendency)\nSIZE: S (1' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nNormal: I/7 + 1 per hit point\nElder: II/32 + 1 per hit point\n\nJermlaine, also called jinxkins or bane-midges, dwell in elaborate underground tunnel warrens, often very deep below the surface. They frequently cohabit with normal and giant rats and often share integrated tunnel systems with them. These evil runts are cowardly and attack only when they believe they can overwhelm victims without serious opposition. They prey on weakened, asleep, isolated, or unwary targets, and otherwise prefer sabotage and malice.\n\nThey are very fast, move quietly, and are masters of concealment. They commonly arm themselves with needle-sharp darts doing 1–2 hit points and pike-like weapons doing 1–4. Their favorite methods are ambush with pits or nets, taking victims alive, or vandalizing equipment by cutting straps, polluting water, spoiling food, stealing small objects, blunting arrows, puncturing flasks, and so on.\n\nIf more than 35 are encountered, one exceptionally evil elder can drain all magic from any magical item except an artifact or relic if he can handle it for 1–4 rounds. Their grey-brown warty hide and rags blend with earth and stone, so they surprise on 1–5 on d6 and are 75% undetectable if looked or listened for unless caught off guard suddenly. Jermlaine are treated as 4 hit dice creatures for magical attacks and saving throws, and because of their size and quickness they take no damage at all when they successfully save against attacks that would normally inflict half damage. Though their infravision extends only 30', their hearing and smell are keen enough that even invisible creatures are 50% likely to be detected under normal dungeon conditions. They speak their own tongue, their alignment language, converse with rats, and some speak common, dwarven, gnomish, goblin, or orcish.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_jermlaine"
  },
