    "npc_notes": "KHARGRA\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare (at best)\nNO. APPEARING: 1–6\nARMOR CLASS: -3\nMOVE: 3\" (15\")\nHIT DICE: 6\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3–18\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Surprise on 1–7 (d8)\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (3½' long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: V/300 + 6 per hit point\n\nKhargra are creatures from the Elemental Plane of Earth which occasionally venture onto the Prime Material Plane in search of high-grade ore. They “swim” through rock in small schools, riding earth movements and shifting strata as if surfing through the sea. When they find suitable ore they settle down to feed, ingesting it and refining the metal within their peculiar digestive systems. Naturally they prefer refined metal over ore, and if they sense worked metal nearby they pursue that instead.\n\nThey leap from wall or floor like fish leaping from water and attempt to fasten themselves with their clawed arms onto metallic objects, surprising nearby adventurers on 1–7 on d8, or 1–5 on d6 if dwarves or gnomes are present. A single khargra can swallow 5 pounds of metal per melee round and can hold 100 pounds or more. Once out of rock, it must crawl, pulling itself along with its arms. If attacked, it fights only because its meal has been disturbed. When attacked with a metal weapon, it bites the end off and swallows it on a roll of 16 or better. Against nonmetallic opponents it bites for 3–18 hit points, but even then its main goal remains eating metal.\n\nIts three strong clawed arms do no damage, but at least one arm must hit before it can bite a victim; once one arm has grasped, it does not let go until the way is clear to the desired metal or until its victim is dead. Each arm hits as if it were a 12 HD creature. Khargra can often be appeased by surrendering all metallic items. If one is cut open, up to 500 gp weight of non-assimilated metal pebbles may be found in its digestive tract.\n\nThough a khargra can emerge from rock instantly, it requires a full melee round to reintegrate into its native substance. If phase door is cast during reintegration, it dies instantly and remains out of phase until the magic is dispelled. Transmute metal to wood also kills it. They are immune to fire- and cold-based spells except for heat metal, which always does maximum damage. Lightning does full damage, and move earth stops a khargra in its tracks, stunning and confusing it for 1–3 rounds.\n\nPhysically, a khargra is a tapering cylinder about 3½' long, with three large metal fins, three extensible clawed arms, small eye bulges, and an iris-like metal-toothed mouth a full foot across.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_khargra"
  },
