    "npc_notes": "KILLMOULIS\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1–3\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 1/2 (1–4 hit points)\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: K\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Nil\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral (chaotic good)\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/9 + 1 per hit point\n\nKillmoulis always dwell where some kind of work is going on, preferably involving grain or other foodstuffs. They live under floors, in wall cracks, or in dark rafters, coming out only after the human workers leave. Brownie-like, they then work and make themselves useful while at the same time devouring prodigious amounts of meal, flour, grain, and similar food.\n\nIt is also part of their nature to play tricks and practical jokes. If they are molested, these pranks become destructive and harmful; otherwise they are merely irksome and bothersome. Killmoulis are very fast and can blend with surroundings and hide in shadowy places so effectively that there is only a 10% chance to detect them. They hate dogs, cats, and rats, as these animals attack them. Rats are usually snared or pinned, while cats and dogs are commonly poisoned if they pose a threat. If killmoulis cannot kill the animals threatening them, they simply move elsewhere.\n\nA killmoulis is usually under a foot tall, with a thin body and limbs but a large head with proportionate ears. It has no mouth; food is drawn into its huge nose. They seem to communicate telepathically.",
