    "npc_notes": "LAMIA NOBLE\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 10+1\n% IN LAIR: 60%\nTREASURE TYPE: D\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spells — see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: High\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2,550 + 14 per hit point\n\nLamia nobles rule over other lamias and over the wild lonely places they inhabit. Unlike the normal lamia, the noble has the lower body of a giant serpent, and the upper body may be either male or female. Male lamia nobles wield short swords and have magical ability equal to 1st–6th level, in addition to charm person, mirror image, suggestion, and illusion. Female lamia nobles are unarmed and attack only by spells, but have stronger magical powers, at 2nd–8th level, along with those same spells.\n\nThe touch of a lamia noble permanently drains 1 point of Wisdom, and once a victim’s Wisdom drops below 3 he willingly obeys whatever the lamia noble commands. All lamia nobles can assume human form, though intelligent humanoids can always penetrate the disguise. In this guise they try to infiltrate human society to work acts of evil. They speak all the languages of the man-like races. In human form they are recognized as lamias only by humans and demi-humans of 7th level or above, with a 10% cumulative chance per level above 6th, and clerics get a flat additional 15% chance. Lamia nobles are prone to senseless violent outbursts.",
