    "npc_notes": "LAVA CHILDREN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 3–18\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4 or more\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Q\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 3\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6/1–6/2–12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Spells — see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: “Immune” to metal — see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard, but see below\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n4 HD: III/150 + 4 per hit point\n5 HD: IV/205 + 5 per hit point\nSpell-casters: V/260 + 5 per hit point\nDouble-classed: V/475 + 6 per hit point\nTriple-classed: VI/700 + 7 per hit point\n\nThese humanoids are about the size of a broadly built man, but with a curious childlike appearance, pinkish-white skin, and permanent smiles. They are the unnatural offspring of spirits of earth and fire. In melee they attack with two claws for 1–6 hit points each and a powerful bite for 2–12.\n\nMetal simply does not exist for them in any meaningful physical sense: metal weapons and objects pass through them harmlessly, they can move through metal without hindrance, and any metal worn by a victim is ignored when figuring armour class against their attacks. Most lava children are 4 HD fighters. Larger groups include 5 HD warriors, 5 HD magic-users, 5 HD clerics, and in the largest groups a 6 HD double-classed warrior/magic-user; their greatest leaders are said to be triple-classed 7 HD warrior/magic-user/clerics.\n\nMagic-users cast their listed spells once per day each at 6th level, while clerics have the listed spell selection. Lava children are completely immune to fire and earth magic, but are vulnerable to air and water magic, taking 1 extra point of damage per caster level from the latter. They live underground or in volcanic regions and speak both their own sibilant tongue and the common tongue.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_lava_children"
  },
