    "npc_notes": "LIZARD KING\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 15\"//12\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 5–20\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Skewering — see below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 20%\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (about 8' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VI/550 + 10 per hit point\n\nThe lizard king is a taller, more intelligent, and more human-like variety of lizard man. It dwells in damp places, usually near an underground river or lake, and is attended by 10–100 lizard men followers or guards from whom it demands two human sacrifices every week. If humans are unavailable, it substitutes two of its followers for each missing human victim, so its followers work hard to satisfy it.\n\nIts fearsome trident inflicts 5–20 hit points of damage. If the attack roll exceeds the number needed to hit by 5 or more, the trident skewers the victim for double normal damage and at least 15 hit points. These special trident properties work only in the hands of a lizard king; in human hands it behaves like an ordinary trident. Except for these listed differences, the creature has the normal characteristics of a lizard man.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_lizard_king"
  },
