    "npc_notes": "MANTARI\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–3\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 18\"\nHIT DICE: 1+1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Special — see below\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: S\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/65 + 2 per hit point\n\nThe mantari closely resembles a marine ray, with a flat body about 3' long and nearly as wide, plus a thin whip-like tail 4' long. It usually preys on giant rats and similar creatures, but it is normally aggressive toward humans and other beings. It flies with its tail hanging down, but when diving from a height of 10'–12' above ground it angles the tail sharply forward.\n\nIt attacks only with the tail. The sting is not poisonous, but acts on the victim’s nervous system. Damage from a hit equals 19 minus the victim’s constitution, with no saving throw allowed. If the same victim is hit in two successive rounds, the second hit does four times normal damage. Further successive hits remain at quadruple damage, not higher. Mantari are found in many locales, though they favor dirty dungeon chambers where prey is abundant. For aerial combat they are manoeuvrability class C.",
