    "npc_notes": "MEAZEL\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 95%\nTREASURE TYPE: B\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4/1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/85 + 4 per hit point\n\nMeazels are solitary bipeds just smaller than man-sized, usually found in marshes or small damp underground caverns. They have 4th-level thieving abilities and rarely attack openly. Instead they hide, move quietly and quickly, and try to strangle stragglers from behind or pick pockets for the gold they love. They are traditional enemies of orcs and kobolds.\n\nThey seldom venture far from their lairs and drag corpses back there to eat in safety. Sacks of bones are often found near a meazel lair, and any gems it has happened to take will be mixed in those sacks because it does not understand their value. In combat it attacks with two claws for 1–4 each, or it uses a thin tough cord to strangle a victim. A successful strangling hit means the cord is around the neck, and the victim dies within two melee rounds unless he breaks free, the meazel dies, or it is forced to release him. This attack works only on man-sized or smaller victims and only if the meazel reaches them from the rear undetected.\n\nMeazels have a nasty reputation even among other dungeon creatures. Their skin ranges from light grey to dark green, and most have angry red patches from a harmless but ugly skin disease. Their eyes are jet black and their feet are partially webbed.",
