    "npc_notes": "MEENLOCK\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 3–5\nARMOR CLASS: 1 (but see below)\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: 100%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–4/1–4\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Dimension door\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: S (2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/240 + 4 per hit point\n\nMeenlocks are small black-furred bipeds with white ridged heads and a horrifying appearance. Anyone with 4 hit dice or fewer who sees one must save or collapse inert in fear for 5–8 melee rounds, halved on a successful save. Their lairs lie at the bottoms of dark sealed underground shafts lined with thick moss and reeking of rot and evil. If intruders reach the lair, the meenlocks attack with two claws for 1–4 each, and their touch causes paralysis, save allowed.\n\nIn close quarters their telepathic powers are less useful, which is why they deliberately create the smell of rotting corpses to discourage intrusion. They try hard to extinguish light sources and can use a limited dimension door of 6' every other round; while doing so, attacks against them are at -4 to hit. They cannot use this power while carrying a victim, and three meenlocks are needed to carry one.\n\nIf adventurers open a meenlock shaft but do not destroy the lair, the creatures may follow them at a safe distance, mark one victim, usually a human if present and preferably a paladin, and torment him with telepathic threats and false sensory impressions. Over time this harassment reduces his effectiveness, temporarily draining strength, dexterity, intelligence, and wisdom by 1 point each per hour, imposing -1 to hit in melee, and granting targets of his spells +2 on saves. These effects accumulate until the threat is ended. When the party camps, the meenlocks attack with great stealth, trying to silence guards and drag away the marked victim. If they succeed, they take him to the shaft, reseal it, and after a gruesome process turn him into another meenlock.",
