    "npc_notes": "MEPHIT - FIRE\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 5\nMOVE: 12\"/24\"\nHIT DICE: 3+1\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: 2–12 platinum pieces\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–3/1–3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Breath weapon\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Variable but always evil\nSIZE: M (5' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/150 + 4 per hit point\n\nFire mephits are dull red with thin black streaks and wisps of flame around their bodies. Touching one with bare flesh causes 1 point of damage. Their claws do 1–3 each, and the body text adds 1 point of heat damage per claw strike. Their breath weapon can be either a jet of flame 15' long and 1' wide, automatically hitting one designated target for 2–9 damage, save for half, or a 5' square blanket of flame immediately in front of the mephit for 4 damage to each victim with no save. They can breathe three times per day.\n\nA fire mephit can use heat metal and a two-missile magic missile once each per day. Once per hour it may try to gate in another mephit, with a 25% chance of success; the arrival may be a fire, lava, smoke, or steam mephit.",
