    "npc_notes": "MEZZODAEMON\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (rarely 1–3)\nARMOR CLASS: -3\nMOVE: 15\"\nHIT DICE: 10+40 hit points\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals Q(x5), X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 or 1 weapon\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 7–12/7–12 or by weapon +5\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Special\nINTELLIGENCE: High to exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Evil (neutral)\nSIZE: M (about 7' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/2,700 + 14 per hit point\n\nMezzodaemons inhabit the Lower Planes between the Abyss and the Hells, especially Tartarus, Hades, and Gehenna. They associate freely with night hags and demons, tolerate devils, and roam the Astral and Ethereal Planes as well. They are not hard to summon to the Prime Material Plane, and they often accept service with evil mortals if paid and properly respected.\n\nA mezzodaemon may strike with its horny hands and talons for 7–12 hit points each, or it may use magical weapons such as battle-axes, flails, bastard swords, or two-handed swords, usually with a magic shield. When armed, it receives a +3 bonus to hit and adds +5 damage with the weapon. They can use most magical items not restricted by alignment or class, though their own magic resistance may interfere.\n\nTheir innate powers include dimension door twice per day, become ethereal once per day, magic jar once per day, passwall four times per day, repulsion once per day, wind walk once per day, and word of recall once per day. At will, one power per round, they may use comprehend languages, detect invisibility, detect magic, ESP, invisibility, levitate, polymorph self, and read magic. They are unaffected by nonmagical weapons, including iron and silver, and immune to paralysis and poisons. Acid, cold, and fire do only half damage. Their magic resistance depends on spell level: 95% against 1st-level spells, 90% against 2nd, 85% against 3rd, and so on down to 55% against 9th-level spells, adjusted from an 11th-level caster base. They can never be charmed, and suggestion never affects them. They see in infrared and ultraviolet and have limited telepathy with creatures of low or better intelligence. Each keeps its true name secret to avoid control by stronger fiends or summoners.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_mezzodaemon"
  },
