    "npc_notes": "MITE\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 6–24\nARMOR CLASS: 8\nMOVE: 3\"\nHIT DICE: 1–1\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: C\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: S (2' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/5 + 1 per hit point\n\nMites are tiny humanoids with large heads and evil faces, their skin ranging from light grey to violet. They inhabit networks of narrow tunnels above and below main dungeon corridors. Their scampering feet and shrill twittering voices are often heard, but they are rarely seen and almost never attack openly.\n\nInstead they try to trap lone adventurers or unwary stragglers with trapdoors, nets, tripwires, and similar devices, then hustle the captive away before help can arrive. Captives are robbed, stripped, bound, beaten, and later dumped back into the main corridor for wandering monsters to find. In melee mites bite for 1–3 damage. Like jermlaine, they use weighted clubs to beat captives insensible, and a trapped victim is 90% likely to be treated this way. Their tunnel entrances are hidden and found only as secret doors, and the tunnels themselves are difficult for human-sized beings to enter. Mites are related to jermlaine and snyads. They have no real language beyond rudimentary twittering sounds.",
