    "npc_notes": "NECROPHIDIUS, DEATH WORM\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation (and see below)\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to poison (and see below)\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/118 + 2 per hit point\n\nThis creature appears to be a giant snake skeleton with a human skull for a head. It is totally silent, immune to sleep, charm, and mind-affecting spells, immune to poison, and never checks morale. Its bite inflicts 1–8 hit points of damage and causes paralysis unless the victim saves against magic; the paralysis lasts 1–4 turns.\n\nA necrophidius surprises 50% of the time, and if it is not itself surprised it performs the Dance of Death, a hypnotic semi-magical swaying that rivets any observer who fails a save against magic; treat this as hypnotism. It is created for one specific purpose and is therefore encountered as an assassin or guard, never as a wandering monster. It may be created from a special tome, by a high-level magic-user using limited wish, geas, and charm person, or by a high-level cleric using quest, neutralize poison, prayer, silence, and snake charm. The materials are a complete giant snake skeleton and the skull of a cold-blooded murderer killed within the last 24 hours. It costs 500 gp per hit point and takes 10 days to construct. Despite appearances, it is not undead and cannot be turned.",
