    "npc_notes": "NEEDLEMAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 5–50\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 3+4\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: G\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1–6\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–2\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Surprise\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Sub-standard — see below\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/85 + 3 per hit point\n\nThis intelligent woodland plant resembles a zombie but is neither animal nor undead. Its flesh is embedded with masses of sharp pine-like needles. Each round it may fire 1–6 needles, each doing 1–2 hit points of damage out to 20', with the accuracy of a short-range arrow. Its needle supply is effectively endless.\n\nThe creature is particularly vulnerable to magic: offensive magical attacks do triple normal damage, though it still gets saving throws, and non-offensive magic such as charm plants is triply effective where appropriate. Needlemen appear to hate elves and attack them on sight. When concealed among conifers or heavy undergrowth, they are 75% undetectable and achieve surprise 75% of the time. It is very rare to encounter one outside that habitat.",
