    "npc_notes": "NILBOG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare (at best)\nNO. APPEARING: 4–40\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 1–1\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals K; in lair G\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–6 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/53 + 1 per hit point\n\nA nilbog looks exactly like a normal goblin and has all goblin characteristics except that it suffers from a bizarre spatio-temporal reversal called nilbogism. The disorder is extremely rare and imperfectly understood. In the presence of nilbogs, adventurers may be compelled to act in ways directly contrary to their intentions, with no saving throw and no known defense short of very powerful magic such as a properly used wish.\n\nAnother strange power is that a nilbog gains hit points whenever it is struck, adding the intended damage rolled. It can be harmed only by reverse means such as cure wounds spells or forcibly administered healing potions. Nilbogs are feared because there is apparently no reliable way to distinguish them from ordinary goblins except by divination or trial and error. No other creature is known to suffer from nilbogism.",
