    },
    "npc_notes": "NONAFEL, CAT O’NINE TAILS\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: Parent 5, “children” 6\nMOVE: Parent 9\", “children” 12\"\nHIT DICE: 9\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2–20 or 1–8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,400 + 12 per hit point\n\nAt first glance this creature appears to be a large black panther with bloodshot yellow eyes. It is usually found in caves in warm regions of the underworld and is carnivorous; its hide may fetch as much as 1,500 gp. Its extraordinary dissociative power allows it to divide into nine separate black panthers in one segment, apparently instinctively. It will usually transform as soon as enemies are sighted and try to surround them, the nine “children” acting in coordinated fashion as if linked telepathically. There is only a 10% chance that it remains in parent form initially, and even then the dissociation occurs after 1–2 melee rounds.\n\nIf one or more children are damaged, there is a 25% chance each melee round that they blink back together into the parent, provided all are within 50'. While re-formed, the parent regenerates 9 hit points per round, one per child, though dead offspring do not regenerate. After one round of regeneration it dissociates again, with fewer offspring if any have been killed. The parent attacks as a 9 HD monster with its flail-like tail for 2–20 damage; each child fights as a 2 HD creature and strikes with its tail for 1–8. When it dissociates, the parent’s current hit points are divided as evenly as possible among the children.",
