    "npc_notes": "NORKER\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 3–30\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 1+2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: E\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1–3/1–6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: I/20 + 2 per hit point\n\nNorkers are distant relatives of hobgoblins and resemble them in most ways, but they have developed 3\" fangs which inflict 1–3 hit points of damage in melee. In the same round they can also attack the same target with a club for 1–6 hit points. If disarmed, they have no effective claw attack.\n\nThe norker has a very tough skin, a sort of exoskeleton, which gives it armour class 3. In all other respects they resemble hobgoblins.",
