    "npc_notes": "NYCADAEMON\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 (very rarely 1–2)\nARMOR CLASS: -4\nMOVE: 12\"/36\"\nHIT DICE: 12+36 points\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Q (x10), X\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 or 1 weapon\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 9–16/9–16 or by weapon +6\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Special\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional–genius\nALIGNMENT: Evil (neutral)\nSIZE: L (about 8' tall and broad)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IX/6,800 + 16 per hit point\n\nNycadaemons are among the most powerful native beings of the middle Lower Planes, especially Tartarus, Hades, and Gehenna, and unlike mezzodaemons they can also enter both the Abyss and the Hells freely. Other lesser fiends avoid them because they are utterly wicked, domineering, and calculating. They cooperate with other evil beings only when it benefits them.\n\nTheir strength is comparable to that of stone giants, and their fists inflict 9–16 hit points of damage each. When using a suitably large magic weapon and shield, they gain +4 to hit and do weapon damage +6. They can use many magic items suitable to their size and nature, though their multi-planed structure makes lesser spell devices unreliable.\n\nTheir powers include command three times per day, dispel magic twice, dimension door three times, gaseous form once, mirror image (4 images) twice, reverse gravity twice, wind walk three times, and word of recall once. Once per round they may use one of the following: comprehend languages, detect invisibility, detect magic, enlarge/reduce, fear by touch, invisibility in a 10' radius, polymorph self, project image, read magic, and telepathy. Only +2 or better weapons harm them. Iron and silver do not. Paralysis, poison, and gases do nothing to them. Acid, cold, and fire do only half damage. They regenerate 3 hit points per turn.\n\nTheir magic resistance is graduated from 100% against 1st-level magic down by 5% per spell level to 60% against 9th-level magic, adjusted up or down by caster level relative to 11th. Beguiling, charm, and suggestion never affect them. They see the full radiation spectrum and communicate telepathically with creatures of low or better intelligence. Each keeps its true personal name secret to avoid control.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_nycadaemon"
  },
