    "npc_notes": "OGRILLON\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1–4 (5–30 in lair)\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: Individuals M; in lair B, S\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2–7/2–7\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/28 + 2 per hit point\n\nThe ogrillon is a smaller species of ogre, an orc-ogre crossbreed. In general behavior it resembles its larger cousin, except that it never uses weapons and fights only with its horny fists. Because of its strength of 18(01), each fist inflicts 2–7 hit points of damage.\n\nMost resemble orcs closely enough that there is a 90% chance they cannot be told apart, even when both are present together. About 10% appear more ogrish, though smaller, and these are easily distinguished. They speak only ogrish and their alignment language.",
