    "npc_notes": "OSQUIP\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 2–24\nARMOR CLASS: 1\nMOVE: 12\" (3\")\nHIT DICE: 3+1\n% IN LAIR: 80%\nTREASURE TYPE: D\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2–12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (2' high at shoulder)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/60 + 4 per hit point\n\nThe osquip is a multi-legged, hairless, rodent-like creature about the size of a small dog. Most have 6 legs, 25% have 8, and 5% have 10. Its hide is pale yellow and like pliable leather. The small eyes are set close together and protected by ridges of hide-covered bone, while the jaws project forward and carry large spade-like teeth.\n\nIt lairs in extensive tunnel systems under buildings or in dungeons, with entrances hidden like secret doors and too small for normal human passage. It feeds on rats, mice, and other small vermin, but is ferocious and attacks fearlessly, sometimes springing from hidden openings to surprise victims. Its bite does 2–12 hit points of damage. It has high dexterity. Using its jaws, it can burrow through rock at movement rate. Its relations with other tunnel-dwellers such as jermlaine, mites, and snyads are unpredictable; at times it cooperates with them, and at other times it preys on them.",
