    "npc_notes": "PENANGGALAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: Normal 10; head and gut when detached 8\nMOVE: As normal woman; head and gut when detached 12\"\nHIT DICE: Body variable; head and gut when detached 4\n% IN LAIR: See below\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-6 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Blood drain\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: Variable, but at minimum V/290 + 5 per hit point\n\nA penanggalan is a female vampire-type undead. By day it appears as an attractive human woman and retains the combat and class abilities it had in life. At night, the head and entrails detach from the body and fly out to feed on human blood. Witnessing this detachment requires a save versus magic; failure means death, and success still results in feeblemind.\n\nThe detached head tries to hypnotise sleeping human victims at -3 to save, then makes tiny wounds in the throat and feeds throughout the night. Each feeding drains 1-6 hit points and 1 point each of strength and constitution. Females slain by a penanggalan rise after three days as new penanggalans. In detached form it may be turned as a wraith. The creature keeps hidden lairs containing large vessels of vinegar, because the swollen entrails must soak in vinegar for an hour before they can re-enter the body.",
    "id": "fiend_folio_penanggalan"
  },
