    "npc_notes": "PERNICON\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 4-40 (in lair 300-3,000)\nARMOR CLASS: 3\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 20%\nTREASURE TYPE: 1-4 gems and 25% chance of 100-600 gold pieces\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-3\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Constitution drain\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (2\" long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III + 1 per hit point\n\nA brightly coloured insect rather like a grasshopper, the pernicon is prized by desert nomads because its antennae detect water within 120 feet. When disturbed, it leaps onto exposed flesh and grips with the pincers at the end of its abdomen. A hit inflicts 1-3 hit points of damage and drains 1 point of constitution. Thereafter the drain continues automatically each round.\n\nEven when killed, a pernicon’s pincers remain attached, and removing it inflicts a further 1-4 hit points of damage. If constitution falls below 3, the victim collapses unconscious; below 0, he dies.",
