    "npc_notes": "POLTERGEIST\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-8\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 6\"\nHIT DICE: 1-4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 95%\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Nil\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Fear\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Invisibility; silver or magic weapons to hit\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Lawful evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: II/34 + 1 per hit point\n\nA wandering poltergeist is treated as a skeleton on the cleric/undead matrix, but one bound to the place where it was “killed” is treated as a ghoul. It is invisible and non-corporeal, so only silver and magical weapons can harm it, and attacks against it are at -4 unless the attacker can see invisible.\n\nIt attacks by hurling nearby objects as though a 5 HD monster were throwing them. If the target is hit, no hit point damage is inflicted, but the victim must save versus fear or flee the area in random directions for 2-24 melee rounds. Holy water or a strongly presented holy symbol drives it back but does not harm it.",
