    "npc_notes": "PROTEIN POLYMORPH\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 2\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 6-8\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: O\nNO. OF ATTACKS: Variable\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 6-36 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\n6 HD: V/400 + 6 per hit point\n7 HD: VI/575 + 8 per hit point\n8 HD: VI/925 + 10 per hit point\n\nProtein polymorphs are intelligent cellular colonies able to assume almost any form they choose, including inanimate objects, creatures up to their hit dice limit, or several linked forms connected by nearly invisible films of protoplasm. They can imitate anything from a treasure pile to a room to a party of humanoids.\n\nTheir normal attack is to bludgeon and then enfold prey, crushing for 6-36 hit points of damage per round. If disguised as armed creatures, they attack by weapon type instead. They copy physical form and ordinary strength, but not special abilities.",
