    "npc_notes": "QUAGGOTH\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 2-24\nARMOR CLASS: 6\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 1+2\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: A\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 2 or 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4/1-4 or by weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Immune to poison\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L (7'+ tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE:\nWarrior II/28 + 2 per hit point\nLeader II/50 + 3 per hit point\n\nQuaggoths are large white shaggy bipeds of uncertain origin, possibly once a warlike cannibal race. They are highly aggressive and usually attack anything that flees, threatens them, or even merely remains motionless within sight.\n\nAbout 70% are unarmed and fight with two claws for 1-4 each. The remainder are armed with either battle-axes or two-handed swords. For every 12 encountered there is one leader with 15 hit points, 3 HD, AC 4, and a battle-axe or two-handed sword. They are totally immune to poison and fight on berserkly even after being reduced below zero hit points.",
