    "npc_notes": "QULLAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-6\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 2\n% IN LAIR: 10%\nTREASURE TYPE: Most types in lair but in small quantity (10% of A at most)\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 5-11\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (8'+ tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: III/73 + 2 per hit point\n\nQullans are strong, large, seemingly insane humanoids who wear wild warpaint and tiger-skins or go naked. They attack with specially honed broadswords that strike at +3 to hit and +3 damage, for a total of 5-11 damage. These swords blunt easily, with a cumulative 20% chance per hit of losing their exceptional edge.\n\nAll qullans radiate confusion in a 5-foot radius. Anyone in melee with them must save or become confused, either standing still, attacking the nearest qullan without regard for safety, or attacking the nearest friend. They are so totally chaotic that any successful charm or control effect causes their own confusion power to feed back and kill them instantly.",
