    "npc_notes": "REVENANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-16\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Paralysation\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: See below\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: VII/1,275 + 10 per hit point\n\nA revenant is created only rarely, when a violently slain character of exceptional strength of will returns from death solely to take vengeance on the killer. It is undead, but unlike ordinary undead it is driven by personal will rather than evil, so clerics cannot turn or destroy it and holy paraphernalia do not affect it.\n\nIt attacks by locking its hands around its victim’s throat and strangling for 2-16 points of damage each round. It can also paralyse only its killer with a terror gaze, save versus magic or be paralysed for 2-8 rounds. It regenerates, even after apparent death, unless burned to ashes. Once all intended victims are dead, it disintegrates permanently.",
