    "npc_notes": "SON OF KYUSS\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 10\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 4\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Regeneration and see below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\nLEVEL/X.P. VALUE: IV/215 + 4 per hit point\n\nThese horrifying undead are putrid corpses with fat green worms crawling in and out of all openings in the skull. Each son is surrounded by a 30-foot fear aura. It regenerates 2 hit points per round, and even severed limbs regenerate. It can be permanently destroyed only by fire, lightning, acid, or application of holy water or holy objects to its wounds.\n\nIt attacks with flailing fists for 1-8 damage, and each hit has a 25% chance to inflict advanced leprosy. In addition, one worm per round may leap from the head onto an adjacent opponent; if it reaches the victim’s brain, the victim becomes a son of Kyuss.",
