    "npc_notes": "WATER WEIRD\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 4\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 3+3\n% IN LAIR: 50%\nTREASURE TYPE: I, O, P, Y\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 0\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: Nil\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Drowning\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Sharp weapons do only 1 point; many attacks ineffective; reforms unless killed properly\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Chaotic evil\nSIZE: L (10'+ long)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: The water weird is a life form originating in the elemental plane of water. It attacks all living things, feeding from their essences in some unknown manner. The creature forms in two melee rounds from the water, appearing as a serpent, and lashes out, striking as a 6 hit dice monster. Any creature struck will be dragged into the water unless it saves versus paralyzation. Sharp weapons cause but 1 hit point of damage; blunt ones cause normal damage when striking these monsters. Damage equal to its total hit points disrupts the water weird, but it reforms again in 2 melee rounds. Cold spells slow it, fire-based spells do half or no damage, but a purify water spell actually kills it. All other attacks simply do not harm or disrupt the creature. A water weird can take over a water elemental on a dice score of 11 or better on a 20-sided die.",
