    "npc_notes": "MEN, TRIBESMAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 120\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 12\"\nHIT DICE: 1\n% IN LAIR: 40%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Nil\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Low to average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Primitive tribesmen are typically found in tropical jungles or on islands. They use large shields. Their leaders conform to those of cavemen, but they have additional clerics: one 4th-level cleric for every 10 tribesmen, one 6th-level cleric for every 30 tribesmen, and one 8th-level head cleric, witchdoctor. Tribesman clerics are druidical in nature. These men dwell in villages of grass, bamboo, or mud huts. There is a 50% chance that the village lair will be protected by a log palisade. The village will contain females and young equal to 100% of the males encountered. There is a 75% chance that there will be 20-50 slaves and a 50% chance that there will be 2-12 captives held for food. Their treasure is exactly that of cavemen, but tribesmen can possess all three types. They are armed with shield, spear, and club; shield and two spears; or shortbow and club. Treat tribesmen’s clubs as maces.",
