    "npc_notes": "MEN, PILGRIM\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 10-100\nARMOR CLASS: See below\nMOVE: See below\nHIT DICE: 1-6 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 0%\nTREASURE TYPE: See below\nNO. OF ATTACKS: See below\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: See below\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Mean average to very\nALIGNMENT: See below\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: See below\nAttack/Defense Modes: See below\n\nNotes: Pilgrims are groups of individuals on their way to visit some place which is holy or unholy to them. They are found nearly everywhere. A group of pilgrims will always have additional clerics: 1-6 of 2nd level, 1-4 of 4th level, 1-2 of 6th level, and 1 of 8th level with 3rd- and 5th-level assistants. There is a 25% chance that a 5th- or 6th-level monk will be with the party. For every 10 pilgrims there is a 10% chance there will be 1-10 fighters of 1st-8th level, a like chance that there will be 1-6 thieves of 2nd-7th level, and a 5% chance per 10 pilgrims that a magic-user of 6th-9th level is with the group. If the pilgrims are lawful good, fighters will be paladins. If chaotic good, fighters will be rangers. If neutral, the clerics will be druids. If lawful evil, all pilgrims will fight as berserkers though armed only with daggers. If chaotic evil, the thieves will be assassins of the indicated levels.\n\nA group of pilgrims is likely to be aligned as follows: lawful good 35%, chaotic good 20%, neutral 10%, chaotic evil 15%, lawful evil 20%. All above-average characters have normal chances for psionic abilities. Pilgrims are 75% likely to be afoot and 25% likely to be mounted. Pilgrims and monks carry type J treasure. Fighters carry types L and M, while clerics have types J, K, and M. Magic-users have types L, N, and Q, thieves types J, N, and Q. There is a 5% chance that some high-level member of the band is carrying a religious artifact. Such an artifact will be carefully hidden and well guarded by traps and/or magic devices.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_men_pilgrim"
  },
