    "npc_notes": "MERMAN\n\nFREQUENCY: Uncommon\nNO. APPEARING: 20-200\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 1\"/18\"\nHIT DICE: 1+1\n% IN LAIR: 25%\nTREASURE TYPE: C, R\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Ship grappling and missile attack\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Average to very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Mermen are found in the seas and oceans in the warm temperate and tropical areas. They range over areas harvesting vegetation and hunting fish. Additionally, mermen actually herd certain fishes. They venture out of water only to sun themselves or to visit some coastal spot. Mermen have regular undersea communities, generally a reef or cliff honeycombed with passages and rooms. Only 10% of the time will they construct a village of shells, rocks, and coral. This community will have areas where the merwomen and their young, equal to 100% and 100% of the total merman population respectively, live, netted pens where food fishes are kept, workshops, and so on. These communities will be guarded by from 3-18 larger-sized barracuda, for mermen have learned to tame and use these fish.\n\nMermen use trident and dagger, crossbow and dagger, or net, javelin, and dagger. Some carrying tridents also have grapples and 50' lines. On occasion mermen will attack surface vessels. To do so they must surface and grapple it. They are very accurate with these hooks and are 90% likely to hit. Ten mermen will then hold the line, and the ship will be slowed 1\" for every such grappling. Meanwhile, the other mermen will fire their crossbows and darts at exposed crewmen. A motionless ship will be held by the mermen in 4-16 melee rounds and then slowly sunk and eventually looted. During such an attempt the attacking mermen are exposed to missile fire from the vessel, and if flame is used against them the mermen take double damage. Mermen speak their own language, and 50% also speak locathah.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_merman"
  },
