    "npc_notes": "MIMIC\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 3\"\nHIT DICE: 7-10\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 3-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Glue\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Camouflage\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Semi- to average\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Mimics are subterranean creatures which cannot stand the light of the sun. They are able to perfectly mimic stone or wood. There are two varieties of this creature, the large, 9-10 dice, semi-intelligent carnivorous killer mimic and the slightly smaller intelligent sort. While the former will attack anything nearby, the latter are generally friendly if offered food. All mimics move about constantly in their search for prey. Mimics pose as stonework, doors, chests, or any other substance or item they can imitate. When a creature touches the mimic, it lashes out with a pseudopod, delivering 3-12 points of damage per hit. Meanwhile, the mimic excretes a glue which holds fast whatever member the creature touched the mimic with. Killer mimics do not speak, but the other breeds have their own language and can usually speak several other tongues such as common and orcish. For consideration they will usually tell a party about what they have seen nearby.",
