    "npc_notes": "MOLD, BROWN\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 patch\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 0\"\nHIT DICE: —\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 0\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 0\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Freezing\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Non-\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S to L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Brown mold grows anywhere beneath the surface of the ground. It is light tan to golden brown in color. It cannot stand high concentrations of ultraviolet light, but it feeds on radiant energy of most other sorts. Where a patch of brown mold grows, the temperature will be below average. If a creature walks within 5' of the patch, the mold will begin absorbing body heat. Each melee round that a creature is within 5' of brown mold, the mold will drain heat equal to 1-8 hit points frost damage for every 10 degrees of body heat over 55 degrees the creature has. Worse still, this mold grows instantaneously from heat, so if a torch, flaming oil, or a fire ball is near the patch, it will be able to grow 2, 4, or 8 times its area from the heat fed to it. This growth is so rapid that on the next melee round it will have spread and be draining heat in its new area. Brown mold is not fed by light spells or faerie fire. It is affected only by magical cold, and no other magical or non-magical attacks. Ice storms or walls of ice cause it to go dormant for 5-30 turns. A cold wand or white dragon breath will kill it. The growth does not harm creatures which use cold.",
