    "npc_notes": "YELLOW MOLD COLONY, INTELLIGENT\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1 colony\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 0\"\nHIT DICE: —\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-8\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Poison spores; psionic attack\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: See below\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: See below\nINTELLIGENCE: Collective vegetable intelligence\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: Colony\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Special\nAttack/Defense Modes: Special\n\nNotes: When formed into great colonies of at least 300 square feet in area, yellow mold will form a collective intelligence about 1 time in 6. If this should happen the yellow mold will be aware mentally and psionically. It will attack by spore cloud if it senses the presence of other life forms, range varying from 10' to 60', or psionically if such abilities are used within from 20' to 120'. If it attacks psionically, it will await the approach of the life form and then loose an attack equal to the most powerful form of id insinuation. It cannot be counter-attacked psionically unless a cleric able to telepathically communicate with plants is on hand to channel such attacks into a form which will affect the vegetable intelligence of the colony. Otherwise, the yellow mold must be physically attacked and destroyed. The colony has sufficient power to make from 1 to 10 psionic attacks within as many turns, and after resting for 1-4 days it will thereafter be able to attack in this manner again.",
