    "npc_notes": "NIGHT HAG\n\nFREQUENCY: Very rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1\nARMOR CLASS: 9\nMOVE: 9\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: Nil\nTREASURE TYPE: Nil\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 2-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Sleep and strangulation; dream riding; magic missile; ray of enfeeblement; gating\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Etherealness; broad spell immunities; special weapon requirements\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 65%\nINTELLIGENCE: Exceptional\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: M\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Night hags rule the convoluted planes of Hades and are seldom encountered elsewhere. In their own region they are numerous, but on the material plane they appear singly, always searching for very evil persons to slay and bring to Hades to form another larva. If a night hag finds a very selfishly evil person, she will cast a powerful sleep spell affecting even up to 12th-level humans unless a saving throw versus magic is successful. The night hag then strangles the sleeping victim. If the sleep spell fails, the hag visits the victim nightly in ethereal state, intrudes upon dreams to cause the victim to become ethereal also, and then rides the victim until dawn. The night hag cannot be removed from the back by the victim, and each nightly ride permanently drains 1 point of Constitution. When 0 Constitution is reached the victim is dead, and the night hag returns to Hades with the larval soul.\n\nNight hags hate goodness, and they will attack any creature of good alignment if success seems possible. They can employ a magic missile spell 3 times per day, each missile causing 2-16 hit points of damage when it strikes. They can likewise use a ray of enfeeblement 3 times per day. They can become ethereal at will, know a creature's alignment, and polymorph themselves at will. If hard pressed, a night hag can attempt to gate in a type I demon or a barbed devil, 50%/50%, with a 50% chance of the gate opening. Night hags are totally invulnerable to sleep, charm, fear, fire-, and cold-based spells. It requires a silver, iron, or +3 or better weapon to harm one. Night hags are able to astrally project their bodies, but only if in possession of a special periapt forged in Hades. This periapt cures diseases contracted by the possessor and grants +2 on all saving throws, but in the hands of a good creature it decays by 10% with each use and eventually vanishes. Description: The night hag is a hideous dark blue-violet color, with black hair and glowing red eyes. Her taloned hands and feet have jet-black nails.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_night_hag"
  },
