    "npc_notes": "NIXIE\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 20-80\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 6\"/12\"\nHIT DICE: 1-4 hit points\n% IN LAIR: 95%\nTREASURE TYPE: C, Q\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 1\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: By weapon type\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Charm\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Nil\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: 25%\nINTELLIGENCE: Very\nALIGNMENT: Neutral\nSIZE: S (4' tall)\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Nixies are water sprites inhabiting lakes. They can, but seldom do, venture onto land. Nixies weave dwellings of living seaweed, so it is 95% unlikely that their lair will be noticed at any distance under 2\". Furthermore, nixies will have giant fish guarding their lair, 1-2 gar 20% of the time or 2-5 pike 80% of the time, and these obey simple commands given by the nixies. They can also summon 10-100 small fish. Nixies delight in enslaving humans, and if one or more approach within 30' of a group of nixies, the latter will generate a powerful charm spell, one such spell for each 10 nixies, requiring the victim to save versus magic at -2 on the die roll. If a charmed person has dispel magic cast upon him before entering the water, there is a 75% chance the charm will be broken, but once in the water the chance is only 10%. If a human is charmed, the nixies will take the victim to their lair for 1 full year, after which the charm wears off and the victim is allowed to go free. During enslavement the nixies maintain a water breathing spell on the human captive. Each nixie can cast water breathing, or dispel it, once per day, lasting 1 day.\n\nNixies are armed with long daggers and darts, javelins, using the latter as spears underwater and as missiles above. Each nixie carries one of each weapon. The javelins can be thrown 6\" maximum. Although nixies are 25% magic resistant, they fear fire and very bright light. A flaming sword or a light spell will keep them back. A continual light spell will keep them at bay until they can negate it by summoning small fish to crowd around the light and dim it. Nixies speak their own language and common. Description: Nixies appear to be very comely humanoids, with greenish skin, dark green hair, and silver eyes. Their skin is lightly scaled and their hands and feet are webbed.",
