    "npc_notes": "OCTOPUS, GIANT\n\nFREQUENCY: Rare\nNO. APPEARING: 1-3\nARMOR CLASS: 7\nMOVE: 3\"/12\"\nHIT DICE: 8\n% IN LAIR: 70%\nTREASURE TYPE: R\nNO. OF ATTACKS: 7\nDAMAGE/ATTACK: 1-4 (x6)/2-12\nSPECIAL ATTACKS: Constriction\nSPECIAL DEFENSES: Ink cloud; color blending\nMAGIC RESISTANCE: Standard\nINTELLIGENCE: Animal\nALIGNMENT: Neutral evil\nSIZE: L\nPSIONIC ABILITY: Nil\nAttack/Defense Modes: Nil\n\nNotes: Giant octopi inhabit warm waters of medial to shallow depth. They lair in wrecked ships and undersea caves. They hunt at night, snatching and dining on any form of life that is vulnerable. They readily attack swimmers or seize small vessels in order to eat the crew. These creatures are malicious and cunning. Several will cooperate to overwhelm a larger ship if the opportunity presents itself. Vessels grabbed by giant octopi will lose way and come to a full stop in 3 turns. A giant octopus will generally attack with 6 of its 8 tentacles, using 2 to anchor itself. Each tentacle striking does only 1-4 hit points of damage, but unless the member is loosened or severed, it will do twice initial damage, 2-8 points, each melee round thereafter. The octopus also has a vicious beak which can bite nearby prey for 2-12 hit points.\n\nAny creature will be struck only by 1 tentacle at a time unless it is larger than about 8' tall or long. There is a 25% chance that a creature struck by a tentacle will have its upper limbs pinned, and a 25% chance that neither upper limb will be held. If both limbs are held the creature has no attack with them; if only 1 is pinned the creature attacks at -3 to hit; if both are free the creature still attacks at -1. A tentacle grasps with a grip equal to 18/20 Strength, and any creature of equal or greater Strength can grasp the tentacle and negate its constriction; but this does not free the victim, and the octopus will immediately seek to drag the victim to its mouth. To break free, a tentacle must be severed. Each tentacle takes 8 hit points in addition to the 8 hit dice the octopus itself has. If 3 or more tentacles are severed it is 90% probable that the octopus will retreat, blowing forth a cloud of black ink 4\" high by 6\" wide by 6\" long. It will then run to its lair or hide in some nearby place, changing its color to blend with its surroundings. The ink cloud completely obscures the vision of any creature within it.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_octopus_giant"
  },
