    },
    "npc_notes": "LYCANTHROPE, GENERAL NOTES\n\n\nNotes: Lycanthropes are humans with the ability to assume animal form. During darkness they most commonly change into their animal shapes. During a full moon they are 90% likely to be compelled into that form. They usually move about as humans for whatever purposes they may have. Each type has its own language in addition to common. Any humanoid bitten by a lycanthrope for damage equal to or greater than 50% of total possible hit points, but not actually killed and eaten, is infected with lycanthropy. If the victim carries belladonna, there is a 25% chance that this cures the affliction if eaten within one hour. The infusion incapacitates the person for 1-4 days and has a 1% chance of killing from poison. Otherwise, a cure disease spell from a 12th-level or higher patriarch must be applied within 3 days, or the victim becomes a lycanthrope in 7-14 days. Other forms of lycanthropy exist, but are extremely rare.",
    "id": "monster_manual_i_lycanthrope_general_notes"
  },
