  "npc_notes": `DEMON, General Notes

Notes: Each type of demon, and especially the high-level demon lords and princes, has many unusual characteristics and extraordinary abilities. Characteristics and abilities common to all demons are given here. Demons are able to move from their own plane into those of Tarterus, Hades, or Pandemonium, or roam the Astral Plane. However, they cannot enter the Material Plane without aid, such as conjuration, gate, or name-speaking. Demons are chaotic and evil. The smarter and stronger rule those of their kind who are weaker and less intelligent. The less intelligent attack without question and fight until slain. Demons of type V and above are not actually slain when their material form is killed in combat; instead, they are forced back to their plane of origin, there to remain until a century has passed or until another aids them to go forth again. If demons are encountered on their own plane, however, they can be slain. No demon can ever be subdued. All are able to divide their attacks amongst two or even three opponents if their means allow.

Demons will never willingly serve anyone or anything. If forced to serve through magic or threat, they continually seek a way to slay their master or captor. Those to whom demons show a liking are typically carried off to the demons’ plane to become slaves, although favored ones. Demons can be summoned by characters of any alignment, but controlling a demon is another matter entirely. A thaumaturgic circle will serve to keep out demons of types I-V. A special pentacle is required for demons of type VI or greater. The threat or reward used to attempt to gain a demon’s service must be handled carefully. Demons are repelled by holy, good relics or artifacts. Demon lords and princes maintain their vital essences in small containers called their amulets. Possession of such an amulet gives temporary power over the demon to whom it belongs, usually for no more than one adventure and never more than one day. Use of an amulet is extremely dangerous. If the amulet leaves the hand of the one commanding the demon, that demon attacks instantly and in its most effective fashion.

Demons frequently roam the Astral and Ethereal Planes, and their attention is attracted by persons in an ethereal state. If the name of a particularly powerful demon is spoken, there is a chance that the demon will hear and turn attention to the speaker. A base 5% chance is suggested. Unless the speaker is prepared to avoid such attention or to control the demon, the demon will immediately attempt to kill the one pronouncing its name. If demon types I through VI are encountered in lair, there will be 1-6 of the same type 75% of the time and 1-6 mixed types I-VI 25% of the time. Types I-III are affected by non-magical weapons; type IV and greater are not. All demons possess infravision, teleportation without error, darkness, and gate, though range and specifics vary. They take full damage from acid, iron weapons, magic missile, and poison; half damage from cold, electricity, fire, and gas; and no damage from silver weapons unless they are also affected by normal weapons, in which case silver does damage according to weapon type. Because of a special form of telepathy, demons understand every intelligent communication. Those of average or better intelligence can converse.`
};

