Notes: Rivalry between demon lords is great, but the enmity between Demogorgon and Orcus is immense and unending. Demogorgon is a terrible opponent. If he fixes the gaze of both heads upon his enemies he is able to hypnotize. This hypnosis affects from 10-100 creatures of 1 to 3 hit dice, 5-40 with 4 to 6 hit dice, 3-24 with 7 to 9 hit dice, 2-12 with 10 to 12 hit dice, and 1-4 with 13 or more hit dice. Those over 15 hit dice save versus magic; all others are automatically hypnotized. This mass hypnosis lasts 1 turn, during which victims follow most instructions absolutely, short of self-destruction, and for 1-6 turns afterwards will tend to believe or carry out the residual effect. Demogorgon’s left head has a gaze with the effect of a rod of beguiling, and his right head causes insanity for 1-6 turns. When used independently, potential victims save versus magic to avoid the eyes.

Demogorgon can lash with his forked tail, striking as a whip-like weapon. Its touch causes energy drain of 1-4 levels, the tail striking as a flail for hit determination. His tentacles are also deadly weapons, each causing 1-6 hit points of damage. Opponents of lesser stature, particularly humans, dwarves, elves, and similar material-plane beings, are subject to rot: a limb becomes useless in 6 melee rounds and drops off in another 6; body hits permanently remove 25% of the victim’s hit points in 6 melee rounds, cumulative per hit. A cure disease cast within the first 6 melee rounds saves the limb, which then heals in 1-4 weeks, and cures body hits entirely if cast within the same limit.

Whenever desiring to do so, Demogorgon may use any one of the following powers: continual darkness, charm person, illusion as a wand, fear as a wand, levitation as a 16th-level magic-user, detect magic, read magic, read languages, detect invisible objects, ESP, dispel magic, clairvoyance, clairaudience, suggestion, water breathing, polymorph self, wall of ice, charm monster, telekinesis of 7,000 gold pieces weight with each head or with one, feeblemind once per day, project image, power word stun once per day, any symbol once per day, sticks to snakes, and gate other demons with an 85% chance of success: 50% chance for a type I-IV and 50% for a type V or VI. Description: Demogorgon is a gigantic reptilian demon 18' tall. He has two heads with the visages of evil baboons or mandrills, blue-green snake-like scales, the body and legs of a giant lizard, twin necks like snakes, a thick forked tail, and great tentacles instead of arms.`
};

